title: holiday potato bake
directions: Remove skin from potatoes; shred into bowl.
Saute onions in butter until tender.
Remove from heat, stir in soup and sour cream.
Pour over potatoes and cheese; mix well.
Turn into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: german chocolate pie
directions: Combine sugar and cocoa.
Be sure lumps are out. Add remaining ingredients, except coconut and nuts. Add coconut and nuts last. Mix with spoon.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Mix together egg and Parmesan cheese.
Mix first 7 ingredients in large bowl.
Pour in buttered 9-inch pie plate.
Top with egg/Parmesan cheese mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix cream cheese and condensed milk; add pudding and milk. Mix well. Fold in half of whipped topping. Alternate layers of cookies, bananas, pudding mix. Top with rest of whipped topping and refrigerate. Serves 12.

title: porcupine balls
directions: Heat soup and water in medium saucepan.
Mix all other ingredients.
Shape in medium-size balls and drop in soup.
Cook on medium heat for 45 minutes, stirring only slightly.
Serve with mashed potatoes or with linguine.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Spread cookie dough on 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 8 to 12 minutes, until light brown.
Cool 15 minutes.
Mix cream cheese and sugar to soften mixture.
Spread onto cookie dough.
Put whatever fresh fruit you want on it.
Cut into squares.

title: icing
directions: Drain pineapple well; add the pudding to pineapple and mix. Slowly fold in the Cool Whip.

title: american turkey burgers(low calorie)
directions: Combine 1 pkg. turkey gravy mix with 1 lb. ground turkey, onions and parsley.
Shape into 4 patties.
Broil or grill.
Top with American Cheese.

title: rum cake
directions: Grease and flour pan.
Bake at 325°.
Sprinkle nuts over bottom of pan.
Mix all cake ingredients and pour over nuts.
Bake for 1 hour; cool.
Prick cake and drizzle glaze over top and sides.
Use Bundt cake pan.

title: five cup salad
directions: Drain orange sections and pineapple.
Add all ingredients and refrigerate until all flavors blend, approximately 2 hours or overnight is fine.

title: brown sugar pie
directions: In a saucepan, combine eggs, sugar, butter and milk.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Add vanilla.
Pour into 2 unbaked pie crusts.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes until crust is golden brown.

title: strawberry yogurt smoothie
directions: Reserve 4 strawberries for garnish.
Use a hand blender or food processor to blend milk, yogurt, strawberries and ice cream until smooth.
Pour into 4 medium size glasses.
Decorate with remaining 4 strawberries.

title: quick fruit salad
directions: Cut apple and orange into small bite size pieces.
Use a small can of mandarin oranges if you don't have an orange.
Chop lettuce as for a salad.
Use other fruit as available like grapes or raisins.
Toss fruits and lettuce together.
Throw in a handful of nuts and marshmallows, if you like.
Mix salad dressing, such as Miracle Whip, and milk together and pour over fruit.
Toss to coat.

title: stromboli
directions: Place frozen bread dough loaf on cookie sheet, rub with olive oil.
Loosely cover with plastic wrap and let thaw and rise.
Roll out into a rectangle shape, about 12 x 9-inches.
Layer meat on bread leaving about 1-inch on both short sides and 1-inch of 1 long side bare (to seal the roll).
Add a layer of cheese.
Roll toward the long bare side, like for a jelly roll.
Fold in the short sides.
Brush with a bit of water to seal.
Place seam side down in baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes until golden brown. Suggestions:

Roast beef slices with cheddar cheese, ham with cheddar or American cheese, pepperoni with a little tomato sauce and shredded Mozzarella cheese (after rolling brush with olive oil and sprinkle with Italian seasonings), cooked ground beef with cheddar or a bit of salsa and taco cheese, finely shredded leftover chicken with...The possibilities are nearly endless!

title: honey corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients until thoroughly moist.
Pour into a greased 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: cream puffs
directions: Heat 1 cup water and add the butter and flour.
Beat with beaters, adding the eggs all at once.
Spoon on cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: delicious cookies
directions: Cream sugars and margarine.
Add oil, egg and vanilla.
Sift and add flour, soda and cream of tartar.
Add Rice Krispies, coconut and pecans to creamed mixture.
Dip 1 teaspoon dough and make into a ball.
Flatten it with a fork.
Cook 10 to 12 minutes. Makes several dozen.

title: zucchini with mozzarella
directions: Peel and finely chop onion.
Peel and crush garlic.
Heat butter and 1 tablespoon oil in a skillet and fry onion and garlic until transparent.
Drain tomatoes.
Add to pan with basil and cook over a low heat for 20 minutes.
Puree mixture in a blender or food processor.

title: flank steak marinade
directions: Marinate 8 hours.
Cook about 7 minutes per side.

title: taco dip
directions: Combine cream cheese and salsa.
Mix well until smooth.
Pour into square dish.
Layer cheese, lettuce and tomato on top of cream cheese mixture.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: ever so easy fruit cake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Grease two 9 x 5-inch loaf pans. Combine flour and soda; set aside.
In a large bowl, combine remaining ingredients.
Blend in dry ingredients.
Pour batter into pans.
Bake approximately 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: rye things
directions: Mix all ingredients and spread on bread. Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Serve warm.
(Freezes easily on cookie sheet. Just pop in oven for quick appetizer.)

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Cut shortening into flour and salt.
Mix egg, vinegar and water together and add to flour/shortening mixture.
Mix altogether.
Makes 3-4 nine inch crusts.

title: chinese casserole
directions: Mix rice seasoning, soup, water and vegetables together.
Pour into large casserole.
Place pork chops on top of rice.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: grandma june's sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugars and margarine.
Add beaten eggs.
Stir in oil and vanilla.
Mix dry ingredients and blend in.
Chill overnight.

title: edwinna's fruit cake
directions: Crumble crackers.
Cut marshmallows into fine pieces.
Whip cream and add it to the marshmallows and pickle juice or wine. Wash raisins and currants and pour boiling water over them; set aside to soak.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream the butter, cream cheese and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each egg.
Slowly add flour; mix in vanilla and salt.
Bake at 300° in a large, greased and floured tube pan for 1 1/2 hours.
Check after 1 1/4 hours.

title: blender custard pie(makes own crust)
directions: Put all in blender and zip up.
Pour into greased and floured pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes to 1 hour.
Pie is done when knife blade comes out clean.

title: yeast rolls(my own recipe)
directions: Warm
all
ingredients	to room temperature.
With whisk dissolve
yeast
in lukewarm water (110°to 115°).
Mix shortening, sugar,
salt
and boiling water.
Let cool.
Mix eggs and yeast and add to cooled mixture.	Add flour, 2 cups at a time, until flour
is
completely
worked into dough.
You may add a little more
flour
if necessary.	Chill dough thoroughly (approximately 4 hours).
Knead for 5 minutes.
Shape into rolls. Brush
tops with

and
cover
with

place in an unheated closed oven with a pan of hot water on shelf below them. Let rise until double in size.
Bake at 425° for

20 minutes or until golden brown.
Brush tops with butter.

title: easy rice pudding
directions: Combine in buttered bowl the milk, rice, sugar and butter. Cook very slowly at least 2 hours at 325° in oven.
Stir pudding down every half hour while it is baking.
Add salt.
Add raisins and nutmeg and bake another half hour.
Pudding thickens after removing from oven.

title: party ryes
directions: Brown hamburger and sausage with oregano.
Add cheese and melt.
After cheese is completely melted, put on party ryes and cook at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: spaghetti
directions: Heat tomatoes and mushrooms.
Season with Nature's Seasons. Serve over spaghetti noodles.
Add grated Parmesan cheese.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain fruit and mix and chill!

title: broccoli bouquet salad
directions: Put dressing over broccoli mixture.
Mix well.
Let set 2 hours or so, then stir well and serve.

title: fudge pie
directions: Put all ingredients in bowl and mix well.
Pour into unbaked pie crust and cook in a 350° preheated oven for 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter crisscrosses
directions: Thoroughly cream shortening, sugars, eggs, and vanilla.
Stir in peanut butter.
Sift dry ingredients; stir into creamed mixture. Drop by rounded teaspoons onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Press with back of floured fork to make crisscrosses.
Bake in 350 degree oven for 9 - 10 minutes.
Makes approximately 5 dozen cookies.

title: piggies (stuffed cabbage)
directions: Remove hard core from cabbage and place head of cabbage in pot of boiling water.
Let cabbage steam in covered pot 10 to 15 minutes (with heat off or warm).
While cabbage is steaming, mix together ground beef, rice, salt, pepper and onion.
When cabbage leaves are easily removed from head of cabbage, fill leaf with approximately 1 heaping tablespoonful of ground beef rice mixture. Fold bottom of leaf up and both sides in.
Roll to close.
Place cabbage roll, flap side down, in baking dish.
Mix tomato soup with about 1/2 can water per can of soup used.
Add brown sugar.
Pour over cabbage rolls.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for about 1 1/2 hours. Can also be done in slow cooker.

title: dill pickles
directions: Sterilize jars.
Wash cucumbers thoroughly; pack in quart jars, 20 each jar.
Add 2 buttons of garlic, 1 dill weed head and stem and 1 or 2 small hot peppers.

title: fresh coconut cake
directions: Make the cake according to the directions on the box and make the frosting while the cake cools.
Yields two 8-inch round layers.

title: better than ever cake
directions: Bake the cake as directed.
Then let cool.
Using a wooden handle on spoon, poke holes in cake (lots of holes).
Fill holes with caramel topping.
Spread whipped topping over cake and sprinkle with crushed Heath bars.

title: banana fruit punch
directions: Mix well and freeze.
Three hours before serving, thaw and add a 64-ounce container of carbonated lemon-lime drink (Diet Sprite can be used).

title: apple slices
directions: Mix eggs and sugar.
Add all other ingredients.
Bake in ungreased 10 x 17-inch or 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar when cool.
Cut in bars.

title: cherry pretzel
directions: Mix pretzels, sugar and oleo. Press into bottom of 9 x 12-inch pan. Mix Cool Whip, cream cheese and powdered sugar. Spread over pretzel mixture. Top with pie filling.
Sprinkle top with broken pretzels and nuts if desired.

title: butterscotch pie um um
directions: Combine brown sugar, flour and salt in a double boiler.
Heat milk and slowly stir into flour and sugar.
Cook over boiling water until mixture begins to thicken.
Beat egg yolks in small bowl and stir about 1 cup hot milk mixture into egg yolks.
Combine the two mixtures in top of double boiler; add butter and cook until thick. Pour into pie shell.
Make meringue by beating egg whites and cream of tartar until stiff.
Gradually add 4 tablespoons sugar to whites and continue beating until it holds a peak.
Cover pie with meringue and bake at 400° until brown.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix and heat until celery and onion are tender.
Add chicken broth to moisten preceding mixture.
Pour into greased casserole. Sprinkle top with 1/2 cup dressing.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: date batter pudding
directions: Mix sugar, flour, dates, milk, baking powder and melted butter.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Combine boiling water, brown sugar and butter; pour over mixture in pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: fast 'n fancy macaroons
directions: Combine all ingredients, mixing well.
Drop from teaspoon 1-inch apart on well-greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly browned.
Remove at once from cookie sheet, using moistened spatula.

title: upside-down cherry cobbler
directions: Thoroughly cream together 1/2 cup of the sugar and butter. Blend in flour, baking powder and salt.
Gradually add milk, mixing thoroughly.
(There will be a few lumps but don't worry about these.)
Spread batter in greased square pan (8 x 8-inch or 9 x 9-inch).
Distribute cherries evenly over batter.
Pour on cherry liquid.
Sprinkle cherries with remaining 1/2 cup of sugar. Bake in oven preheated to 375° for about 45 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: brunch eggs
directions: Combine ingredients; mix lightly.
Pour into slightly greased 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Cover; refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes or until knife inserted in near center comes out clean.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: crock-pot macaroni
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in a greased crock-pot, or spray with Pam.
Put several thin slices of cheese on top. Cook on low for 3 1/2 or 4 hours.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Grease casserole; line bottom with cut up broccoli. Cover with cut up chicken, then mushrooms. In a separate bowl, combine mushroom soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder. Pour over the chicken. Sprinkle cheese over top of casserole. Sprinkle with buttered bread crumbs. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix in order given.
Pour into greased (not floured) bread pan.
Bake 45 minutes in a 350° oven.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: cheese grits
directions: Bring water to a boil. Stir in grits, salt and butter.
Reduce heat and cook 20 minutes. Stir into grits, Cheddar cheese and Parmesan cheese. Season to taste with pepper, cayenne and nutmeg.

title: oreo cookie dessert
directions: Mix melted margarine with crushed cookies.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan, saving 1 cup for topping.
Stir pudding into milk. Stir Cool Whip into pudding mixture and spread on the cookie crust. Sprinkle top with balance of cookie crumbs and refrigerate.

title: mocha cocoa
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a large saucepan. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture comes to a boil. Add milk and vanilla.
Cook until thoroughly heated.
Serve each cup with a cinnamon stick.
Yields 7 cups (about 116 calories per 1 cup serving).

title: pumpkin stew
directions: In a Dutch oven, brown meat in 2 tablespoons oil.
Add water, potatoes, carrots, green pepper, garlic, onion, salt and pepper. Cover and simmer for 2 hours.
Stir in bouillon and tomatoes. Wash pumpkin; cut a 6 to 8-inch circle around top of stem.
Remove top and set aside; discard seeds and lose fibers from inside.

title: divinity fudge
directions: Mix sugar, corn syrup, water and dash of salt in heavy saucepan.
Cook over medium heat until forms soft ball in 1 cup water.
Pour 1/3 mix over stiffly beaten egg whites, beating constantly.

title: breast of chicken casserole
directions: Butter dish.
Layer with dried beef, chicken next.
Cover with bacon.
Pepper to taste.
Mix soup and sour cream; pour over. Bake at 275°, uncovered, for 3 to 4 hours.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Rub pie crust with egg white and bake in 400° oven for 2 minutes.
(Egg white keeps the crust from becoming soggy.) Beat eggs slightly; add sugar and mix well.
Add remaining ingredients and pour into pie crust.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 375° and bake 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake 12 to 20 minutes.

title: corn meal muffins
directions: Mix the meal, baking powder and sugar, then add egg and buttermilk.
Mix well.
Bake in well-greased muffin tins at 450° until brown, approximately 30 minutes.

title: celery casserole
directions: Cook celery in small amount of boiling water; drain.
Combine celery, almonds, chestnuts and mushrooms.
Pour into greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch casserole dish.
Melt 1/4 cup plus 1 tablespoon of butter and blend in flour and cook for 1 minute.
Add chicken broth and half and half.
Pour over veggies.
Combine cheese and bread crumbs and drizzle with melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Enjoy!

title: best cutout cookies
directions: Cream the margarine and both sugars.
Combine eggs and water; add to creamed mixture.
Mix dry ingredients; add to mixture with vanilla.
Chill for at least 30 minutes.
Keeps for days in fridge.
Roll 1/8 to 1/4-inch thick for crisp cookies, or 1/4 to 1/2-inch thick for thick and softer cookies.
Bake until golden.

title: velveeta cheese fudge
directions: Melt cheese and butter over low heat and add to the dry ingredients.
Mix well and place on 2 cookie sheets lined with wax paper (or jelly pans).
Put in cool place.
When cooled, cut and store in cool place.

title: barbecue shrimp and scallops(serves 4)
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Add all but shrimp and scallops; simmer for 5 minutes.
Pour butter sauce into large pan that can be put on grill.
Add shrimp and scallops.
Put this pan on grill with medium heat.
Bring to simmer; let simmer for 20 minutes. Remove shrimp and scallops from sauce and serve.

title: sauteed squash
directions: Saute ingredients in black skillet over medium heat 5 to 6 minutes.
Stir.
Serve hot.

title: layered mexican salad with jalapeno dressing
directions: Garnish with avocado slices.
Sprinkle with bacon.
Serve dressing on the side.
Yields 6 servings.

title: baby doe's beer cheese soup
directions: Melt butter; add carrots and onion.
Cook until tender.
Blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Add milk, stirring constantly.
Add Cheez Whiz.
Blend in beer.

title: mexican chicken
directions: In a 9 x 13 inch pan, add all ingredients together.
Add some more crushed Doritos and top with some more shredded cheese.
Bake in 350 degree oven for 30 minutes.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix together.
Pour into large baking dish or pan and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: beef and noodles
directions: Put roast in roaster pan and add water to top of meat.
Bring almost to boil.
Turn heat down and simmer about 3 hours covered. Remove meat and bring water to boil.
Add beef bouillon cubes, one for about each cup of liquid.
Add noodles and turn heat down to simmer.
Cook for at least 1 hour.

title: make-ahead salad
directions: Layer in large bowl:
lettuce, cauliflower and red onion. Combine mayonnaise, sugar and Parmesan cheese and spread on top; sprinkle with bacon.
Refrigerate at least 6 hours before serving in an airtight container.
Toss before serving.
Makes large portions; may cut ingredients in half.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add the eggs and the pumpkin; beat thoroughly.
Sift together dry ingredients, add to the creamed mixture in thirds with the water.
Beat enough until the batter is smooth.
Stir in nuts.
Pour batter into greased and floured cans (4 smooth ones) or two loaf pans.
Bake in a 350° oven for 35 minutes or until done.
When baked (test with a toothpick) roll can and loosen, cake will come out easily.

title: easy punch
directions: Mix ingredients and serve with crushed ice.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix and refrigerate overnight (do not freeze).
Red and green cherries could be added for color.

title: boiled cookies
directions: Cook sugar, milk, margarine (or butter) and cocoa for 1 1/2 minutes.
Start counting time when mixture has reached full boil. Remove from heat and add oats, vanilla (and peanut butter if desired).
Mix until blended.
Spoon on wax paper.
Place wax paper on top of brown grocery bag.

title: christmas cranberry salad
directions: Chop the cranberries in chopper or blender; coarse.
Add sugar and let sit in refrigerator overnight.
Add marshmallows, pineapple and pecans.
Whip the whipping cream and stir into mixture. Refrigerate until time to serve.
Serves a million and three people.
Keeps well for 2 or 3 days.
Excellent with any kind of meat dish.

title: ham spaghetti supreme
directions: Saute 2 tablespoons oleo with onion.
Add next 5 ingredients and cook until cheese melts.
Cook spaghetti noodles.
Mix well with first 7 ingredients.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch pan and top with last 3 ingredients.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: be-be salad(rosamarina)
directions: To fruit juices, add sugar, flour and lemon juice.
Cook until thick like pudding.
Add 2 beaten eggs and fruit.
Cool mixture and noodles.
Add Cool Whip to fruit and noodles; mix well.

title: granola
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Pour oats into a large shallow baking pan.
Combine sugar, oil, water, cinnamon and salt.
Stir into oats and mix well.
Spread evenly in pan.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes or until lightly toasted, stirring every 10 minutes. Remove from oven.
Cool; store in a tightly covered container.

title: bacon-cheddar potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes until done.
When cool, cut into chunks.
Melt butter in large frying pan.
Add potatoes, cheese and bacon bits. Season with salt, pepper and seasoning salt to taste.
Cook until cheese is melted.
(Great for left over baked potatoes.)

title: super chunk jumbles
directions: Beat butter and sugars until fluffy.
Beat in egg and vanilla. Mix in flour, soda and salt.
Stir in white chocolate, walnuts and raisins.
Drop by tablespoon, 1 1/2-inches apart, on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Cool 2 to 3 minutes.
Remove from sheet.
Cool on wire racks.
Yields 3 dozen.

title: peach pie
directions: In a brownie pan, place drained peaches evenly over the bottom.
Sprinkle cake mix over peaches.
Pour juice over the cake mix. Dot with butter over the entire mixture.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool.
Cut in squares and serve with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: coconut cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed.
Add 2 teaspoons of vanilla flavoring to batter.
Make 4 layers.

title: beef and bean casserole
directions: Brown hamburger meat and onion in oil.
Combine with beans and catsup.
Pour into baking dish.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs if desired (optional).
Bake at 375° for about 30 minutes.

title: waist watcher's cauliflower soup
directions: Chop cauliflower and onion in food processor.
Combine vegetables with water, bouillon cubes and salt in large saucepan. Cover and simmer about 15 minutes or until tender.
Stir in dry milk powder.
Shred cheese and add to soup.
Stir until cheese melts.
Makes 8 servings.

title: melt-in-your-mouth chicken pie
directions: Place chicken in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bring to boil the broth and soup.
Combine flour, salt, pepper, buttermilk and oleo.
Mix to form batter.
Pour broth mixture over chicken.
Spoon batter over top.
Bake at 425° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: tomato cucumber mix
directions: Dice tomatoes. Slice cucumber. Chop onion and mix together. Mix together 1/4 cup sugar and 1 cup mayonnaise. Pour this over tomato mixture. Sprinkle with cheese. Add bacon bits.

title: turtles
directions: Melt caramels and water over hot water and add nuts.
Drop by teaspoon on buttered cookie sheet.
Cool.
Melt chocolate and paraffin over hot water.
Dip caramels and drop on wax paper.

title: fruited chicken 'n rice salad
directions: Prepare rice pilaf following package directions.
Place in large bowl; cover and chill.

title: dandelion salad
directions: Tear the greens into bite size pieces and place in bowl.
Mix the salt, pepper, dry mustard, sugar, onion (minced), salad oil, vinegar and water; pour over greens.
Toss bacon or ham with greens.
Top with egg slices and serve.

title: fruit-pretzel salad
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix pretzels, sugar and margarine.
Press mixture into 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake 12 minutes.

title: peanut blossoms
directions: Cream shortening, peanut butter and sugars.
Add egg, milk and vanilla; beat well.
Sift together the flour, soda and salt; blend in gradually.
Mix thoroughly.
Shape by rounded teaspoonfuls into balls.
Roll in sugar.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 8 minutes.
Remove from oven; place a solid milk chocolate kiss on top of each cookie.
Press down so that cookie cracks around edge.
Return to oven; bake 2 to 5 minutes longer. This recipe makes about 4 dozen cookies.

title: low fat chicken tostados
directions: Combine chicken, lettuce, peppers and tomatoes in a large bowl. Heat tortillas by placing them one at a time in a dry skillet. Turn once until brown and puffy. To assemble:
Place a tortilla on a plate and top with some of the chicken mixture. Garnish with sour cream, salsa and cheese. Serves 6.

title: velvet cheese soup
directions: Heat and dissolve cheese and milk.
Add chicken, beef seasonings, butter and water.
Add broccoli and pimento.
Heat all and serve.

title: four bean casserole
directions: Brown bacon and drain fat.
Crumble.
Brown hamburger with onion.
Add the 4 cans of beans (don't drain liquid), catsup, brown sugar and crumbled bacon.
Mix and put in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 8.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Cook chicken. Then skin and dice up chicken.
Save chicken broth.
Cook broccoli.
Let cool and chop fine.
Mix dressing mix together using the chicken broth to replace water according to package directions.
Then add chopped broccoli to dressing mix. Then add the chicken and cream of chicken soup.
Sprinkle the Mozzarella cheese on top.
Cook at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: texas beef casserole
directions: Cook meat until done.
Add sugar and sauce until well blended. Cook noodles as directed on package.
Add cream cheese and sour cream to noodles.
Stir until melted, then add chopped onions. Add the noodle mixture and the meat mixture together and mix well. Pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Cover with grated cheese. Place in either warm oven or microwave on High just long enough to melt the cheese.

title: cheese bran balls
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Blend flour, salt and red pepper in a bowl.
Add shortening and cheese, beat until light and fluffy.
Mix in cereal.
Shape into balls, flatten slightly and place on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: pistachio fruit salad
directions: Mix pudding into Cool Whip. Add rest of ingredients and mix well. Chill about 3 hours before serving.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Place chicken in baking pan.
Mix other ingredients and spoon over chicken.
Bake 45 minutes at 375°.

title: tarleni
directions: Chop onion and pepper; saute in oil until tender.
Add meat; stir and cook until browned.
In large bowl, place mushrooms, tomatoes, corn and 1/2 of cheese.
Cook noodles in salted water until tender; drain.
Add to mixture in bowl.
Add meat mixture; blend well.
Pour in greased 3-quart casserole dish.
Let stand 12 to 24 hours.
Cover and bake at 400° for 45 minutes.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese and bake uncovered for 10 to 15 minutes longer. Serves 6 to 8.

title: barbecue green beans
directions: Mix all ingredients and cook 4 hours in crock-pot or covered in oven at 250°.

title: crispy barbecued chicken
directions: Dip chicken into barbecue sauce.
Coat with crushed stuffing. Place chicken on rack in a shallow roasting pan.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour or until chicken is done.
Prep time:
10 minutes. Serves 4.

title: cheesy corn casserole
directions: In large bowl, beat egg; add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Bake in a greased 2-quart baking dish at 350° for 1 hour. Yields 10 servings.

title: chocolate sour cream pound cake
directions: Beat butter 2 minutes until creamy.
Add sugar 5 to 7 minutes, add eggs one at a time.
Mix dry ingredients.
Add to creamed mixture.
Mix low speed until blended.
Stir in vanilla.
Add 4 ounces black walnuts.
Mix well.
Grease and flour tube pan.
Bake on 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes or until done.
Cool in pan 10 to 15 minutes.
Remove from pan and finish cooling.

title: nancy reagan's rancho california rice
directions: In a large skillet, saute onion in margarine until limp.
Add rice, sour cream, cottage cheese and bay leaf.
Mix together.
In a buttered casserole, put layer of rice, then a layer of chilies, and 1/2 of the grated Cheddar cheese; repeat.
Bake for 25 minutes at 375°.
Yields 8 servings.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Saute onion in butter until tender.
Blend in flour, salt, paprika, mustard and pepper and cook until bubbly.
Remove from heat.
Add milk gradually.
Boil 1 minute, stirring constantly. Remove from heat; add corn and egg.
Pour into 1-quart baking dish. Top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: impossible pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat eggs and sugar together.
Add flour and beat.
Add other ingredients and pour in greased pie plate. Bake about 30 minutes or until firm.

title: chicken enchiladas(non-fat or lo-fat ingredients may be used.)
directions: Remove tortillas from refrigerator; set aside. Melt margarine in skillet; cook onion until tender. Stir in chilies, soup and sour cream; mix well. Reserve 3/4 cup sauce; set aside. Stir in chicken and 1/2 cup cheese to remaining sauce in skillet. Warm tortillas according to package directions. Fill tortillas with chicken mixture; roll up. Spray baking dish with Pam and place seam side down. Combine reserved sauce and milk; spoon over rolled tortillas. Top with remaining cheese and bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: bavarian red cabbage
directions: Place all ingredients in crock-pot in order listed.
Cover and cook on low for 8 to 10 hours (high for 3 hours).
Stir well before serving.
Excellent served with a rich meat.

title: cranberry-pear relish
directions: Combine the cranberries, pears, onion, vinegar and pickling spice in a 9-inch microwave plate.
Cover and microwave on High power for 9 minutes, stirring twice.
Uncover.
Stir in sugar and salt.
Let cool and divide among 4 (6 ounce) jars.
Cover and chill.

title: barbecued spareribs
directions: Brown spareribs with salt and pepper.
Cook onion in fat until golden.
Add remaining ingredients.
Heat to a boil; reduce heat. Simmer for 20 minutes.
Pour over spareribs.
Bake for 1 hour and 30 minutes at 350°.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate.

title: lime congealed salad
directions: Cream together cheese, Jell-O and mayonnaise, making a paste. Heat pineapple juice (do not boil); add to paste and dissolve good.
Refrigerate until partially thickened, then add pineapple, nuts and celery.
Chill.
Use a 3-quart rectangular dish.

title: banana bread(dutch)
directions: Mix and bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Roll dough; cut with cookie cutters.
Sugar before baking or bake and frost with powdered sugar frosting.
It helps to mix up the dough and chill before rolling.

title: sweet and sour meatballs(serves 10 to 12)
directions: Simmer chili sauce and grape jelly until jelly is melted.
Mix remaining ingredients and form into balls.
Simmer in sauce 20 to 30 minutes or until meatballs are fully cooked.

title: lemon dessert
directions: Mix butter, flour and nuts together. Pat into a 9 x 13 inch baking pan. Bake 10 to 15 minutes at 350°. Cool.

title: 10 minute cookies
directions: Cover cookie sheet with graham crackers.
Combine all of the ingredients;
melt
to a bubble up, do not boil.
Pour hot mixture over
graham
crackers.
Bake
for 10 minutes at 375°. Cut into bars while hot.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: buttercream icing
directions: Combine pineapple, including juice, with pudding.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Fold in thawed Cool Whip.
Delicious on angel food cake and handy because all the needed ingredients can be stored in the freezer and one the shelf.
Leftovers can be frozen.

title: layered vegetable casserole
directions: In casserole layer ingredients:
Brussels sprouts, 1/3 can soup, 1/3 cup cheese, broccoli, 1/3 can soup, 1/3 cup cheese, cauliflower, remaining soup, then remaining cheese.
Bake for 20 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Mix together pecans, flour and margarine.
Press into 8 x 8-inch casserole dish and bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Mix together cream cheese, 1 cup Cool Whip and confectioners sugar.
Pour over cooled crust.
Mix pudding as directed on box.
Pour over cream cheese mixture.
Spread Cool Whip over top.
Chill well and serve cold.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all together.
Place in casserole.
Top with shredded Cheddar cheese and bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350° to 375°.
Mix all ingredients into a large bowl.
Put into square cake pan. Cook for 1 hour.
Remove. Cover with ketchup.
Return to oven for 15 to 20 minutes to finish cooking.

title: chicken and peppers
directions: In bowl combine chicken with soup mix, 1 tablespoon oil, 1 tablespoon soy sauce, garlic and 1 tablespoon cornstarch. Marinate for 20 minutes.
In skillet heat remaining oil and cook peppers and celery over high heat, stirring frequently for 3 minutes.
Add green onions and cook 2 minutes.
Remove from pan. Add chicken to skillet and cook 3 minutes.
In separate bowl mix remaining soy sauce and cornstarch with water and sugar.
Add to chicken in skillet with vegetable.
Simmer for 3 minutes.

title: fruit cocktail salad
directions: Drain the juice from fruit cocktail, sprinkle the jello on it. Fold in sour cream and Cool Whip.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: black bean quesadilla sandwiches
directions: Combine beans, green chiles and 2 tablespoons tomatoes; stir well.
Spread bean mixture evenly onto 4 tortillas.
Top each evenly with goat cheese.
Top with remaining tortillas.
Place sandwiches on an ungreased baking sheet.
Top each sandwich with 1 teaspoon chopped tomatoes.
To serve, cut into wedges.
Yields 4 servings.

title: stuffed fish fillets(may be fresh or frozen)
directions: Sprinkle fish with salt and pepper.
Place half of fish in well greased dish, 12 x 8 x 2-inch.
Place stuffing on top of fish and put remaining fish on top. Brush with oil or melted oleo. Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: christmas hard candy
directions: Mix together and stir sugar, syrup and water.
Boil to 300° (use candy thermometer).
Remove from heat; add food color and candy oil.
Pour onto pan or board covered with powdered sugar. Cut in pieces with scissors while cooling.

title: chocolate chip frosting
directions: Combine sugar, milk and margarine.
Cook to a good boil.
Add chocolate chips and beat until thick.

title: cream puffs
directions: Put shortening and water in 2-quart saucepan and bring to boil. Add flour and cook until thick, stirring constantly.
When mixture gathers into a mass, remove from range and place into mixing bowl. Add eggs, one at a time, mixing thoroughly after each egg.
Place in mound on greased cookie sheet about 1 1/2-inches apart.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 400°.
Remove from pan.
Place puffs on wire rack to cool.
Take a sharp knife and slit a small hole in base of puff. This permits steam to escape and keeps puff from falling.

title: ham and cheese ring
directions: Beat eggs, flour, milk, baking powder and salt with electric mixer. Fold mixture into liquid mixture. Pour into greased and floured tube pan. Sprinkle top with crisp fried bacon bits. Bake 55 to 60 minutes at 350°. Serve slices like cake.

title: mild mexican jerky
directions: Mix all spices together.
Sprinkle on both sides of meat. Cover tightly and marinate 6 to 12 hours in the refrigerator.
Dry at 145° for about 4 hours.
The dehydrator works best.

title: rhubarb bread
directions: Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: honey lemon chicken
directions: Salt and pepper chicken; arrange in shallow baking dish.
Mix catsup and honey together.
Pour over chicken, turning once to coat both sides.
Slice lemon into thin slices; lay on top of chicken.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake for 45 minutes more.

title: fettucini
directions: Cook noodles; drain and rinse.
Melt butter with cream before noodles are done.
Put noodles back in big boiler.
Pour butter and cream over noodles.
Add cheese; mix well.
Stir until cheese is melted.
Serve hot.

title: orange roughy fish with kiwi fruit
directions: Place fish in glass dish which has been sprayed with Pam. Sprinkle with salt, garlic, pepper and oregano to taste.
Add kiwi slices.
Slowly squeeze and dribble lime over fish.
Add nuts. Dribble margarine over all.
Cover with tin foil to keep from drying out fish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes until flaky.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together.
Beat in eggs one at a time.
Sift dry ingredients and add alternately with buttermilk to first mixture.
Add coconut flavoring and coconut.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan at 350° for 50 minutes to 1 hour.

title: scalloped pineapple
directions: Cream margarine, eggs and sugar together, then (in mixer) add gradually the pineapple, vanilla and bread cubes.
Mix all together with juice and milk gradually.
Put in greased casserole. Bake 50 minutes at 350°, uncovered.

title: french onion soup
directions: In large saucepan, simmer 2 cans beef bouillon and 2 cubes beef bouillon, sliced onions and Worcestershire sauce for 1 hour. Fill four oven-worthy bowls with simmered ingredients.
Add croutons; sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Place sliced Mozzarella cheese on top.
Bake in 300° oven for 20 minutes or until cheese has melted.

title: sesame honey candy
directions: Take fresh graham crackers and spread with peanut butter.
Top with a little honey.
Yum!

title: old-fashioned cream pie
directions: Combine flour, cornstarch, sugar, nutmeg and butter until crumbly.
Put in unbaked pie shell and pour in cream.
Bake in 400° oven for 1 hour.

title: pig feet 'n sauerkraut
directions: Alternate layers of
pig feet and sauerkraut.
Allow to boil 5 minutes.
Add
other
ingredients
and let simmer until vegetables are tender.

title: baked chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients, except soup and mayonnaise.
Combine soup and mayonnaise and add to chicken mixture.
Stir lightly.
Put in casserole and bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: quick and easy party cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to package directions.
Bake and cool.
With a large meat fork, punch holes in top of cake.

title: double chocolate brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.

Combine butter, sugar, water and 1 cup chips in a large saucepan. Cook over low heat until all chocolate and butter are melted and thoroughly mixed. Remove from heat. Gradually add the remaining ingredients and stir well. Spread mixture in a greased and floured 9 x 13 pan. Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until set.

title: pork barbecue
directions: Cook shoulder until it falls from the bone.
When cool, shred meat and set aside.
Cook vegetables slowly in the oil until tender.
Add sugar, salt, dry mustard, red pepper and tomato paste.
Simmer for 30 minutes, then add vinegar.

title: pecan cookies
directions: Cream sugar and butter until fluffy.
Add eggs and beat well. Sift together dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture.
Stir in nuts.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Top with pecan halves.
Bake at 325° for about 12 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: cheesy bacon meat loaf
directions: Mix meat, egg, cheese, milk, bread crumbs and seasonings. Shape into loaf in 9 x 5 pan. Top with bacon slices. Bake at 400° for 1 hour or until center is no longer pink. Let stand 3 minutes before removing from pan. Cut into slices to serve.

title: mushroom dip(double or triple)
directions: Saute onion in the butter; add mushrooms, salt and pepper. Saute on low heat.
Add cream cheese, sour cream and Worcestershire sauce.
Stir until melted.

title: chili
directions: Brown ground chuck and drain.
Put all other ingredients in crockpot and add ground chuck.
Cook on low heat all day.

title: toll house pie
directions: Mix all together and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: coconut cake
directions: Bake cake according to package directions in a 9 x 13 pan. Use handle of wooden spoon to poke holes throughout cake while it is still hot. Mix cream of coconut and condensed milk. Pour over cake while it is still hot. Let cool. Top with Cool Whip and coconut.

title: puff filo spinach squares
directions: Arrange 6 sheets of the filo dough in the bottom of a 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan, brushing butter or margarine between each sheet.
Allow edges of dough to overlap sides of pan.
Spread souffle evenly over dough; sprinkle with water chestnuts.
Top with remaining filo, brushing butter between each sheet.
Fold edges of filo toward center; brush with remaining butter.
Score top layers of filo into 48 squares or diamonds.
Bake in a 400° oven 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool slightly; cut through all layers.
Serve warm or cold.
Makes 48 appetizers.

title: baked lasagna
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch baking pan, arrange layers of the meat sauce, lasagna noodles, Jack cheese, Ricotta cheese and Parmesan cheese. Repeat once or twice, topping with meat sauce and Parmesan cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbling.
Allow to stand a few minutes before serving.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: 1. Saute onions, garlic, and mushrooms in oil. Cook until onion is golden.
2. Add ground beef, cook and stir for 5 minutes.
3. Add tomato paste, tomato juice, sugar, and seasonings.
Simmer for at least 1 hour.
4. Add water as needed but the sauce should be thick and
smooth.

title: chicken and green bean casserole
directions: Boil chicken and chip into bite-size pieces.
Boil rice in chicken broth and drain.
Combine all remaining ingredients.
Pour into large casserole dish.
Bake at 425° for 30 to 40 minutes until top is golden brown.
Serves 4.

title: oat raisin cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients and drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto greased baking sheets.
Bake in a preheated 375° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes about 2 dozen.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown meat, drain off fat.
Add next five ingredients and simmer, covered, for 30 minutes.
Cook noodles according to directions.
Drain and rinse.
Combine all remaining ingredients, except for Mozzarella cheese.
Place half the noodles in a large cake pan; spread with half the cottage cheese filling; add half the Mozzarella cheese and half the meat sauce.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: super cherry dessert
directions: Line a 9-inch square dish with graham cracker squares, fitting in to cover the bottom.
Combine pudding mix and milk; beat well. Allow to stand 15 minutes.
Fold in whipped topping.
Pour half of pudding on crackers.
Add another layer of crackers.
Top with remaining pudding and another layer of crackers.
Spoon cherry pie filling on top.
Refrigerate at least 3 hours.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: boiled cookies
directions: Mix ingredients together and boil 1 1/2 minutes; remove from heat and
add
oats.
Mix well and add vanilla flavoring. Drop on wax paper.
Let cool.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding with milk and condensed milk.
Add whipping cream and sour cream.
Mix well.
Layer dish with wafers, then bananas and pudding.
Crumble wafers on top.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight.

title: garden zucchini pie
directions: In a large mixing bowl combine 1 egg, onion and Parmesan cheese.
Stir in potatoes.
Transfer mixture to a 9-inch pie plate or a 10-inch quiche dish.
Pat the mixture in the bottom and up the sides.
Bake uncovered at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes or golden brown.
Cool.
Reduce oven to 350°.

title: all american apple pie
directions: Pare apples and slice thin.
Mix sugar, flour, salt and spices.
Add to apples.
Fill a 9-inch pastry lined pie pan.
Dot with butter.
Adjust top crust.
Bake at 400° for 50 minutes.
If apples aren't tart, add 1 tablespoon lemon juice.

title: paprika cheese roll
directions: Cream above ingredients until thoroughly mixed.
Add lemon juice to reach a good consistency.
On a piece of aluminum foil, sprinkle sheet heavily with paprika and roll cheese into a loaf or log-like shape, covering the cheese outside thickly with paprika. Refrigerate until needed to serve.
Can be made two weeks ahead. Can be used as two cheese balls with nuts also.

title: cherry balls
directions: Mix strawberry jello with Eagle Brand milk.
Mix well.
Add coconut and pecans.
Mix well and shape into balls.
Roll into powdered sugar and refrigerate.

title: no knead roll dough
directions: Place all ingredients into a large mixing bowl in order.
Beat at medium low of mixer for 3 minutes.
Stir in 3 to 3 1/4 cups of flour to make a stiff dough.
Cover; let rest for 15 minutes. Toss on floured surface until no longer sticky.
Shape into dinner rolls.
Cover; let rise in warm place until doubled.
Bake at 400° until brown.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Spray loaf pan with Pam.
Bake in loaf pan 45 minutes at 450°.

title: chex party mix
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Melt butter in a 15 x 10 x 2-inch roasting pan.
Remove.
Stir in seasoned salt and Worcestershire sauce.
Gradually add cereal, pretzels and nuts, mixing until all pieces are coated.
Bake one hour.
Stir every 15 minutes.
Spread on absorbent paper to cool.

title: walnut tassups
directions: Mix together cream cheese, margarine and flour.
Make small balls.
Put in muffin tin and work with thumb to form cup.
Fill 3/4 with filling and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: crock-pot chicken
directions: Skin the chicken and place in a crock-pot.
Stir all the other ingredients together and pour over the chicken.
Cook for 6 hours on low or 4 hours on high.

title: chickenette
directions: Cook spaghetti, using package directions; drain.
Combine with chicken, pimento, green pepper, onion, soup, broth, salt, pepper and 1 1/4 cups cheese in bowl; mix well.
Spoon into a 9-inch square baking dish.
Top with remaining 1/2 cup cheese.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes, or until bubbly.

title: fruitcake
directions: Grease three 8 x 3 loaf pans. Preheat oven to 275 degrees.

title: mainstay inn chicken pies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Heat chicken, 1/2 cup milk, sour cream and soup to boiling.
Spoon into 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish.
Beat remaining ingredients (except cheese) with wire whisk.
Pour over chicken mixture.
Sprinkle with cheese and paprika.
Bake, uncovered, until top is set and soup mixture bubbles around edges, 20 to 25 minutes.

title: liver with peppers and onions
directions: In a bowl, combine flour, salt and pepper.
Add liver; toss to coat.
Heat 2 tablespoons oil in a large skillet.
Add onion and peppers; cook until crisp-tender.
Remove from pan; set aside. Add remaining oil to the skillet.
Cook and stir liver for 5 to 7 minutes, or until no pink remains.
In a small bowl, combine beef broth, soy sauce and cornstarch; stir into liver.
Cook and stir constantly until sauce thickens.
Return vegetables to the skillet; cook until heated through.
Serve over rice or noodles. Serves 4 to 6.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Fix broccoli according to package directions; drain.
Mix egg, mayonnaise and soup.
Add to broccoli.
Mix in cheese and optional items.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 350° until bubbling noted.
Use 1 1/2 to 2-quart casserole.

title: travichi
directions: Marinate fish 3 hours in ReaLemon, salt, pepper and marinade. Combine all ingredients. Refrigerate several hours. Serve on crackers. Servings: 1 gallon.

title: grill roasted corn
directions: One to two ears of corn per person is serving size.

title: rob's chicken breasts
directions: Pat chicken breasts dry.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Dust each piece with flour.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook sugar, milk, butter and salt to form a soft ball. Add peanut butter and marshmallow cream just before removing from heat.
Beat until mixture is creamy thick. Add nuts, if desired.

title: tangy pot roast
directions: Salt and pepper meat.
Place in deep roasting pan.
Slice 4 onions and cover meat.
Mix mushrooms, tomato sauce, water and garlic and pour over meat.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Add carrots, potatoes and remaining onions (sliced) to pan.
Sprinkle with Worcestershire sauce.
Top with canned gravy and bake 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Place meat on platter and surround with veggies.
Top with gravy.
Serves 6.

title: baked macaroni
directions: Mix together 1st 5 ingredients to make a white sauce.
Add 1 cup grated cheese to the white sauce.
Mix mixture with macaroni and sprinkle 1 cup of cheese mixture on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: grandma's mincemeat
directions: Cook sausage, wine and water.
Add other ingredients and cook about 15 minutes.
Put in jars and process.
Makes about 8 quarts.

title: five minute mousse
directions: Beat Jello pudding and milk with wire whisk for 1 minute. Stir in cool whip.
Spoon into 6 dessert dishes or serve as you like. Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: failure-proof gravy
directions: Blend flour with drippings in heavy skillet over low heat until smooth (2 to 3 minutes).
Gradually add mixture of Carnation and water.
Stir constantly over low heat until thickened and smooth.

title: low-fat bran muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix flour, baking soda, baking powder and cinnamon in a large bowl.
Mix cereal, milk and sugar in another bowl. Let stand 10 minutes. Stir in eggs and applesauce. Add to flour mixture. Stir or mix in mixer (batter will be lumpy).
Spoon into cupcake tins sprayed with Pam or similar product.
Makes 12 with tins 2/3 full.
Bake 18 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: swiss onion bake
directions: In skillet, melt butter; add onion and cook until tender. Spread in bottom of 10 x 6 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish.
Top with sliced eggs.
Sprinkle with cheese.
In saucepan, combine soup, milk and mustard.
Heat and stir until smooth.
Pour over casserole, being sure some goes to bottom of pan.
Place bread slices on top, overlapping a little.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: pudding cake
directions: Cook pudding according to package directions.
Stir in cake mix.
Spread in a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch cake pan. Sprinkle with chips and pecans.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: marinated halibut tacos
directions: To make marinade, in a small bowl, combine butter, jelly, onion, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Place fish in a 9 X 9 inch baking dish.
Brush both sides with the marinade. Cover and refrigerate 15 minutes.
Meanwhile, prepare and preheat an outdoor grill or broiler.
Remove fish from marinade and grill over hot coals or under broiler 5 minutes on each side or until fish is tender and flakes with a fork.
Slice into 1/2 inch wide pieces. Place several pieces on one side of each tortilla.
Top each with tomato, lettuce and a dollop of sour cream.
Fold tortillas. Serve with a small dish of jelly on the side.
Makes 6 servings.

title: onion-smothered steak
directions: Microwave Directions:
Pound steak to 1/2-inch thickness; cut into 3/4-inch wide strips.
Combine flour, salt and pepper; dredge steak in flour.
Preheat a 10-inch browning dish at High for 8 to 9 minutes.
Add oil, then steak; stir until sizzling stops. Microwave at High for 3 minutes, or until browned, stirring once. Add remaining ingredients; stir.
Cover with lid or wax paper; microwave at Medium (50% power) for 30 to 35 minutes, stirring at 10-minute intervals.
Remove bay leaf before serving.

title: orange chicken breast
directions: Pound chicken breasts to 1/4-inch thickness.
Sprinkle with thyme, salt and pepper.
Saute chicken and onion with butter for 2 or 3 minutes.
Add orange sections. Serve while hot over white rice.

title: pecan pie
directions: Melt
butter;
remove
from
heat.
Add both sugars and salt. Mix
well.	Add
eggs; mix well.
Add syrup and pecans. Pour into pie shell.	Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: piccalilli
directions: Remove label from 1 (12 ounce) jar sweet mixed pickles.
Drain juice and thoroughly fill jar with sugar (about 1 1/2 cups), being sure all space between pickles is filled.
Insert table knife in jar to make room for sugar.
Let stand for a few minutes and add more sugar, if possible.
Put a lid securely on jar.
Invert jar and place in refrigerator.
Turn jar occasionally so the sugar dissolves and pickles crystallize.
After a week, refrigeration is not necessary.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix pumpkin, sugar, salt and spices.
Add eggs and milk and mix.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake in oven at 425° for 15 minutes, then 350° for 45 minutes.
When knife comes out clean from center of pie, it is done.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Soften gelatin in cold water. Dissolve over hot water. Blend into mayonnaise and whipped cream. Fold in remaining ingredients. Pour into refrigerator tray; freeze until firm. 8 servings.

title: broccoli bake
directions: Melt 2 tablespoons margarine; stir in flour and salt.
Add milk gradually, mixing until smooth.
Cook until mixture boils, stirring constantly.
Add cheese, stirring until melted.
Mix in 1/4 cup corn flake crumbs.
Arrange cooked broccoli in baking dish.
Pour cheese sauce over broccoli.
Toss remaining 1/2 cup cornflake crumbs with 2 tablespoons margarine, melted.
Sprinkle over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: paper sack apple pie
directions: Mix 1/2 cup flour, 1/2 cup sugar and cinnamon together.
Roll sliced apples in mixture.
Put in pie crust.
Sprinkle with lemon juice.
Mix with fork the following:
1/2 cup sugar, 1/2 cup flour and 1 stick oleo.
Place in brown paper sack on cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken with mushroom sauce
directions: Sprinkle each piece of chicken with onion powder, pepper and soy sauce.
Fry chicken in pan on medium heat (spray pan with Pam) until brown, approximately 15 minutes each side.
If chicken seems too dry, add 1/4 cup water and soy sauce.
Mix soup with 1/2 can milk and 1/2 can water.
Add to chicken.
Simmer over low-medium heat for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: springerle cookies
directions: Roll slightly more than 1/4 inch thick.
Then use springerle roller to create design.
Cut out and place on well-greased cookie sheet.
Let stand overnight in cool room.
Bake 20 minutes at 300°.
Store 3 weeks in tightly covered jar.

title: creamy orange salad
directions: In a bowl dissolve gelatin in

water. In a mixing bowl beat cream cheese until fluffy. Gradually blend in the gelatin mixture until smooth. Stir in the milk and fold in whipped topping. Transfer to a serving bowl. Refrigerate for 4 hours or until firm. If desired garnish with oranges.

title: five o'clock buns
directions: Combine water, sugar and yeast.
Add salt, oil and then eggs. Blend in flour until dough is formed.
Mix at 5 o'clock in the afternoon.
Punch down every hour. Shape into buns at about 10:00 or 11:00 in the evening. Cover and let set on cupboard until morning. Bake at 350° for 15 or 20 minutes. Will make about 100 small buns.
Freezes well.

title: smoky beef chowder
directions: In a medium saucepan, cook chopped celery and onion in butter until onion is tender.
Blend in flour, salt and basil.
Stir in smoked beef.
Add milk all at once.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Stir in the shredded cheese until melted.
Stir in parsley; heat through.
Makes 3 to 4 servings.

title: valley ranch pancakes
directions: Add eggs to buttermilk.
Sift dry ingredients; add to liquid mixture and stir just until mixed.
If thicker pancakes are desired, add more flour.

title: hopkins county stew
directions: Boil chicken in water with celery and seasonings until tender, about 1 1/2 hours.
Debone and cut up chicken into chunks and return to sauce.
Simmer, covered, about 2 hours.

title: snowflake salad
directions: Mix all together and put in refrigerator.

title: pumpkin pie squares
directions: *May use 2 or 3 teaspoons pumpkin pie spice.

title: lemon mint peas
directions: In large skillet, melt butter.
Add bread and brown over medium heat until toast-like.
In 2-quart casserole dish, combine sugar, eggs and flour and stir well.
Stir in undrained pineapple. Put toasted bread on top.
Press down, but do not stir.
Bake, uncovered, in preheated oven at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve hot. Makes 8 servings.

title: strawberry cream pie
directions: Beat
cream
cheese and powdered sugar.
Fold in mashed and sliced strawberries.
Then fold in Cool Whip and vanilla. Pour into graham cracker crust and refrigerate.

title: grits casserole
directions: Cook quick grits in 5 cups boiling water with salt.
Brown sausage; drain fat.
Add grated cheese, sausage, 3 beaten eggs, milk and margarine.
Pour into a 3-quart casserole dish; bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: fish and vegetable casserole
directions: Drain vegetables, reserving liquid.
Add enough milk to reserved liquid to measure 1 cup.
Place fish in greased 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with the next 4 ingredients.
Saute green pepper and onion in shortening in skillet until tender.
Blend in flour.
Add liquid gradually, stirring constantly.
Cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Add Worcestershire sauce and vegetables.
Pour over fish; top with crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: potato cakes(old english british treat)
directions: Mix potatoes with flour until a doughy consistency.
Roll out 1/2-inch thick.
Cut into squares.
Bake on aluminum foil, greased and flour at 450° until golden brown on bottom.
Flip and bake until golden brown to your liking.
Crispy or doughy.
Serve hot with butter.

title: rice and mushroom casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients into casserole dish; bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Raw rice only; Minute rice will not work.

title: shrimp pilaf
directions: Stir Worcestershire sauce, flour and shrimp together, coating shrimp well.
Place in refrigerator until needed.
Cook bacon. Saute vegetables in margarine and 2 to 3 tablespoons of bacon drippings.
Cook until tender.
Add shrimp and cook until they turn pink.
Add cooked rice and seasoned salt to taste.
Add crumbled bacon.
Serve with a salad or slaw.

title: oyster cornbread pone
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Pour into a well-greased iron frying pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve while hot.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Cream together cream cheese and sugar.
Add marshmallows, strawberries with juice, pineapple, oranges and bananas.
Mix and fold in Cool Whip.
Freeze in two (2) loaf pans or one (1) 9 x 13 pan.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix well.
Pour into a 13 x 11 x 2-inch pan.

title: rhubarb cherry pie
directions: Combine all ingredients except for pastry.
Let stand for 15 minutes.
Line a 9 inch pie plate with pastry, add filling, arrange top crust.
Bake at 400 degrees for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: bit of honey
directions: Mix well.
Spread in pan and cut into squares or roll into balls.
Refrigerate before serving.

title: sweet sour beans
directions: Blend at high speed until it homogenizes.

title: * sweet and sour meat loaf *
directions: Mix tomato sauce, sugar, vinegar and mustard in a small bowl until blended.
Place the remaining ingredients and 1 cup of the sauce mixture in a large bowl.
Blend thoroughly.
Place meat mixture in a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf.
Pour 1/4 cup of the sauce over the top.
Bake in a 375° oven for 1 hour, basting with the remainder of the sauce.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: antipasta salad
directions: Toss ingredients.
Garnish with anchovies, parsley and cheese and serve.

title: coconut potato candy
directions: Mix potatoes and sugar.
Add butter, coconut, vanilla and salt.
Blend well.
Press into ungreased pan, so that candy is about 1-inch thick.
Melt chocolate and pour over candy.
When firm, cut into 1-inch squares.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add molasses and egg and beat well.
Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Roll in small balls. Dip in sugar and place 2 inches apart on
greased cookie sheet. Cookies will spread as they bake.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan, combine sugars, milk and marshmallows; bring to a boil over medium heat.
Stir until sugar is dissolved and marshmallows melted.
Remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter.
Add nuts.
Put in an 8-inch pan and cool.
Makes 3 dozen pieces.

title: canned apples
directions: Set overnight and bring to a boil.
Put in jars and seal.

title: bran muffins
directions: Mix flour, baking soda, salt and sugar in a large bowl.
Add eggs, oil, buttermilk and cereal.
Mix until cereal is all mixed in.
Bake in greased tins or place paper in muffin tins. Remaining dough can be kept in refrigerator up to 6 weeks in airtight container.
Do not stir batter after it has been mixed initially.
Just spoon out what's needed.

title: oatmeal muffins
directions: Dissolve the soda in hot water; pour over shortening, sugar and eggs, mixed together.
Mix all ingredients together and bake in a moderate oven at 350° until golden brown.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Grease deep 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer bread, meat, cheese, bread, meat and cheese.
Combine eggs, milk, dry mustard and salt. Pour over layers; cover.
Let set for at least 8 hours or overnight.

title: pepsi jello
directions: Heat Pepsi and Jell-O to dissolve; do not boil.
Add can of cherries.
Add can of pineapple.
Heat together, but do not boil. Pour into a 9 x 13-inch dish.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers and onions. Let soak in ice and salt for 3 hours. After 3 hours, drain. Put cucumbers, onions, vinegar, sugar and pickling spices in a kettle and heat for 5 minutes. Put in jars and seal. Makes 14 pints.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown hamburger, spoon off excess fat.
Add next 7 ingredients.
Simmer until thick (about 45 minutes).
Stir occasionally (add water as needed).
Cook noodles, drain and rinse in cold water.
Combine remaining ingredients in separate bowl. Mix well.
In 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan, place noodles, then layer cheese mixture and meat mixture.
Repeat until all ingredients are used.
Top with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes. Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: moist n' creamy coconut cake(luscious)
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed; bake in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan (lightly greased and floured).
Cool 15 minutes.
Poke holes down through cake with utility fork.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind entire orange, including rind.
Dissolve Jell-O and sugar in hot water.
Add all ingredients and mix well. Refrigerate.

title: old-fashioned beef stew
directions: Dredge meat with flour and brown on all sides in shortening in kettle.
Add 2 teaspoons salt, pepper and water.
Bring to boil; simmer, covered, for 1 1/2 hours, or until meat is almost tender. Add remaining ingredients, except peas, and simmer for 45 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Season with salt to taste and sprinkle with peas.
Makes 6 servings.

title: meaty mushroom chili
directions: In a large saucepan, cook the sausage, beef and onion over medium heat until the meat is no longer pink. Drain. Stir in the mushrooms, V-8 juice, tomato paste and seasonings. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat. Cover and simmer for 1 hour. Garnish with sour cream, if desired. Yield: 8 servings.

title: franklin nut cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar. Add beaten eggs and 3 cups of the flour, sifted with baking powder and salt. Mix remaining flour with candied fruits and nuts. Stir into batter. Add vanilla. Pour into large tube pan, greased and lined with wax paper. Bake 1 1/2 hours at 300°. Let cool in pan before removing.

title: granny's sugar cookies
directions: Mix all together and chill 20 minutes.
Roll in balls the size of a walnut.
Roll in sugar; place on cookie sheet and press with a glass dipped in sugar.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: jo's cheese casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until set.

title: waffles
directions: Mix batter.
Make test waffle.
Add more flour if necessary.

title: dutch apple cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add egg and beat well.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour cake mixture into a well-greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Arrange apple slices on top of dough, pressing sharp edge into batter. Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar and dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes.
Serve warm with lemon sauce or vanilla ice cream.

title: nutty tuna sandwiches
directions: In a bowl, combine the tuna, egg, onion, peanuts, dressing and lemon juice.
Line each pita half with a lettuce leaf; stuff with tuna mixture.
Yields 2 to 4 servings.

title: ravioli meat loaf
directions: Thoroughly combine beef, egg, onion, salt, pepper, bread crumbs and milk.
Place 1/3 of meat mixture in greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Spread 1 can of ravioli on the meat.
Sprinkle with half of the cheese.
Repeat layers, ending with meat mixture. Pat down firmly to form a loaf.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Drain off any fat.
Loaf should stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: gumbo
directions: Mix margarine and flour together in a heavy pot.
Cook over low heat, stirring until roux becomes dark brown.
Add onion, okra, garlic and bell pepper; saute until tender.
Add water and seasoning.
Cook 1 hour.
Add meat and tomatoes.
Cook 1 more hour.
Serve in soup plate over boiled rice.

title: stir-fry
directions: *Carrots, onions, green pepper, mushrooms, cauliflower, broccoli and Chinese peas.

title: cranberry sauce
directions: Mix in order given. Chill until firm.

title: green salad
directions: Mix Jell-O as directed.
Add marshmallows and let melt.
Let cool.
Add whipped cream cheese and pineapple that has been mixed with mayonnaise.
Cool to jell in refrigerator.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown meat and chopped onion, discarding any excess fat.
Add all other ingredients (possibly a very small amount of water) and cook very slowly 30 minutes or more.
Serve on spaghetti.

title: southern cornbread
directions: Combine buttermilk, egg, cornmeal, flour, soda, baking powder and salt.
Mix well, then add 3 to 4 tablespoons bacon drippings. Pour into a very hot well-greased iron skillet.
Bake at 450° for 20 to 25 minutes, until brown.

title: french fried veggie batter
directions: Mix until thick.
Dip veggies and deep fry.

title: jello cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as per package, baking in 13 x 9-inch pan at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool 15 minutes, then poke with fork at 1/2-inch intervals.
Dissolve gelatin and pour over cake. Chill 3 to 4 hours.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: fragrance of christmas
directions: Simmer in an open pan (or potpourri pot) during the holidays. Makes a nice Christmas aroma throughout the home.

title: barbecue cups
directions: Roll biscuits until flattened.
Place in muffin tin. Brown ground meat. Add barbecue sauce and brown sugar.
Spoon meat mixture into biscuits.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Cook in a 400° preheated oven for 10 minutes or until biscuits are done and cheese is melted.

title: poor man's steak
directions: Mix all ingredients, except soup, and press in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Chill several hours or overnight.
Cut into squares; roll in flour and brown.
Pour 1 can soup in pan; place browned meat squares on top of soup and pour other can of soup over top.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: quick lunchbox cake
directions: Combine the first seven ingredients and beat for 2 minutes at medium speed.
Pour into greased and floured pan (13 x 9-inch). Sprinkle chocolate chips and nuts on top.
Bake in a 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: banana cream pie
directions: Line a 9-inch pie plate with cookies; slice bananas on cookies.
Mix instant pudding with 1 cup milk until thick.
Add cup of Cool Whip.
Pour over bananas.
Top with remaining Cool Whip.

title: wackys
directions: In kettle, put sugar and cocoa; mix well.
Add oleo and milk; stir continually.
Cook until it forms a soft ball in cold water. Put in peanut butter; continue to stir until melted.
Set off the stove and add oats slowly.
Mix well.

title: coffee punch
directions: Combine coffee, sugar and salt in saucepan.
Add water and mix well.
Place over low heat and stir constantly until well mixed. Remove from heat; chill, then stir in milk.
When ready to serve, pour into punch bowl.
Spoon in ice cream; stir slightly.
Pour in carbonated water.
Makes 24 punch cup servings.

title: hush puppies
directions: Cook corn meal and water, stirring until stiff and begins to roll into ball, about 6 minutes. Remove from heat; add milk, oil and onion.
Stir until smooth.
Gradually stir into beaten eggs in a 2-quart bowl.
Measure flour by dip-level-pour method or by sifting.
Blend dry ingredients. Add to corn meal batter; blend thoroughly.
Heat fat (1-inch deep) to 375°.
Drop batter by teaspoonfuls into hot fat.
Fry 6 to 7 minutes. Drain.
Makes 24 to 30.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs, 1 stick margarine and sugar.
Press evenly in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat together the confectioners sugar, egg whites and other stick of melted margarine.
Spread over cracker crust.
Cut bananas lengthwise and layer on crust. Layer drained pineapple on bananas.
Cover with whipped topping and refrigerate.
May top with sliced cherries or pecan halves.

title: barbecued "baby back" spareribs
directions: Combine catsup, chili sauce, soy sauce, brown sugar, vinegar and water in a saucepan.
Stir well.
Cook over medium heat until it thickens.
This can be made up and refrigerated for several days.
Place ribs in oven at 250°.
I use cookie sheets covered with aluminum foil.
Cook at least 3 hours.
Remove to the grill. Coat with sauce, using a pastry brush, until both sides are browned.
Allow 30 minutes on the grill.
Try to buy your ribs on sale since they are expensive.
Bring them home and freeze them until you are ready to cook them.
This amount will feed 6 to 8 hungry people.

title: cheese barslubbock, texas
directions: Mix together egg yolks, cream cheese, vanilla and 1 c. sugar. Stretch 1 pkg. of crescent rolls to fill bottom of a 9 X 13-inch pan.
Spread cheese mixture over rolls.
Stretch second pkg. rolls over cheese mixture.
Beat egg whites until frothy, then brush on top of rolls.
Combine remaining 1/2 c. sugar, cinnamon and nuts. Sprinkle on top and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cut into squares.

title: steak melt sandwich
directions: Cook meat, onion, pepper and bouillon cube together until tender.
Drain juice from meat into a bowl, then put meat, onion and peppers on bread.
Put cheese on top of meat.
Use the juice from the meat as a sauce to dip sandwich into.
You can put mayonnaise or horseradish sauce on the bread.
Enjoy.

title: superb brandy alexanders
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender.
Blend well.
Yields 1 quart.
Nice sipping dessert.

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: Melt marshmallows.
Add milk, crumbled wafers, fruit and nuts. Pack in dish or box and refrigerate.

title: oil-free muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Mix the milk, egg whites and corn syrup and blend with dry ingredients.
Line muffin pans with paper baking cups and fill with batter.
Bake 13 to 15 minutes; test for doneness with toothpick.

title: blueberry angel food cake rolls(no fat, no cholesterol)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Line two 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch jelly roll pans with aluminum foil.
Prepare cake following package directions; divide into pans.
Spread evenly.
Cut through batter with knife or spatula to remove air bubbles.
Bake for 15 minutes, or until set.
Invert cakes at once onto clean, lint-free dish towels dusted with confectioners sugar.
Remove foil.
Roll up each cake with towel, jelly roll fashion.
Cool completely. Unroll cakes and spread about 1 cup blueberry pie filling to within 1 inch of edges.
Reroll and dust with 1/4 cup confectioners sugar.
Very good.
Makes 2 cakes.

title: green rice casserole
directions: Mix together the soup, margarine, celery, onion and salt.
Add the Cheez Whiz, rice and broccoli.
Bake 1 hour at 350° or until onions are tender.
Buttered bread crumbs or crushed potato chips may be sprinkled over top before baking if desired.

title: crunchy drop cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease cookie sheet.
In small bowl, combine flour, soda and salt; mix well.
In large bowl, beat together sugar and shortening (or margarine) until fluffy; blend in egg, milk and vanilla.
Add flour mixture; mix well.
Stir in cereal.
Drop by teaspoons onto prepared sheet.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: glazed apricot pork kabobs
directions: Cube pork loin in 1-inch cubes.
Mix all ingredients well. Put in heavy plastic bag.
Marinate 30 minutes or more.
Thread pork onto 4 to 6 skewers (if using bamboo skewers, soak in water for 30 minutes to prevent burning).
Grill over hot coals 10 to 12 minutes, turning often.
Baste frequently with marinade.
Serves 4.

title: mexican wedding cake
directions: Mix all ingredients in large mixing bowl.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes in an ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
After cake is cool, ice cake with cream cheese or frosting.

title: strawberry yogurt pie
directions: Combine crushed fruit and yogurt.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Spoon mixture into a graham cracker crust.
Freeze 4 hours, remove and place in refrigerator for about 30 minutes before serving.
Store leftovers in freezer.

title: pork chops and potato scallop
directions: Combine mushroom soup, sour cream, water and dill weed in small bowl; blend well.
Alternate layers of potatoes and soup mixture in a lightly greased 2-quart casserole.
Cover.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Sprinkle pork chops or pork steaks with salt and pepper.
Brown on both sides in small amount of oil in medium skillet.
Drain on paper towels.
Place chops on top of potatoes. Cover and bake an additional 30 minutes.
Garnish with parsley, if desired.
Makes 4 servings.

title: granapple relish(diabetic recipe)
directions: Shred apple in food processor.
Quarter orange and combine with cranberries in processor.
Blend apples, cranberries, coriander and sweetener.
Refrigerate.
Equals 1 fruit exchange.

title: chocolate chip cookies(sugar-free)
directions: Sift together dry ingredients. Cream margarine. Add sugar substitute, vanilla and egg, blending well. Add flour mixture and beat well. Stir in chocolate chips. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto a greased baking sheet. Bake 10 minutes at 375°. Serves 18 (2 cookies per serving).

title: instant mincemeat
directions: Mix all ingredients except oleo in a bowl and fill pie crust. Dot with oleo, then cover with top crust.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour or until done.

title: spicy crinkle cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Beat in egg, molasses and dry milk. Blend in dry ingredients, mixing well.
Roll dough into balls, then in sugar.
Place on well-greased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 minutes at 375°.
Cool.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: angle food cake
directions: Sift flour 3 times. Beat egg whites, slightly and add tartar, vanilla and almond and beat until meringue holds soft peaks. Beat in sugar, 2 Tbsp at a time. Continue to beat, turning bowl until meringue holds. Sift 1/4 of flour over whites. Fold in remaining flour by fourths. Place in an ungreased tube pan.

title: hot cheese balls
directions: Mix cheese, flour and small pinch of pepper.
Add the stiffly beaten egg whites to first mixture.
Fold in lightly.
Dip out by teaspoons.
Roll in small balls.
Roll in beaten egg yolks, then roll in cracker dust.
Fry in deep fat to light brown.

title: hearty meat loaves(individual)
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Combine ground beef and egg in a large bowl and mix well. Add bread crumbs, onion, 1/2 cup ketchup, milk, onion soup mix, 2 tablespoons Worcestershire sauce, salt and black pepper; mix well. Shape into 4 individual loaves and place in a 15 x 10 baking dish.

title: oatmeal raisin cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Beat together margarine and sugars until creamy. Add eggs and vanilla; beat well.
Combine flour, baking soda, cinnamon and salt; mix well and add to sugar mixture. Stir in oats and raisins; mix well.

Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheets. Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown (do not overbake). Cool 1 minute on cookie sheet before removing to wire rack. Makes about 4 dozen.

title: taffy apple salad
directions: The night before serving, mix drained pineapple (save juice) with marshmallows.
Let chill overnight in refrigerator.
In small saucepan, add juice, sugar, flour, egg and vinegar; heat to boil. Cool; let stand overnight in refrigerator, too.

title: grilled veggies
directions: Slice squash, onion and mushrooms.
Chop tomatoes.
Lay out on a large piece of heavy-duty foil.
Cut butter in pieces and scatter over vegetables.
Fold over foil and seal well.
Cook on barbecue grill for 15 to 20 minutes, turning several times.

title: deviled ham cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese in mixer bowl; beat with electric beater. Beat in Cheddar cheese and next 8 ingredients until mixture is creamy.
Stir in parsley and pimiento.
Cover and refrigerate until firm enough to handle.
Shape into a ball and coat evenly with the chopped nuts.
Wrap in moisture/waterproof paper and refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: vegetable bars
directions: Cover bottom of jelly roll pan with crescent rolls.
Pinch seams together.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned, 8 to 10 minutes; let cool.
Beat cream cheese, salad dressing and Hidden Valley Ranch mix until smooth; spread on crust; mix vegetables in bowl and sprinkle on top.
Refrigerate.

title: old italian family recipe spaghetti sauce
directions: Chop and sear onions, peppers and garlic in olive oil.
Brown hamburger and Italian sausage.
Combine with onions, peppers and garlic.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer for 4 hours.
You may add more water as needed.
Will serve approximately 50 people.

title: strawberry fool
directions: Mash strawberries until liquified.
Dissolve sugar in water and add berries.
Boil for 1 minute and leave to cool.
It should be like jelly.
Mix with more strawberries and add whipped cream and stiffly beaten egg white.
Serves approximately 4 to 5.

title: french meat pies
directions: Cover meat and spices with 1 inch water in skillet; simmer until cooked.
Add potatoes and enough bread crumbs to soak up grease.
Put in pie crust.
Cover with top crust; bake until crust is nicely browned.
This will make 2 pies.
Bake in oven at 375°. These freeze well.

title: cherry dump cake
directions: Layer cherry pie filling, pineapple with juice and dry cake mix in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Drizzle with margarine. Sprinkle coconut and pecans over top.
Bake at 325° for about 1 hour.
It may not need quite an hour.

title: lamb and cabbage(far-i-kal)
directions: Cook all ingredients together for about 2 hours.

title: chicken marsala with mushrooms(serves 4)
directions: Mix flour and pepper in a shallow dish.
Dredge chicken in flour mixture to coat.
Shake off excess.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Add flour and eggs. Mix the buttermilk and lemon extract with mixture. Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake for 45 minutes at 350° or until set.

title: beef bourguignonne
directions: Cook salt pork or bacon and onions until onions are golden brown.
Remove the onions and set them aside.
Put into the pan the round steak in 2-inch cubes.
Brown well.
Sprinkle with flour, salt, pepper, marjoram and thyme.
Stir and add red wine and bouillon or water.

title: crostini
directions: Cut bread into 1/2 inch slices.
Coat both sides with cooking spray and place on a baking sheet.
Broil four inches from heat for one minute or until cheese melts.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix unmade pudding with pineapple and juice.
