Add marshmallows and softened cream cheese.
Dissolve gelatin in 1 tablespoon cold water and 2 tablespoons hot water.
Add to mixture.
Fold in Cool Whip and pecans.
Chill for 1 hour.

title: peach delight
directions: Sprinkle peaches with lemon juice.
Cream 3/4 cup sugar with butter.
Sift flour with baking powder and salt.
Add with milk to sugar mixture to form stiff batter.
Spread peaches in buttered 8 x 10 x 12-inch baking dish.
Spread batter over peaches.
Combine cornstarch and remaining sugar; sprinkle over top of batter.
Pour boiling water over all.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.
Serve warm with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: hot pepper jelly
directions: Be careful in your selection. Do not choose while still green. Some wives insist on keeping them in a pickle; others are constantly getting them in hot water.
This makes husbands, sour, hard and sometimes bitter.
Even poor varieties may be made sweet, tender and good by garnishing them with patience, sweetening well with love and seasoning them with kisses.
Spice them up with a dash of play.
Keep warm with a steady diet of devotion and serving the Lord together. Thus prepared they will keep for years.

title: ratatouille-eggplant country style
directions: Saute garlic and onions in oil.
In a casserole, combine all ingredients and simmer 35 to 45 minutes.
Uncover and continue cooking until most of the liquid is absorbed.
Serve warm or cold.

title: hot pepper jelly
directions: Seed and grind peppers fine, using rubber gloves.
Mix peppers, sugar, vinegar and lemon juice in a large pot.
Bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and cool 5 minutes.
Add Certo; mix thoroughly.
Let stand a few minutes; stir again.
Pour into sterilized jars.
Yields about 12 baby food jars.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Cut up dates, nuts and candy in small bowl; mix with 1/2 cup flour (not part of 3 1/2 cups flour in recipe).
Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, 2 at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add buttermilk; mix well.
Add flour and soda; beat well.
Fold in the first 3 ingredients, then coconut.
Bake in greased and floured pan for 3 hours at 250°.

title: bread(4 loaves)
directions: Melt the first 3 ingredients in bowl with hot water.
Add cold water to bring liquid to good warm temperature.
Add 4 cups bread flour; sprinkle dry yeast over it.
Stir with wire whisk.
Add wheat flour; stir with big spoon.
Add more bread flour; knead until dough pulls away from bowl and is no longer sticky.
Grease top; cover with plastic wrapper.
Let rise 1/2 hour.
Punch down; let rise 1 hour.
Shape into loaves.
Put in pans; let rise rounded above top of pan.
Bake in a hot oven for 25 minutes. Adjust oven so they'll be golden brown in that length of time. Put in plastic bags while still slightly warm.

title: heller family lunch
directions: You can make as much or as little as you want.
For a small amount, beat one egg into a small bowl.
Add 1 cup milk;
stir together.
Break crackers into pieces and add to egg and milk mixture until liquid is absorbed by the crackers.
Melt shortening in skillet; spread crackers and egg mixture over the bottom of skillet.
It will look like one large pancake.
Brown one side and then flip and brown the other side.
Can be eaten with butter, syrup or ketchup.

title: dirt cake
directions: You will need 1 medium bowl for mixing, 2 medium bowls for cookies and 1 large bowl.

title: blueberry cheese cake
directions: Mix crushed crumbs, powdered sugar and oleo in 9 x 12 x 2-inch pan for crust.
In mixer, beat eggs, 1/2 cup sugar and cream cheese until blended.
Pour into crust and bake 20 minutes at 325°.
Drain the blueberries.
Cook juice with cornstarch and 1/2 cup sugar until thick.
Mix in blueberries; let cool.
Put in crust on top of cheese mixture.
Cool well.
When ready to serve, spread whipped cream on top and cut into squares.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: chicken monterey
directions: Rub chicken breasts with 3/4 teaspoon salt.
Brown chicken in a 12-inch skillet in oil over medium-high heat.
Arrange chicken in a 3-quart baking dish.
Drain all but 2 tablespoons drippings from skillet.
Add green onion to drippings and saut until tender. Stir in flour.
Gradually stir in milk and water until smooth. Stir in ketchup, rosemary, bouillon and 3/4 teaspoon salt.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens slightly.
Pour over chicken.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Stir in artichoke hearts and green beans.
Bake 20 more minutes or until chicken is tender.

title: apple pie
directions: Toss first 4 ingredients together and then fold in sliced, peeled apples.
Place in a pie shell and dot with 6 small dots of butter.
Put on top crust.
Place slits in top and sprinkle top with cinnamon sugar. Bake at 450° for 5 minutes, then at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: excellent and easy blueberry muffins
directions: Cream butter, sugar and eggs.
Mix flour, baking powder and salt together.
Add flour mixture and milk to creamed mixture. Beat well at medium speed.
Fold in blueberries.
Pile high in muffin tins.
Sprinkle sugar over top and bake in preheated oven at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool about 20 minutes before removing from pan.
Makes 1 dozen.

title: johnny's squash dressing
directions: Melt margarine in skillet.
Add onion and garlic.
Cook until tender.
Add sage, red pepper, cayenne pepper, black pepper and salt.
Set to one side.

title: quick cherry cobbler
directions: Drain juice from cherries; add sugar, red hots and cornstarch. Cook until candy has melted and mixture is thick and clear.
Add cherries.
Remove from heat.
Pour into 8 x 8-inch casserole dish. Put cinnamon rolls on top of cherry mixture.
Bake 20 minutes at 375°.
Put icing on top when done.

title: blueberry sauce
directions: Bring to a boil in a heavy saucepan. Allow to cook until thick, stirring occasionally. Serve over pancakes, ice cream, etc.

title: hot german potato salad
directions: In a large bowl, thaw and crumble hash brown patties.
Prepare bacon in large skillet over medium heat.
Remove bacon from skillet; reserve drippings in same skillet.
Using a wire whisk, stir flour into bacon drippings until smooth.
Add sugar, vinegar, water, salt, pepper and celery seed.
Stir mixture until well blended.
Continue heating over medium heat until mixture boils and thickens.
Add onions and crumbled bacon to mixture.
Pour mixture over crumbled hash brown patties.
Stir to blend all ingredients.
Make ahead and refrigerate to allow flavors to blend.
Makes 8 servings.

title: quick beef stroganoff
directions: Cut meat into 1/4 x 2-inch strips.
Mix flour with the salt. Toss meat with mixture.
Heat butter in heavy frying pan. Add garlic and onion. Saute until garlic is lightly browned.
Spoon out and reserve. Add meat to same pan, a few pieces at a time. Brown quickly and keep pieces as separate as possible to prevent stewing the meat.
When all meat is browned, return onion and garlic to pan. Sprinkle with paprika and pepper.
Blend well. Fold in sour cream.
Heat slowly; do not boil. Serve over hot buttered noodles.
Garnish with parsley and buttered sauteed mushroom caps.

title: italian biscotti
directions: Melt butter and cool. Beat together all ingredients. Grease 2 cookie sheets. Spoon batter, making a loaf- 2 loaves each sheet. Bake at 375° for 15 minutes. Remove from oven and slice loaves on the diagonal. Lay slices on side and put back to brown to a golden color. Turn cookies over and repeat - just check them as ovens vary.

title: fruited chicken
directions: Spray large baking pan with Pam or grease pan.
Place chicken in pan skin side up or skinless.
Combine all ingredients and pour over chicken.
Cover pan with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, basting several times. Uncover and cook for 10 minutes to brown. Serve over white rice.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Add 2 or 3 teaspoons to a cup of hot water for a nice drink on a cold day.

title: ground beef and rice casserole
directions: Blend together cooked beef, dry onion soup mix and cream of mushroom soup.
Add water, rice and chopped onion.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake covered for 1 hour.
Remove cover, sprinkle cheese on top.
Broil a few minutes until cheese melts.

title: spoon rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Combine yeast mixture, margarine and flour in large bowl; mix well.
Stir in egg and sugar.
(Mixture will be a very soft batter.)
Cover and refrigerate batter overnight.

title: chicken on pasta
directions: Remove skin from boned chicken and cut into julienne strips. Set aside.
Melt butter in a large saute pan.
Add garlic and green onion and saute until tender.
Add chicken and mushrooms and cook until chicken loses its pinkness.

title: 5 layer dessert
directions: Layer 1:
Combine flour, butter and 1 cup pecans.
Put into pan for crust.
Bake for 10 to 15 minutes at 350°.

title: ribbon sandwiches(appetizers)
directions: Stack 5 slices of bread alternately (1 wheat, 1 white and so on), filling with one or more spreads.
Trim off crust.
Wrap stack in plastic wrap; chill at least 2 hours.
Cut stack into 6 (1/2-inch) slices; cut each slice into halves for a total of 12 sandwiches.
Place on tray and serve.
About 1 1/2 cups filling will spread 5 dozen sandwiches.

title: baked chicken and rice casserole
directions: Butter bottom of baking dish.
Place in chicken breasts.
Mix soup and milk.
Heat slightly.
Add rice and mix well.
Pour over chicken.
Bake at 350°, covered, for 1 hour; uncovered for 15 minutes.

title: wigglers
directions: Brown hamburg and onion.
Cook vegetables before mixing.
Hot dogs (raw) can be added, too.
Add salt, pepper and seasoned salt to taste.
Mix all ingredients; pour into casserole.
Bake 1 hour at 300° to 325°.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Combine soup and enchilada sauce.
Dip tortillas in hot oil to soften, a few seconds on each side.
Top each tortilla with 1 heaping tablespoonful of chicken, 1 spoon of cheese and 1 spoon of soup mixture; roll up.
Place seam side down in large baking dish. Pour remaining sauce over and top with remaining sauce.
Bake at 350° (preheated oven) for 25 to 30 minutes.
For added spice, cook chicken, using spicy taco mix and water before adding to tortillas.

title: chicken-broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions.
Arrange in bottom of greased, shallow casserole (9 x 13-inch).
Layer chicken on top of broccoli.

title: seven-layer bars
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle the graham cracker crumbs evenly over bottom of pan.
Add a layer of each of the remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Remove from oven; cut into squares.
Cover loosely.
When completely cool, cut again and remove from pan.
Keep covered.

title: chicken parisian
directions: Combine flour, paprika and pepper in a plastic bag.
Add chicken and shake to coat.
In a skillet, brown chicken in margarine.
Remove from pan.
In the same skillet add remaining ingredients and simmer 3 minutes.
Return chicken to pan and simmer 20 minutes covered until tender.

title: moist pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening and add eggs one at a time.
Mix flour, baking powder and salt together.
Add flour mixture alternately with milk.
Add flavorings.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: hamburger-corn pie
directions: Cook and stir hamburger, pork sausage, onion and garlic until meat is brown; drain.
Stir in tomatoes (with liquid), corn, olives, chili powder and salt.
Heat to boiling.
Pour into ungreased baking dish, 9 x 9 x 2-inch or 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch, or a 2-quart casserole dish.

title: hot hamburger casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion; drain.
Mix Ro-Tel with soup. Crush tortillas slightly.
Layer all ingredients in a 2-quart casserole dish. Begin and end with chips.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 20 minutes, or until bubbly.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix rice, soup, Cheez Whiz and Worcestershire sauce, then add broccoli and chicken.
Keep about 2 tablespoons soup to spread over top.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: hank thalgott's cake
directions: Mix salt and baking powder with flour.
Mix sugar, butter, milk and vanilla together.
Add milk and flour alternately in several steps.
Bake in preheated oven at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Mix melted shortening, molasses and sugar until smooth.
Add buttermilk and sifted flour, salt, ginger and soda.
Add extract. Mix to a smooth, stiff dough and chill until firm.
Roll out on lightly floured surface.
Place on greased baking sheet and bake 10 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: Mix in a quart microwave dish the oleo, sugar, salt and Karo. Cook on full power until it bubbles, then cook for 2 minutes (a total of 4 minutes).
Add the baking soda.
Stir well until mixed and frothy.
Pour over corn in the bag and shake vigorously.

title: chicken breasts in mushroom sauce
directions: Sprinkle chicken with pepper; saute in butter until breasts are cooked through and nicely browned, turning frequently.
Remove to a serving dish.
Add shallots to pan and cook briefly.
Add mushrooms and cook for 2 minutes, stirring frequently.
Add cognac and cream; cook down over high heat for 5 minutes.
Add any drippings from chicken in serving dish.
Stir and pour over chicken.
Delicious!!

title: persimmon bread
directions: Cream
together
shortening,
sugar and egg; set aside. Sift together flour, baking powder, soda, cinnamon, ginger and salt. Gradually
blend
dry
ingredients into shortening mixture.
Add persimmon
pulp,
vanilla and nuts; mix to a stiff dough.
Pour into
greased
x 5-inch loaf pan and set aside for 20 minutes. Heat
oven	to
375° and cook 50 minutes to 1 hour or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: sweet and sour pork kabobs
directions: Boil carrots for 8 minutes.
Drain pineapple; reserve juice. Cut pineapple into quarters.

title: potato cheese soup
directions: Mix potatoes, onion, celery, carrots, parsley, boullion cubes, water, salt, and pepper into a large pot.
Bring to a boil, then cover and let cook on med. to low heat until tender (about 8 minutes).
Mix flour and 1/2 c. milk until well blended.
Add to pot of vegetables and mix well.
Add 3 c. milk and Velveeta cheese.
Stir until cheese is melted and serve hot.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Drain fruits, add water if needed to make 2 cups juice.
Bring to a boil.
Dissolve jello with juice.
Add fruit.
Let congeal in a 9 x 12-inch dish.

title: lemon butter
directions: Mix together and bring to boil until thickened like pudding.

title: frozen fruit slush
directions: Mix pink lemonade, orange juice, pineapple, strawberries, cherries, water, sugar and bananas together in a large container. Freeze.
Can be frozen in smaller containers for family use.
Take our of freezer 1 hour before serving.
Break up with a spoon and serve in small glass bowls.
Makes about 20 to 24 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: scrambled cabbage
directions: Mix vegetables, salt and pepper.
Heat oil in skillet or kettle.
Add vegetables.
Cover and cook for 8 or 9 minutes.
Do not overcook.
Should be crisp.

title: delicious dessert
directions: Mix together for crust.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Put in freezer for 1 hour.
Remove from freezer and put 1/2 gallon ice cream on top.
Freeze.

title: dijonnaise pork chops
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Spread mustard on pork chops. Press pork chops into bread crumb mixture.
Broil on rack 5 to 6 minutes.

title: calorie counter's moussaka
directions: In skillet, cook beef and onion until meat is browned; drain off fat.
Stir in vegetables, mushrooms, herbs and seasonings. Cook, uncovered, for 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Turn into rectangular baking dish.
Use electric mixer or blender to blend together eggs, cheese, yogurt and 1/4 teaspoon salt until smooth. Pour over meat.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: sausage potato cheese soup(this feeds 4 hungry males or 10 people)
directions: Peel and cube potatoes and chop onion.
In a large soup kettle, place 1 cube butter on medium heat and melt.
Add potatoes and onion.
Saute 3 to 5 minutes.
Fill pot 1/2 full with water and boil.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Sift flour.
Add sugar, soda, baking powder, salt and spices into large bowl.
Beat eggs, oil and pumpkin.
Add to sifted dry ingredients, stirring until just moistened.
Fold in nuts.
Turn into greased 8 x 4-inch or 9 x 5-inch pans.
Bake at 375°.
Serves 4.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Bake cake according to package directions.
Combine 1/2 cup of strawberry glaze with water.
Blend well.
Set aside.
Spread remaining glaze over top of cooled cake.
Alternate diagonal rows of Cool Whip.
Put whole strawberry on top of glazed cake. Carefully spoon glaze and water mixture over tops of strawberries. Chill until ready to serve.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: While cooking the broccoli, saute the celery, green peppers, onions and garlic until soft in a stick of margarine.
Cook rice as usual; add mushroom soup and Cheez Whiz.
Mix well.
Combine everything; mix thoroughly and place in a casserole dish.
Bake, covered, for 20 minutes at 350°.
Bake an additional 10 minutes, uncovered.
Serves 10 to 12 people.
Nice dish for Thanksgiving or Christmas dinner.

title: layered buffet salad
directions: In a large salad bowl, layer lettuce, celery, green beans, eggs, green pepper, onion rings and peas in order given.
Spread mayonnaise over the top. Sprinkle with cheese. Cover well and let stand overnight.

title: cheesy potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except cheese. Place in flat casserole dish. Top with cheese. Bake 1 hour at 350°. Makes 6 servings.

title: white chocolate nut cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Cream shortening and milk at medium speed. Add sugars.
Gradually beat in egg and vanilla.
Combine flour, baking soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture.
Mix well.
Stir in white chocolate and nuts.
Drop by level tablespoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes.
Makes 5 dozen 2-inch cookies.

title: watermelon cake
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar gradually and beat thoroughly.
Sift flour; measure and add salt and baking powder.
Sift again.
Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with milk and flavoring.
Beat thoroughly after each addition.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Grease and flour 2 (9-inch) cake pans.
Take a spoon and put a white ring of batter along outside edge of cake pans.
To the remaining batter, add chocolate chips and red food coloring. Stir with spoon
to mix.
Pour red mixture into middle of cake pan.
Spread with spoon to touch white ring.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool.
Frost with favorite white icing with green food coloring added.

title: dr. bird cake
directions: Stir all ingredients together in a large bowl.
Pour into greased tube or Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or less.
Set aside to cool completely in pan on rack.
Needs no icing.

title: fish casserole (baked)(armenian)
directions: Saute in oil until soft the onion, carrots, pepper, zucchini and celery stalk.
Add tomato sauce and mushrooms.
Season with salt and pepper and oregano and garlic salt.
Simmer 1 hour. Oil large baking dish.
Arrange in the dish 2 pounds of cod, halibut. Pour the mixture over them.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Boil chicken breasts and debone.
Mix together soups and Veg-All vegetables.
Put deboned chicken in with soup and vegetable mixture.
Pour into 1 pie crust.
Dot with butter, salt and pepper.
Place second pie crust on top.
Prick crust with fork all over.
Bake at 350° for approximately 30 to 45 minutes until pie crust is lightly brown.

title: tropical pineapple coconut bars
directions: Heat oven to 350. Lightly grease 13 x 9 inch pan. In a large bowl, combine all base ingredients at low speed until crumbly. Reserve 1 1/2 cups of the crumb mixture. Press remaining crumb mixture in bottom of greased pan.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix together coconut and pecans and spread over bottom of pan.
Mix cake mix as directed on box.
Pour over nuts and coconut.
Mix together margarine, powdered sugar and cream cheese, beating until smooth.
Drop by tablespoons on top of batter, but not too close to edge.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 325° (maybe longer).
Ice with Chocolate Frosting.

title: almond butter balls
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Add flavorings.
Stir in flour and almonds.
Form into tiny balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 20 minutes.
Roll in confectioners sugar while hot.
Makes about 6 dozen cookies and they'll melt in your mouth.
This is a Swedish recipe.

title: marinated chicken wings
directions: Marinate chicken wings for 2 hours or overnight.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: green tomato pickle
directions: Two tablespoons of mixed pickle spices may be substituted for listed spices.

title: tamale pie
directions: Saut onion, garlic and olives in 1 tablespoon water in frypan for 2 to 3 minutes.
Place corn and tomato sauce in pan and stir well.
Cook over low heat 5 minutes.
Add all seasonings.
Stir in the corn meal and cook over low heat for 10 minutes.
Place in covered casserole dish.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Don't allow it to get too dry.

title: grannie's bread pudding
directions: Tear bread into pieces.
Mix together all ingredients.
Pour over bread.
Let stand 5 to 10 minutes. Sprinkle with cinnamon or nutmeg.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: wilted lettuce
directions: Mix lettuce and onions together.
Crumble bacon up and put in lettuce mixture.
Heat bacon grease up; it needs to be very hot. Pour bacon grease over lettuce.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour vinegar over lettuce mix.
You can also slice radishes and put in this.

title: favorite chicken casserole
directions: Spread the chicken in a 9 x 12-inch casserole dish.
Mix together the soups and sour cream and spread on top of the chicken.
Crush the crackers and spread on top of the soup mix. Cut margarine in small pieces and place on crackers.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: scripture cake
directions: Cream the first 3 ingredients.
Beat 6 Jeremiah 17:11 until frothy and add sifted dry ingredients.
Add to creamed mixture the remaining ingredients.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes for good reading (and eating).

title: bell pepper tofu
directions: Cut tofu lengthwise in half, then cut across, thinly. Marinate in lemon, soy sauce and chili sauce for 10 to 15 minutes. Fry in olive oil.

title: pumpkin cream pie(no bake)
directions: Combine milk, pudding mix, pumpkin, spice and whipped topping in deep, narrow bottom bowl.
Beat at lowest speed of electric mixer for 1 minute.
Pour into pie shell; chill until set, at least 3 hours.
Serve with whipped topping.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Put rice and boiling water in dish with Lipton onion soup. Stir. Brown in skillet and place pork chops on top.
Pour mushroom soup on top.
In 30 minutes, stir and cook about 1
hour at 350°.

title: **grand slam carrot bread or cake
directions: Combine ingredients; mix well.
Bake in loaf pan at 350° for 45 minutes or make 2 small loaves if desired.

title: jalapeno corn bread
directions: Preheat oven 10 minutes at 400°.
Mix all ingredients except cheese.
Pour 1/2 batter in heavy skillet and top with 1/2 cheese. Pour remaining batter and top with cheese. Bake at 400° for 40 minutes.

title: holiday cranberry slush
directions: Place jelled cranberry sauce in large mixer bowl; beat until smooth.
Add cranberry apple drink concentrate, partially thawed lemonade concentrate and spices.
Mix on low speed until well blended and smooth.
Pour mixture into a large, freezer-safe, non-metallic container.
Add water to mixture and stir well. Cover and freeze for 2 hours.
Remove from freezer and stir. Cover and continue freezing for 8 hours or overnight.

title: cafe vienna (coffee)
directions: Stir ingredients together.
If possible, put in blender until powdered, to reduce bulk.
Place 2 rounded teaspoonfuls in cup for each 8 ounces of boiling water.
Yield: 1 cup dry mixture.
Enough to make 20 cups at 35 calories each.

title: ranch style croutons
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Arrange bread cubes in single layer on baking sheet.
Bake until dry, stirring occasionally, about 15 minutes.
Meanwhile, mix butter with remaining ingredients.
Pour over bread and toss until well coated.
Bake until light brown, stirring occasionally, about 10 minutes.
Store in airtight container.

title: posole(hominy stew)
directions: Place posole and 10 cups of water in large stewing pot. Bring mixture to a boil at high heat. Reduce the heat to low and simmer for 5 hours. Approximately 1 hour before the completion of the posole is finished simmering, brown the pork or beef in a large skillet on medium heat. Turkey may be precooked and added when stew is about done. Add the pork or beef to the stewing pot with 5 cups of water and continue to cook on low heat until tender. Add remaining ingredients to posole and simmer for additional 1 to 2 hours. Adjust seasonings to suit your taste. Serve with flour or corn tortillas. This will freeze well. Yields 8 to 12 servings.

title: chicken pie
directions: Put chicken in bottom of buttered casserole dish.
Add sliced eggs.
Pour peas and corn over eggs.
Mix soups and broth and pour over chicken and vegetables.

title: dump cakeeasy & delicious
directions: 1. Heat oven to 325°. Grease and flour a 9 x 13 x 2 pan.
2. In a large bowl mix salad oil, sugar, eggs, and vanilla
then add apples and walnuts.
3. Mix in flour, baking soda, salt, and cinnamon. Fold
into pan and bake for 75 minutes.

title: cajun cornbread
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: broccoli bread
directions: Place package of broccoli in microwave for 8 minutes on High. Pour over melted oleo and stir. Add other ingredients. Mix well. Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid by directions on package, then add to juices and water.
Sweeten to taste.
Add ginger ale and lime sherbet before serving.

title: deluxe baked chicken
directions: Heat oil in large skillet.
Measure flour, salt, paprika and pepper into paper or plastic bag. Shake chicken, one piece at a time, in bag or until thoroughly coated. Brown chicken in oil over medium heat.
Heat oven to 350°. Place chicken, skin side up, in ungreased 9 x 12-inch baking pan.
Mix broth and garlic powder. Pour broth mixture on chicken.
Cover with aluminum foil and bake until tender, 50 minutes or so, basting occasionally with remaining broth.
Uncover the last 5 minutes to crisp chicken. Makes 6 servings.

title: strawberry fig jam
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bring to boil; cover.
Cook on medium-high for 5 to 10 minutes, stirring constantly.
Spoon into jars and seal.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix together and let set overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Serves 10 or 12.

title: mackerel patties
directions: Mix together.
Form into patties and fry in lightly oiled skillet.

title: glaze for popcorn balls
directions: Cook until soft ball stage, stirring.
Pour over popcorn. Form into balls.

title: mushroom spaghetti sauce
directions: Saute mushrooms in butter until tender.
Dissolve chicken broth in water and add to mushrooms; thicken sauce with flour. Simmer 1/2 hour, more or less.
Immediately before serving, stir in sour cream and barely heat through.
Serve over cooked spaghetti and sprinkle with cheese.
Serves 4.
Enjoy!

title: banana milkshake
directions: Fill a 6-cup ring mold 2/3 full with water; freeze.
Alternate Florida orange wedges (peel side down) with red and green maraschino cherries (3 in each group) on top of ice.
Add thin layer of water; freeze 30 minutes or until oranges and cherries are firmly in place.
Slowly add water to top; freeze.
To unmold run warm water on sides of mold.

title: carrot cake(cracker barrel recipe)
directions: Mix flour and cinnamon.
Beat oil, sugar, eggs, add to flour and cinnamon beat smooth.
Add pineapple, carrots, coconut, and nuts.
Grease pan with margarine.
Bake at 350 degrees for 50 minutes.
Top with cream cheese frosting.

title: cream cheese burritos("mexican pinwheels")
directions: Mix and spread on flour tortillas.
Roll and cut into pinwheels.
Serve with salsa.
Fills one tray.

title: fruit dip
directions: In medium bowl, mix cream cheese and marshmallow cream with mixer until well blended.
Put in refrigerator until cool.
Dip with any type of fruit you like.

title: stuffed grape leaves
directions: Brown beef in skillet with onion.
Stir in 1/4 cup of the Greek dressing, rice, parsley and salt.
With shiny surface of leaf down, place 1 tablespoon of the meat mixture in center of each leaf.
Fold edges of leaf toward center and roll up.
Place in large skillet.
Pour remaining 3/4 cup dressing over stuffed leaves and simmer over low heat until liquid is absorbed, about 5 minutes.
Cover and chill.
Makes 20 servings.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Bottom Layer:
Mix butter and nuts.
Press into bottom of 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake 10 to 20 minutes.
Let cool.

title: fruit drop cookies
directions: Sprinkle sugar over cut fruit.
Add rest of ingredients.
Drop on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until firm and slightly brown, about 15 minutes.

title: one egg spice cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put into a greased 8 by 8 in. pan.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: english pea salad
directions: Toss lightly and serve on lettuce leaves.

title: potato pie
directions: Cook potatoes.
Cool, peel and mash with a potato masher.
In large bowl, combine eggs, salt, pepper, parsley and ham.
Add mashed potatoes and mix thoroughly.
Spread 1/2 of mixture in a greased baking dish.
Cover with cheese.
Layer remaining potato mixture on cheese.
Dot with pats of butter; brush with milk. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour or until lightly browned on top.

title: homemade spiced mocha mix
directions: In large bowl, combine all ingredients.
Store in airtight container.
For single serving, place 3 tablespoons mix in cup. Add 3/4 cup boiling water and stir until mix is dissolved.
Top with marshmallows, if desired.

title: hawaiian style chicken
directions: Melt butter in shallow roasting pan.
Roll chicken in butter and arrange pieces, skin side up, in a single layer in pan. Reserve 2 slices of pineapple for garnish.
Dice remaining slices. Mix pineapple and juice with remaining ingredients.
Cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Spoon sauce over chicken.

title: cheesy chicken casserole
directions: Simmer chicken until tender; pull from bones and discard skin and bones.
Cook the rice and set aside.
Stir together soup, mayonnaise, milk and cheese.
Butter a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish. Cover bottom of dish with cooked rice.
Top with chicken and add 1/2 of soup mixture.
Add broccoli and mushrooms and cover with rest of the soup mixture.
Melt butter and mix with bread crumbs. Cover casserole with the bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 or 40 minutes.

title: chocolate pudding cake
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients thoroughly, then add remaining ingredients.
Pour into ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Before baking, prepare topping and pour carefully over batter.

title: nacho cheese dip
directions: Melt cheese either in microwave or on stove.
Add tomatoes and peppers.
Brown sausage in skillet.
Drain grease.
Add sausage to cheese mixture.
Let warm in crock-pot for approximately 15 minutes.
Serve with chips.

title: fried chicken
directions: In a nonstick skillet sprayed with Pam, place chicken breasts and cover with fruit cocktail, Italian dressing and steak sauce. Cover and cook on medium heat until chicken is done (approximately 35 minutes). Cook, uncovered, until browned.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Prepare pastry for 10-inch pie pan.
Mix butter, eggs, brown sugar, salt and vanilla in a bowl.
Beat with wire whip until smooth. Blend in corn syrup and pecans. Pour into unbaked pie shell with rounded side of pecans upright.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes in preheated oven at 375° until set and pastry is brown.

title: hot cinnamon twisters
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Grease cookie sheet.
In small bowl, combine sugar and cinnamon. In a small saucepan, melt butter over low heat.
With hands, flatten each biscuit to a 4-inch circle. Dip in butter, then cinnamon-sugar mixture.
Twist 2 or 3 times. Place on cookie sheet.
Bake 12-15 minutes.

title: country apple dessert
directions: Combine cake mix, butter and 1 egg.
Stir until crumbly.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread pie filling.
Combine sugar, nuts and cinnamon and sprinkle over cake.

title: stir-fry
directions: In frying pan, stir-fry meat in oil over medium heat.
Add soy sauce to taste, then add vegetables.
Fry until tender, but not soggy.
Add 1/4 teaspoon ginger or allspice.
Continue frying, adding noodles and rice.
Add a little more soy sauce and cook five more minutes.

title: mushroom risotto
directions: In a heavy saucepan, saute onion and mushrooms in oil until soft and golden brown.
Add rice.
Saute for a few minutes until coated.
Add broth.
Bring to a boil.
Cover.
Cook over medium-low heat for about 40 minutes or until rice is cooked. Follow directions on package.
Cooking time varies.

title: barbecue chicken (fried)
directions: Beat egg; mix egg
and milk together.
Dip chicken into mixture.
Salt and pepper
to taste.
Fry in oil until chicken is done.
Simmer 1 cup
barbecue
sauce
and
can
Pepsi in saucepan.
Add chicken and simmer about 5 to 8 minutes.
Serve while hot!

title: diana's holiday punch
directions: Bring sugar and water to a boil until sugar is dissolved. Remove from heat and add juice from lemon, pineapple and cranberry juices and almond extract.
Freeze.
Just before serving, put frozen punch in bowl and add ginger ale.
Garnish with apple slices.
Makes about 70 (4 ounce) servings.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients together.
Mix the peanut butter, vanilla and butter together.
Mix all ingredients together by hand over low heat.
Spoon onto wax paper.

title: chicken wraps
directions: Cook rice according to box directions; set aside. Deep-fry breaded chicken strips and set aside. Layer onions, peppers, tomatoes, lettuce, rice and cheese on shells. Drizzle with Ranch dressing and roll up.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: Mix cottage cheese and dry jello together; mix well.
Add pineapple and orange slices.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Mix well and chill.

title: zesty shrimp dip
directions: In a small bowl, combine ingredients, mix well. Chill. Serve with chips or crackers. Refrigerate any left leftovers.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: In baking dish, place layers of chicken and broccoli.
Cook half and half, cheese, cream cheese, garlic salt and pepper over low heat until thick.
Pour over chicken and broccoli.
Cover. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: lemon squares
directions: Combine 1 cup flour, butter and 1/4 cup powdered sugar.
Cut with a pastry cutter until mixture resembles course meal.
Press mixture evenly into a 9-inch square baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Combine eggs, 1 cup sugar, lemon rind, and juice in bowl and beat well.
Combine 2 tablespoons flour and baking powder and add to egg mixture, beating well.
Pour mixture over baked crust.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until lightly brown and set.
Sprinkle lightly with 2 tablespoons powdered sugar.
Let cool and cut into 1 1/2 inch squares.

title: hanna's brownies
directions: Preheat oven at 350°.
Put all ingredients together.
Stir. Spread in greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake for 30 minutes. Do not overbake.

title: best chocolate cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour rectangular baking pan 13 x 9 x 2-inch or two 9-inch round layer pans.
Beat all ingredients except frosting in large mixer bowl on low speed, scraping bowl constantly, 30 seconds.
Beat on high speed, scraping occasionally, 3 minutes.
Pour into pan(s).
Bake until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean, rectangular 40 to 45 minutes, layers 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool; frost with Fudge Frosting.
Makes 14 servings; 420 calories per serving.

title: pepper jelly with mayhaw juice
directions: Wash pepper and cut in half. You may remove seeds, if desired. Put peppers in blender with some vinegar to help liquify. Heat peppers, mayhaw juice, vinegar, and Sure Jell; add sugar and cook until it jells. Pour into 1/2 pint jars and seal while hot.

title: prune cake
directions: Beat eggs.
Add milk, sugar and oil.
Add dry ingredients. Grease a 9 x 13 x 3-inch pan.
Pour in mixture and bake at 300° for 40 minutes.
Frost.

title: ima's chicken
directions: Cook 45 minutes to 1 hour in covered dish.

title: breakfast ham and cheese
directions: Melt stick of oleo and pour over bread, ham and cheese in pan. Beat eggs and add milk, salt and pepper.
Pour this over rest of mixture.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Before baking, sprinkle with corn flake crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: cherry rice dessert
directions: Drain pineapple thoroughly, reserve juice.
Add enough water to juice to make 1 1/2 c liquid, heat to boiling.
Add gelatin and salt, stir until dissolved.
Add rice, chill over ice water until partly thickened.
Fold in whipped cream, nuts and flavorings. Turn into 8 individual molds or one large mold and chill until firm.
Makes 8 servings.

title: nutty pops
directions: Melt butter in large saucepan.
Add Worcestershire sauce, catsup and Tabasco sauce and mix well.
Stir in nuts.
Spread in glass baking dish and toast for 20 minutes at 400°.
Stir two or three times during baking.
Turn out on paper towels and sprinkle with salt.
Good warm or cold.
Yields 4 cups.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Brown chicken.
Mix in sauce, onions, garlic and steamed veggies.
Heat until sauce is not too thick and simmer 10 to 15 minutes. Serve over rice.

title: spinach balls
directions: Mix all together.
Freeze on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: quick bubble nut bread
directions: Sprinkle nuts evenly in bottom of a well-greased Bundt pan. Set aside.
Combine sugar and cinnamon in a bowl.
Cut biscuits into quarters.
Roll each piece in sugar and cinnamon mixture and layer in Bundt pan.
Melt oleo and brown sugar.
Pour over dough. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Cook beef
in skillet until it loses redness. Drain off fat. Melt
stick
of
butter
in
baking
dish. Add potatoes, carrots, onions
and
mushrooms (layering ingredients).
Pour beef on
top layered
vegetables,
then add mushroom soup and tomato soup. Cook for 1 1/2 hours at 325°.
Take out and cover with grated cheese.

title: copper pennies
directions: Cook carrots until just tender. Layer carrots, peppers and onions in bowl, ending with onion and pepper rings.
Mix soup and other sauce ingredients together.
Pour over carrot mixture and refrigerate overnight.

title: humdingers
directions: Combine oleo, sugar and dates and melt over low heat.
Stir constantly for 6 to 7 minutes.
Add nuts, Rice Krispies and vanilla.
When mixture is cool, form small balls and roll in powdered sugar.
Serves: not many, they're so good!

title: lazy dazey cobbler
directions: Melt 1/4 pound butter in a 9-inch square pan.
Mix together 1/2 cup flour, 1/2 cup sugar, baking powder, salt and milk; pour into dish of melted butter.
Mix fruit and remaining ingredients; pour on top of batter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or more.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Put all ingredients in a crock-pot and cook on low for 3 to 4 hours.

title: spinach au gratin
directions: Wash spinach thoroughly, then place moist spinach in a saucepan without adding additional water.
Cover and cook 7 minutes, or until tender; drain well.
Mix 2 tablespoons butter and the flour; add spinach.
Season well with salt and cayenne. Add the other tablespoons melted butter, chopped eggs and 1 cup grated cheese; mix well.
Put in buttered casserole; cover with 1/2 cup grated cheese.
Brown for 25 minutes at 350°.
Serves 6.

title: layered lettuce salad
directions: Fill 9 x 13-inch glass casserole with lettuce, onion and peas. Cover with mayonnaise, then grated Mozzarella.
Top with bacon bits.

title: susan's rolled ginger cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Beat in egg, molasses and vinegar.
Sift dry ingredients; blend into creamed mixture.
Chill 3 hours.
Roll dough 1/8-inch thick on a lightly floured surface. Cut in shapes.
Place 1-inch apart on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 370° for 5 to 6 minutes.
Cool slightly; remove to rack.
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: corn and barley salad
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients in a bowl.
Combine the vinegar and the next 5 ingredients; stir well.
Pour over barley mixture and toss well.
Serve at room temperature or chilled on lettuce-lined salad plates.
Serves four.

title: pumpkin chiffon pie
directions: To the slightly beaten egg yolks, add 1/2 cup sugar, pumpkin, milk, orange juice and rind, salt and spices.
Cook in double boiler until thickened.
Soften gelatin in cold water and add to hot pumpkin mixture. Mix thoroughly and cool.
When it starts to thicken, fold in stiffly beaten egg whites to which the remaining 1/2 cup sugar has been added.
Pour into baked pie crust and chill.

title: almond cream
directions: Place all ingredients in a large bowl and mix on low speed for 1 minute.
Increase until soft peaks form.
Delicious over fruit.

title: shammy creek shrimp casserole
directions: Saute vegetables; add cooked rice, cooked shrimp, soup and grated cheese.
Stir well.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes. Serve with salad and for dessert, Lemon Squares.

title: raspberry cream pie
directions: Stir dessert into 1 1/2 cups of liquid (raspberry juice + water). Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Boil 1 minute. Cool to room temperature.
Add raspberries. (May add more fresh, if you like.) Fold in 1 cup of whipped cream. Fill baked pie shell. Chill. Serve with remaining cup of whipped cream.

title: pepperoni rigatoni
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Layer half the rigatoni noodles, pepperoni, cheese, onion, green pepper, basil, garlic, spaghetti sauce and Mozzarella cheese in that order.
Put in greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Repeat layers. Bake, uncovered, 25 to 30 minutes or until lightly browned.
Serves 6.

title: bege's ham barbecue
directions: Mix sauce ingredients together in a saucepan.
Simmer on top of the stove for about 20 to 30 minutes.
Mix in ham and continue to simmer until ham is warm.
Makes about
1 pint of sauce and serves 4 to 8.

title: fresh fruit bowl
directions: Scoop out small watermelon; cut in small pieces.
Cut up the remaining fruits and put in watermelon shell.
Serve chilled.

title: crock-pot country steak
directions: Flour cubed steak and brown it in skillet. Put into crock-pot and cover with beefy mushroom soup.
For more gravy, add an extra can.
Cook on low for 4 to 6 hours.

title: lucyle's candy
directions: Melt chocolate in electric skillet on low heat; stir constantly.
Cool 5 minutes.
Stir in peanuts.
Drop mixture by teaspoons on wax paper.
Let cool completely.
Drop in plastic bags and refrigerate until ready to use.

title: beef rouladen
directions: Spread meat flat, stuff with bacon and onions; roll up.
Hold together with toothpick.
Roll in flour, salt and pepper; brown in 3 tablespoons shortening.
When brown, take out and saute onion and garlic about 5 minutes.
Add 1 cup water to loosen drippings.
Add meat and 1 beef bouillon.
Simmer 1 1/4 hours.
Last 15 minutes, add sliced mushrooms and a little Gravy Master, if necessary thicken with remaining flour.
Double recipe for more servings.

title: raisin carrot salad
directions: In medium sized bowl, combine carrots, raisins, celery, salad dressing and salt until well mixed.
Makes about 2 1/2 cups. Serves four.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Chill and serve with fresh fruit.

title: light raspberry jam
directions: Boil jelly jars (from grocery store or hardware) on rack in large pot filled with water 10 minutes.
Place flat lids in saucepan with water.
Bring to boil; remove from heat.
Let stand in hot water until ready to fill.
Drain well.

title: famous oatmeal cookies
directions: Beat together oil, sugar, eggs, water and vanilla until creamy and add remaining ingredients.
Drop by spoon on cookie sheet. Bake for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: lemon cooler
directions: Mix together and press on bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 25 minutes in a 350° oven (until light brown).
Cool.

title: oatmeal fudge bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix brown sugar, 3/4 cup margarine, eggs and vanilla.
Mix in Bisquick and oats.
Reserve mixture.

title: spinach with rosemary
directions: Wash spinach; chop and place in heavy pot.
Add rosemary, parsley, onion and butter; cover well.
Simmer in own juice until tender.
Remove cover.
Add salt and pepper.
Serve very hot.

title: pigs in a blanket
directions: You will also need 20 wooden toothpicks.

title: chocolate ice cream
directions: Mix together ingredients; put into freezer container.
Finish filling with milk until it reaches the line, about 1/2 gallon. Makes 4 quarts ice cream.

title: pasta with pepperoni, pepperoncini and roasted peppers
directions: Arrange pasta in 10-inch skillet, sprinkle with rosemary, layer on pepperoni, pepperoncini and roasted red peppers.
Pour boiling water over contents of skillet.
Cover, bringing to full boil, cook briskly over medium high heat or until pasta is firm but tender.
Stir in cream and grated cheese, reheat and serve immediately.

title: scrambled eggs for a crowd
directions: Coat a 9 x 13-inch pan with butter.
Set aside.
Beat eggs well.
Add hot milk slowly to eggs.
Add salt and pepper to taste. Pour egg mixture into buttered pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes; stir.
Bake 15 minutes more.

title: caramel sweet potatoes
directions: Peel and quarter potatoes; boil in water until tender.
Pour off water leaving just enough to cover potatoes. Add other ingredients and cook until syrup is thick.

title: stuffed snow peas
directions: Split snow peas lengthwise.
Blend remaining ingredients. Spread in peas.
Chill and serve.

title: pork chop and potato bake
directions: Brown chops in large skillet.
Drain on paper toweling.
Place potatoes and mushrooms on bottom of buttered 2-quart (oblong) casserole.
Place chops over.
Mix water and soup mix and pour over chops.
Cover and bake 1 1/4 hours or until potatoes are tender at 350°.

title: oh so easy chicken
directions: Melt butter and pour in bottom of layer casserole dish.
Dump ingredients, rice, soup and water in casserole dish with butter and mix well.
Place chicken on top.
Cook at 325° for 1 hour or until done.
Cook, uncovered.

title: pizza breadsticks
directions: *May thaw dough by using the defrost cycle in the microwave. Routinely check dough to make sure it is not being cooked because excess heat will destroy yeast.

title: family casserole
directions: Combine soup, cottage cheese, sour cream and milk.
Mix mixture until well blended.
Add all the other ingredients except cheese and mix lightly.
Spoon into quart casserole or may take larger one.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.	When done top with cheese and continue baking until cheese is melted.

title: chicken broccoli
directions: Cook chicken in water to cover until tender, about 1 hour. Cool.
Take chicken off bone and cut into bite-size pieces. Combine chicken and stuffing mix; set aside.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Add to chicken mixture.
Pour into buttered 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes covered.
Remove cover and bake 10 minutes longer.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: banana fritters
directions: In mixing bowl, add 1 cup pancake mix and gradually add beverage, stirring with fork until blended.
Batter should not be too thin; keep it more thick.
Peel bananas and cut into 3/4 to 1/2-inch slices; dip into batter and fry until golden brown, about 3 minutes, turning to brown both sides.
(Electric skillet is perfect at 375°.)
Remove bananas with slotted spoon from oil and drain on paper towels.
Sprinkle generously with powdered sugar. Serve warm.

title: twinkie cake
directions: Cut twinkie in half and place in cake pan. Cover with pineapple, sliced bananas, and coconut. Mix pudding as directed pour over coconut. Cover with Cool Whip.

title: brown rice
directions: Preheat oven to 375° to 400°.
Melt margarine in a large casserole dish.
Cook onion in skillet until it is translucent. Add rice and stir briefly over low heat until grains are coated with butter.
Stir in broth and water, making sure there are no lumps in the rice.
Add salt, pepper and basil.
Cover with close-fitting lid and place in oven.
Bake 17 to 20 minutes.
If rice is not to be served immediately, keep dish covered.
Makes 8 servings.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix together banana and milk. Cream the oil, sugar and eggs, beat one at a time. Add vanilla, nutmeg, salt, baking powder and baking soda.
Mix banana and milk and add to the other.
Add nut meats and mix. Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix potatoes and all ingredients well.
Pour mixture into greased casserole dish.
Add topping, if wanted.
Bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: roast pork tenderloins with strawberry glaze
directions: Rub tenderloin with seasonings. Place on sheet pans. Roast at 350° for 15 minutes or until light brown. Brush with glaze. Roast and glaze until tenderloins are done, about 35 to 40 minutes or until internal temperature reaches 160°.

title: christmas fruit cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs, milk and molasses and blend well.
Sift 3 cups of flour and spices together.
In large pan, place all the currants, raisins, chopped dates, candied fruit and chopped walnuts and add 1 cup of flour.
Coat all the fruit well.
Now add flour and spice mixture to egg mixture and blend. Then add coated fruits and nuts slowly.
May be necessary to complete this by hand.
Decorate with whole 6 red/green cherries and nuts.
Bake 2 to 4 hours in tube pans or small loaf pans at 250°.
Place large pan of water on bottom shelf of oven to increase volume of fruit cakes.

title: everyday chili
directions: Cook ground beef and onion in a deep saucepan until browned, stirring until meat crumbles.
Drain.
Add cup of water and other items.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 20 minutes, stirring when needed.
Servings:
6 cups.

title: lemon chicken salad
directions: Cook pasta.
Rinse in cold water and drain.
In a large bowl, combine yogurt, mayonnaise and lemon juice.
Stir to mix.
Stir in chicken, pasta, grapes, onions and celery.
Mix well.
Serve immediately or refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: chicken turnovers
directions: Cook and chop chicken into small chunks.
Roll out crescent rolls in triangles thinly.
Mix all ingredients together.
Scoop chicken mixture in middle of triangle.
Bring 3 corners to surround chicken and pinch together.
Bake at 350° covered in foil for 10 minutes.

title: buffalo chips(chocolate chip cookies)
directions: Cream shortening or butter and sugars.
Add eggs, one at a time, then add remaining ingredients.
Bake on cookie sheets sprayed with nonstick coating spray at 350° until brown.
Makes 15 to 18 dozen.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Thaw broccoli in sieve over bowl to catch liquid.
Mix soup and onion.
Stir in 1/4 cup liquid drained from broccoli.
Sprinkle 1/3 of broccoli in casserole.
Top with 1/3 of soup mixture, 1/3 of stuffing mix and 1/3 of melted butter. Repeat twice.
Bake uncovered in preheated oven for 45 minutes until hot and bubbly in center.
Yields 8 servings.

title: ginger krakles
directions: Cream shortening with brown sugar, molasses and eggs until well mixed.
Combine flour, baking soda, cinnamon, ginger and cloves.
Add to creamed mixture; mix well.
Chill until dough can be handled easily, about 2 hours.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Form dough into 1-inch balls; roll each ball in sugar to coat well. Place balls 3 inches apart on cookie sheet.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes, until set but not browned.
Makes 6 to 8 dozen.

title: creamy praline
directions: Combine 2 cups sugar, 1/2 stick butter and milk in saucepan and cook until soft ball forms in cold water. While this is cooking, caramelize 1 cup sugar in heavy iron skillet. Combine with milk and sugar mixture, stirring constantly until smooth. Add 1/2 stick butter and nuts. Drop from spoon on wax paper. Makes 3 to 4 dozen.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Wash, dry and butter potatoes. Bake at 400° for 1 hour. Cut each
in
half lengthwise and scoop out carefully to keep shells intact. Add butter, salt and pepper and mash.
Add milk and beat until fluffy.
Sometimes it takes more than 1 cup of milk.	Fold in	cheese and chives and re-stuff shells, sprinkling tops	with Parmesan
cheese.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes. Serves 12.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Combine 3/4 cup sugar, cornstarch and salt in a medium saucepan.	Gradually stir in milk and cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture is thickened.
Beat egg yolks until thick and pale.
Gradually stir about 1/4 of hot mixture into yolks; add to remaining hot mixture, stirring constantly.
Cook over medium heat 5 minutes, stirring constantly. Remove from heat and stir in 1 cup coconut, butter and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Spoon into pastry shell.	Beat egg whites, cream of tartar and 1/2 teaspoon vanilla at high speed with a mixer until foamy.
Gradually add 1/4 cup plus 2 tablespoons sugar, 1 tablespoon at a time, beating mixture until stiff peaks form and sugar dissolves.
Spread over hot filling, sealing to edge of pastry.
Sprinkle with remaining coconut and bake at 325° for 25 to 28 minutes or until golden.
Cool on a wire rack and chill 1 hour before serving.

title: strawberry pizza
directions: Combine flour, brown sugar, margarine and nuts.
Put on pizza pan
and
bake at 300° until golden brown.
Soften cream cheese to
room temperature, then add Cool Whip and remaining sugar.
Mix well
and
spread on crust.
Mix strawberries and glaze and spread on top.

title: apricot jello salad
directions: Drain pineapple.
Heat juice; mix with jello.
Set aside to cool.
Mix Cool Whip and buttermilk, adding cooled jello and then drained pineapple.

title: pistachio delight
directions: Mix pudding and pineapple with Cool Whip.
Mix with marshmallows and pecans.
Chill.

title: chicken fried chicken
directions: Heat cast-iron skillet and then gently pour cooking oil in pan until pan is half full.
Oil is hot when you can drop a crumb of batter into hot oil and it floats back to top of oil beginning to fry.

title: english toffee bars
directions: Cream the margarine and brown sugar for 3 minutes.
Add the egg yolk, flour and vanilla.
Put in jelly roll pan; bake on lowest shelf in oven at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Break up the chocolate bars; put on crust, then melt and spread.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Put first 6 ingredients in bowl and mix with electric mixer.
Pour mixture into 2 unbaked pie shells and bake 35 to 40 minutes or until top of pie has puffed up like a souffle.
The center will still be shaky when pie is removed from oven.
Don't overbake.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix corn, soup, cheese, onion and sour cream together.
Spread crushed crackers on top.
Sprinkle melted oleo over crackers. Cover with slivered almonds and bake at 350° for 30 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: seven layer casserole
directions: Brown ground beef in small amount of fat and salt and pepper to taste.
Drain excess fat.
Line bottom of casserole dish with spuds, salt to taste and several pats of butter.
Add carrots. Follow with layer of rice and onion.
Add peas.
For layer six, add ground beef.

title: orange glazed pork
directions: Place pork loin, fat side up, on rack in roasting pan.
Bake in preheated 325° oven for 1 hour and 30 minutes.
Saute onion in butter in saucepan until soft.
Stir in remaining ingredients; cook, stirring constantly, until thick.
Brush over pork loins; bake for 1 hour longer, brushing every 15 minutes with onion mixture.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Combine scalded milk, shortening, sugar and salt; cool to lukewarm.
Soften yeast in lukewarm water.
Stir and combine with cooled milk mixture.
Add egg and about half the flour; beat well. Add enough remaining flour to make a soft dough; mix thoroughly.

title: pear pickle
directions: In large pot on low heat, cook vinegar and sugar.
Add pickling spices.
Be sure to stir so sugar won't stick to the pan. After sugar dissolves, you may turn heat up so it will begin boiling.
After it starts boiling, reduce heat.
Cook at least 2 or 2 1/2 hours real slow.
Put in jars and seal.
(Do not overcook.)

title: quiche
directions: Sprinkle meat on bottom of pie crust then cover with grated cheese. Beat eggs slightly, add milk and salt and mix. Pour over meat and cheese. Bake for 15 minutes at 425 degrees. Reduce oven temperature to 300 degrees and bake 30 minutes or until knife inserted 1 inch from edge comes out clean. Let stand 5-10 minutes before cutting. Serves 6.

title: zucchini squash bread
directions: Cream sugar, eggs, oil and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients. Add to creamed mixture.
Stir in pineapple and nuts.
Fold in zucchini squash.
Bake in 2 (9-inch) loaf pans at 350° for 1 hour. Test with cake tester for
doneness.

title: apple cupcakes
directions: Cream sugar, oil and eggs.
Add apples, nuts (if using), baking soda, vanilla, salt, cinnamon and flour.
Stir until well blended.
Pour into paper-lined cupcake tins.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until done.

title: zucchini bread in a bundt pan
directions: Beat eggs until foamy, gradually beat in oil and sugar.
Add zucchini and cinnamon; mix well.
Gradually blend in flour, mixing well after each addition.
Fold in nuts. Pour into greased 3-quart Bundt pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: oven fried potatoes
directions: Peel and cut up potatoes into French fries.
Put in Tupperware bowl.
Add olive oil and salt and pepper to taste.
Put top on bowl and shake until potatoes are seasoned.
Spray cookie sheet with vegetable cooking spray.
Arrange potatoes on cookie sheet so they're not overlapping.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes in a 400° oven (turn once while baking).
These are a low fat alternative to fried potatoes--They're even better!

title: deep dish apple pie with candied crust
directions: Fill well-greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan with thinly sliced apples which have been washed, peeled and cored.
Mix together the remaining ingredients until it is the consistency of coarse corn meal, using a fork or pastry blender.
Put the brown sugar crust on top of sliced apples to form a crust.
There isn't any bottom crust.
Bake in moderate oven at 325° for 50 minutes.
It's delicious topped with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: banana walnut cake
directions: Mix sugar and butter until creamy.
Add eggs and beat until smooth.
Add milk and vanilla.
Then sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Add to creamed mixture, stirring well.
Add mashed bananas and nuts.
Stir until thoroughly mixed.
Bake in greased 9 x 9-inch pan in preheated oven at 350° for 60 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: ponchos
directions: Place nacho chips in the bottom of a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Cover nacho chips with hamburger meat then refried beans. Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Bake in a 350° preheated oven until cheese is melted.
When removed from oven, add in layers the guacamole, sour cream, shredded lettuce, chopped tomatoes and onion.
Then serve!

title: cheese ball
directions: Drain pineapple; mix with cream cheese.
Add salt.
If you prefer a different kind of taste, try adding a tablespoon of minced onion, bacon bits or green chopped onions.
Roll into ball, then roll in nuts.
Refrigerate overnight.
Serve with crackers or celery and carrots.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Combine
pudding and milk.
Beat until thick, then fold in dairy
topping.
In
x 13-inch dish, put layer of graham crackers, then a layer of mix, then another layer of crackers, then another layer of mix, then top with graham crackers.

title: cloud biscuits
directions: Blend shortening into flour.
Add beaten egg to milk and mix. Add to flour which has been mixed with other dry ingredients. Knead 15 times.
Roll to 1/2-inch.
Cut out biscuits and bake at 425° for 10 to 14 minutes.
May be kept in refrigerator 1 to 3 hours before baking or may be frozen and used as needed.

title: shoo-fly pie(poor house pie)
directions: Mix flour, sugar and lard until crumbling.
Put 1/2 crumbs over bottom of 9 to 10-inch pan.
Save the rest for top.
Add 1 cup boiling water to scant 1 cup or 3/4 cup of baking molasses. Then add baking soda.
Stir until foamy and then pour into pie crust pan.
Add remaining 1/2 of crumbs to top.
Bake at 400° for about 1/2 hour, then bake at 350° for another 1/2 hour.

title: pumpkin butter
directions: Put
all ingredients except sugars in a heavy saucepan; bring to a boil.	Quickly add sugar.
When mixture returns to a
boil, cook for 1 minute.	Skim foam.
Ladle into hot jars. Adjust
lids. Process
in
boiling water bath for 10 minutes. Yield:
About 3 pints.

title: whipped cream frosting
directions: Combine milk and flour; cook, stirring until thick. Cool completely.
Combine shortening and sugar; beat until smooth.
Add to creamed mixture.
Add salt and vanilla; beat well.
Beat for 5 minutes more for a whipped cream consistency.

title: doves-doves-and more doves
directions: You will need 1/2 slice bacon, small slice hot pepper (or what you prefer) and wooden toothpicks.
Take 1 side of breast, lay on 1/2 slice bacon.
Put piece of pepper and roll and secure with toothpick.
Just before you are ready to use, mix garlic powder and soy sauce.
It only takes a small amount in a plastic bag; add rolled dove breasts and marinate until either your barbecue or your broiler is hot.
If in broiler, use a pan.
Cook until bacon is completely cooked; turn once.
You won't believe how good!

title: strawberry angel dessert
directions: Mix powdered sugar, cream cheese and oleo.
After this is mixed well, add Cool Whip, then spread it on cake bits in a large oblong dish.
Combine berries and glaze.
Cover cake with berries and glaze mixture.
Serve.
Ideal for ladies meetings.

title: sweet dill pickles
directions: Boil ingredients.
Slice cucumbers; pack in jars with 1 head dill to each jar.
Pour syrup over cucumbers and seal.
Process for 5 minutes in hot water bath.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: Rinse shrimp and pat dry.
Melt oleo in large skillet.
Stir in next 5 ingredients.
Bring to boil over medium heat.
Stir in shrimp.
Cook 5 minutes or until shrimp are pink, stirring occasionally.
Stir in parsley.
Serve hot.

title: barbecue pork sandwiches
directions: Roast pork shoulder, trim and cut into 1 inch cubes.

title: steak diane crepes
directions: Brown meat in butter and add remaining ingredients.
Makes 8 cups.

title: zesty carrots
directions: Spread carrots (cut lengthwise into strips) in shallow baking pan.
Mix water, onion, horseradish, mayonnaise, salt and pepper. Pour over carrots.
Top with bread (or crackers) crumbs mixed with melted butter.
Bake in quick-moderate oven (375°) for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: peanut butter chocolate squares
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Grease 13 x 9-inch pan. Mix sugars and margarine in large bowl until well blended. Stir in flour, oats, peanut butter, baking soda, vanilla, salt and egg. Spread in pan. Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown at 350°. Immediately sprinkle with chocolate chips. Cool 5 minutes. Spread chocolate evenly. Drizzle with Easy Glaze. Cut in 2-inch squares.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream oleo; add sugar.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Sift dry ingredients together; add alternately with buttermilk.
Add vanilla, bananas and nuts.
Bake in loaf pans (2 big pans or 4 small loaf pans).
Bake at 350°.
When cake is done, cake will turn loose from sides of pans.

title: cabbage patch soup
directions: Brown meat, onion and celery.
Add all items, except cabbage. Cook 15 minutes.
Add cabbage.
Simmer until cabbage is tender.

title: spinach balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together and roll into balls.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: dunking platters cookies
directions: Blend margarine and sugars.
Stir in eggs and vanilla.
Mix in oatmeal and flakes.
Sift flour with soda and baking powder and combine thoroughly with oatmeal mixture.
Stir in vanilla.
Drop by tablespoonful onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Keep cookies well separated.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes. Makes 6 dozen.

title: squash relish
directions: Mix squash and onions together.
Sprinkle salt over mixture and let stand 1 hour.
Drain squash well and mix in remaining ingredients, except pimentos.
Bring to a boil.
Add pimentos and bring to a second boil.
Remove from heat and seal in jars.

title: curry dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate for 2 hours before serving.
Great with cauliflower or celery.

title: parmesan potatoes
directions: Melt butter in pan.
Peel and quarter potatoes.
Mix dry ingredients, then coat potatoes and put in buttered pan.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: new england clam chowder
directions: Make roux:
Cook salt pork until crisp; remove meat.
Saute onions in oil until clear.
Blend in flour.
Cook over low heat, stirring frequently, 2 to 4 minutes.
Set aside to cool.

title: randee's cornbread salad
directions: Mix all of this together; serve.

title: hamburger-potato casserole
directions: Grate cheese.
Boil potatoes 5 minutes and drain.
Fry meat, onion and peppers; drain.
Place meat mix in bottom of large baking dish.
Top with potatoes.
Mix soup and sour cream; pour on top of potatoes.
Top with 2/3 cheese.
Cover with foil and bake 45 minutes or until potatoes are tender at 350°.
Remove foil and top with remaining cheese.
Bake for 5 minutes.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Cook chopped spinach.
Beat eggs until fluffy.
Add spinach, cottage cheese, grated sharp cheese, flour and salt.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in a 9 1/2 x 6-inch casserole.
Sprinkle bread crumbs and paprika on top.

title: delicious dessert
directions: Blend and press into ungreased 9 x 12-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes, then let cool.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Mix and bake at 325° for 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in baking dish.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix flour, sugar, milk and baking powder.
Pour over melted margarine. Spread fruit evenly over batter.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: ham and cheese ring(very easy and tastes great)
directions: Prepare hot roll mix according to directions.
Let rise to double.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix butter or margarine and sugar together.
Add eggs, salt, salad oil and vanilla.
Sift together flour, cream of tartar and baking soda.
Mix all together; roll into small ball, roll in sugar, flatten on cookie sheet with glass dipped in sugar.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.

title: baked chicken with rice
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, mix rice and onion soup mix.
Lay chicken pieces on top of mixture.
In a bowl, mix chicken soup and water.
Pour over chicken and rice.
Bake, uncovered, about 1 1/2 hours at 375°.

title: creamy surprise
directions: Mix all items together.
Chill for 1 hour before serving.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Melt peanut butter and margarine in saucepan over low heat. Stir in vanilla and remove from heat.
Add sugar and cracker crumbs.
Shape into small balls.
Chill while preparing dip mixture.
Melt chocolate chips and wax in double boiler over medium heat.
Dip balls and cool on wax paper.
Reheat dip mixture if it becomes too thick.
May want to dip candy a second time. Store, covered, in a cool place.

title: sweetheart salad
directions: Heat pineapple with sugar.
Soften gelatin in 1/2 cup cold water.
Stir into pineapple mixture.
Add lemon juice, cherry juice and cream cheese; mix and cool.
Add chopped cherries. Chill.

title: easter egg bread
directions: Mix salt, sugar, butter and milk; warm over low heat.
In large bowl, mix 1 cup flour with yeast.
Add warm milk mixture, eggs and vanilla; beat at low speed until moist, then at high speed for 3 minutes.
Beat in flour.
Turn and knead dough.
Turn into greased bowl; let rise 45 minutes.
Punch dough down; divide into 3 equal portions.
Make rope and braid dough.
Form ring and pinch together.
Press eggs on top.
Let rise 1/2 hour.
Bake in a 350° oven for 25 to 35 minutes.
Brush top while baking with egg yolk and water mixture to brown and glaze top.

title: squash salad
directions: Mix all vegetables together.
Pour dressing over.
Mix well. Cheese may be added just before serving.
This will keep several days in refrigerator.

title: cream of chicken
directions: Cook together; serve on toast.

title: sugar-coated peanuts
directions: Place in a heavy saucepan and cook until water is gone. Spread out the peanuts on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 10 minutes, until done.
Taste one or two to see if they are as done as you like them.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix with electric mixer.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Add eggs and beat until light and fluffy.
Sift together flour, cream of tartar and soda. Add to creamed mixture and blend well.
Refrigerate for 1 hour. Shape dough into 1-inch balls, then roll into 6 tablespoons of sugar and 2 tablespoons of cinnamon.
Place 2 inches apart on lightly greased cookie sheets.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Balls will flatten.
Makes about 18 dozen.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Chop mushroom stems and saute with crackers that have been broken; add egg and water.
Add crabmeat broken; saute all.
Stuff mushrooms and set on cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: cheesy tater tot hot dish
directions: Fry hamburger with chopped onion.
Put in cake pan. Add milk and soup. Mix all together and spread in the pan. Put Tater Tots on top and sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream together first 3 ingredients; then add applesauce and soda, cinnamon, flour and mix well and add nuts and raisins.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni and salt as desired.
Rinse with cool water and drain.
Add vegetables (uncooked), cheese, mayonnaise and seasonings.
Chill and serve.

title: chicken tetrazzini with sherry sauce
directions: In large stockpot, combine hens, bay leaves, onions, celery and salt.
Cook until chicken is tender.
Cool and remove from bones, reserving broth.
Cut chicken into pieces.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown beef and onion together; drain.
Layer in bottom of 13 x 8-inch casserole dish.
Layer 2 cans cream of celery soup on top of beef and onion.
Place Tater Tots.
Bake at 350° until golden brown, approximately 35 minutes.

title: quick cobbler
directions: Stir with a spoon the first 4 ingredients.
Mix well.
Melt butter in baking dish then add batter.
Then add berries or fruit. Bake at 350 degrees 30 min. or until done.

title: spaghetti art
directions: Cook spaghetti according to package directions; drain and add food coloring.
Keep covered until ready to use.
Let the children stick the wet spaghetti on their paper in any design they wish. They really enjoy the color and feel of the warm noodles.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: In saucepan, combine 1 1/2 cups water, sugar, vinegar, reserved pineapple syrup and red food coloring.
Heat to a boil. Turn off heat.
Combine 1/4 cup cornstarch and 1/4 cup cold water; stir into saucepan until mixture thickens.	Combine flour, 2 tablespoons oil, 2 tablespoons cornstarch, salt, white pepper and egg.
Add chicken pieces and stir until chicken is well coated. Heat oil in skillet or wok to 360°F.
Fry chicken pieces in hot oil until golden brown.
Remove and drain on paper towels.	When ready to serve, layer green peppers, pineapple and chicken on a platter and pour sauce over the top.

title: lemon ice cream pie
directions: Combine ingredients and press into 9-inch pie pan.
Bake at 300° for about 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: orange-pineapple salad
directions: Dissolve gelatine in boiling water.
Add other ingredients. This jells quicker than most gelatine salads because of frozen orange juice.
Pour in mold.
Sliced peaches may be substituted for the mandarin oranges.

title: taffy apple dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and serve with Granny Smith apples.

title: spinach balls
directions: Cook and drain spinach.
Mix dressing mix, onion, eggs, cheese, thyme, garlic, salt and pepper.
Mix in butter.
Chill until mixture is firm enough to form into balls.
Roll into bite size balls.
Bake for 10 to 15 minutes at 350°.
Serve hot.

title: ice cream
directions: Beat ingredients and add fruit.
Add to container of ice cream freezer and add enough milk to fill container to proper level.

title: no cook fruit cake
directions: Mix with hands. Press back in liner of vanilla wafer box. Better if made a few days ahead. Refrigerate.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Place chicken breast halves between sheets of waxed paper or plastic wrap.
Pound slightly with mallet.
Sprinkle with salt and black pepper.
Heat 1 tablespoon each of oil and butter in large skillet.
Cook chicken over high heat for 4 minutes on each side. Do not cook longer or they will be overcooked and dry.
Transfer to warm serving platter.

title: cherry torte - good and easy
directions: Beat egg whites until foamy.
Add baking powder, vanilla and 1 cup sugar.
Beat until stiff.
Add cracker crumbs and nut meats. Butter 9-inch pie plate.
Pour in pan and bake at 300° for 40 minutes.
Put on rack to cool.

title: brown sugar pie
directions: Beat all ingredients together in a pan.
Heat on low heat, stirring occasionally, until thickened.
Pour into a baked pie crust.
Cool.
If desired, top with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: chicken broccoli hot dish
directions: In a 13 x 9-inch pan, layer chicken, onion, mushrooms, broccoli and butter.
Mix sour cream and soups together; pour over chicken then top with Stove Top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes (30 minutes covered and 15 minutes uncovered).

title: shirlee's crackers
directions: Mix oil and dry ingredients.
Pour over crackers.
Blend well and dry on paper towels.

title: apple cobbler or cherry
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Spray a 9 inch pie pan with Pam. Spread pie filling in pan (cut up apple pieces). Spray the filling with butter spray (5 sprays). Mix remaining ingredients together with a whisk. Pour over pie filling (may not cover completely). Bake 25 - 30 minutes or until golden brown. (May have to turn broiler on for a few minutes to brown the top). Great with a dollop of Cool Whip Free.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: In bowl, put cottage cheese, crushed pineapple and 1 large Cool Whip.
Stir all up together.
Put dry Jell-O.
Sprinkle all over this, then stir it all up together.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: orange julius
directions: Put all ingredients in blender; blend well.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Put all the ingredients and 1/2 the potatoes into a blender and blend until potatoes have passed through the blades.
Add remaining potatoes and blend again.
Do not overblend.
Pour into hot well-greased griddle and fry until golden brown.
Makes 12 pancakes.

title: grilled pork tenderloin
directions: Coat the tenderloin with olive oil, black pepper and garlic powder.
Let set an hour or two.
Grill over medium coals for 10 minutes per side, 20 minutes total.
Place on hot platter and slice across the grain.
Pour on sauce.

title: mayonnaise bread
directions: Mix.
Cook
in greased muffin tins at 400° until brown, about 20 minutes.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine in a saucepan the butter, sugar, cocoa, dry milk and water. Mix well and let come to a rolling boil for 2 minutes. Remove from heat and add peanut butter and vanilla. Mix well. Gradually add oatmeal and mix well.
Drop on waxed paper or greased pan.
Yields approximately 50 cookies!

title: gooey pecan bars
directions: Beat first 3 ingredients with an electric mixer and press into 11 x 14-inch pan.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Soak chicken breasts in cold salt water for 1 hour.
Rinse off chicken and place in large pot, cover with water and add onion and bouillon cubes.
Bring to a boil, then reduce heat and let simmer for 1/2 hour to 45 minutes, until chicken is tender.
Remove chicken and set aside to cool.
When cool, remove skin and cut in large pieces and set aside.
While chicken is cooling, peel and slice carrots in large pieces and put in broiling broth.
Wash and cut celery in large pieces and put in boiling broth with carrots; let cook until al dente.
Add dumplings and let cook covered for 15 minutes.

title: pasta tetrazzini
directions: In large skillet, cook onion in margarine until tender.
Blend in soup, water and cheese.
Cook over low heat until cheese is melted, stirring frequently.
Add remainder of ingredients; heat until warmed through.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: While noodles are boiling by directions on package, mash beef. Add soup, onion, milk and cheese. Drain noodles and add, mixing carefully. Cover with bread crumbs. Bake 1 hour at 375°.

title: our favorite potato soup
directions: Cut potatoes into bite size pieces.
Cover onion and potatoes with water.
Cook until potatoes are done.
Add butter, salt, pepper and parsley to soup.
Bring to a boil.
Add evaporated milk, stirring the whole time, until liquid has thickened.
This soup is wonderful!

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix all ingredients. Place in large buttered pan. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: ravioli
directions: Saute onions and garlic.
Add pork and brown for 10 minutes. Add ground beef, salt and pepper.
Cook for 10 minutes.
Cool and then combine in large bowl with remaining ingredients.

title: potato pork chop dinner
directions: Place pork chops in a large baking pan with 1 slice each of onions, green peppers, then tomato on top.
Add potatoes with slices of onions, green peppers and tomatoes on top of them.
Mix water with soup and pour it over the top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: roasted red peppers
directions: Place peppers on gas grill and cover.
Cool until slightly blackened.
Take off and peel skin.
Put peppers in pan; add garlic and oil.
Mix well.
Put in jar and freeze.
Great between two slices of Italian bread, hamburgers, steak, chicken or pork chops.

title: dietetic apple cake
directions: Combine raisins, water and 1 packet of sweetener; simmer over medium heat until water is absorbed.
Combine oil, apple, applesauce, eggs, prunes, spices, vanilla and 8 packets of sweetener.
Mix well.
Add dry ingredients.
Mix well.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix ingredients, roll out on floured surface.
Roll pie crust thin.

title: easy barbecue chicken
directions: Mix ketchup and Coke together.
Add salt and pepper.
Put 1/4 cup of sauce in frying pan, then place cut-up chicken in pan. Pour remaining sauce over chicken.
Cover, cook 10 minutes, turn chicken and cook 10 minutes.
Turn chicken and cook 10 minutes.

title: chopped apple cake(sugar-free)
directions: Bake 15 minutes in 350° oven.

title: corn dish
directions: Mix together and place in refrigerator for a few hours before serving.

title: cappuccino parfait
directions: Combine pudding mix, instant coffee and cinnamon.
Slowly add milk, stirring to keep mixture smooth.
Cook as directed on pudding package.
