Pour into wide bowl.
Place plastic wrap or wax paper directly on pudding.
Chill.
Swirl in whipped topping, reserving some to top each serving, in parfait glasses.
Top with whipped topping.

title: pumpkin swirl cheesecake
directions: Combine crumbs and margarine; press onto bottom of a 9-inch spring-form pan.

title: apple kuchen
directions: Cream margarine and 1 1/2 cups sugar.
Blend in eggs and vanilla.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add alternately with milk, mixing well after each addition.
Pour into a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Arrange apple slices on top of batter. Combine the 1/2 cup sugar and cinnamon and sprinkle over the apple slices.
Bake in 375° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: fluffy white frosting
directions: Cook flour and milk until thick.
Cool.
Cream butter, shortening, vanilla, sugar and salt.
Add cooked milk mixture and whip until it looks like whipped cream.
Frosts two layers or a 9 x 13-inch cake.

title: chicken and dressing
directions: Toss stuffing mix with half can of soup, broth and eggs. Spread in an 11 1/2 x 7 1/2 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish.
Top with deboned chicken.
Combine remaining soup with milk.
Pour over all.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until set.

title: herb vermicelli
directions: Saute mushrooms and garlic in olive oil.
Break whole tomatoes with a fork and add with crushed tomatoes to mushrooms and garlic. Add basil and let simmer for 30 minutes.

title: one crust rhubarb pie
directions: Mix all together; pour into crust.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes, then at 350° until done.

title: mexican meat loaf
directions: Mix well with 1/2 cup salsa.
Use an 8 x 4 x 2-inch loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Top meat loaf with remaining salsa.

title: creamy seafood dip
directions: Blend cream cheese, mayo and lemon juice.
Add crab, onion and celery.
Serve with crackers.

title: hot mulled cider
directions: Tie whole spices in cheesecloth or put in tea strainer.
Put all ingredients in pan.
Cover and simmer on low heat for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: tater chip chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Cut chicken in strips; dip in egg, then roll in potato chips.
Have an oven pan ready, with the butter melted.
After you roll the chicken in the chips, lay it in the pan.
Put in oven for about 40 minutes or until golden brown.
You can also use pork chops or tenderloin.

title: crunchy granola breakfast bars
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients in large bowl; stir well, and set aside. Combine honey, brown sugar and oil in a small saucepan; cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until sugar dissolves and mixture is thoroughly heated.
Remove from heat; add peanut butter and vanilla extract, stirring until peanut butter melts.
Pour honey mixture over oats mixture; stir well.
Mixture will be dry at first; continue stirring until moist. Press mixture into a greased 15 x 10-inch jellyroll pan, using greased fingertips.
Press mixture flat with the back of a wide metal spatula.
Bake at 250 for 1 hour and 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Cut into bars while warm.
Let cool completely in pan.
Remove bars from pan. Store in an airtight container at room temperature up to 1 week.

title: apricot salad
directions: Mix pineapple and sugar, bring to a full boil.
Take off, add jello and cream cheese.
Stir in first mixture until cream cheese had dissolved.
Add ice water, celery and nuts.
Put in box, let thicken slightly and then add Cool Whip.

title: squash casserole
directions: Slice squash.
Place in large pot of water; cook squash until tender.
Drain and mash.
In large bowl, combine squash, sour cream, carrots, onion, soup, salt and pepper.
Mix thoroughly. Spray a 3-quart casserole dish with vegetable spray.
Sprinkle 1 cup of stuffing on bottom of casserole dish.
Pour squash mixture over stuffing.
Top mixture with 1 cup stuffing.
Dot with margarine.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs thoroughly with sugar, salt, corn syrup, and melted butter.
Add pecans.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for about 50 minutes or until knife inserted in center of filling comes out clean.
Cool and serve with whipped topping or ice cream.

title: pretzel mold
directions: Crush pretzels with rolling pin (but not too finely).
Put crushed pretzels into mixing bowl and add sugar and then butter, until pretzels are moist.
Press into 9 x 13-inch baking pan and bake for 8 minutes at 400°. Cool off totally.
Mix Cool Whip with 1 cup sugar.
Pour over cool pretzel crust.
Set aside.

title: grandma morris' chicken and dumplings
directions: Beat egg lightly; add water.
Add flour, shortening and salt. Roll out and cut.
Let stand 30 minutes.

title: microwave pot roast
directions: In 4 to 6-quart microwave dish, combine all ingredients.
Cook High 15 minutes and then low, 90 minutes.
Turn meat over 1/2 cooking time.
Slice and serve immediately.

title: lemon-pecan squares
directions: Combine flour, powdered sugar and 1 teaspoon lemon rind.
Cut butter into flour mixture with a pastry blender until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Press firmly into 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: angel frost punch
directions: In blender container combine 1 package strawberries, 1 can lemonade concentrate, 1 cup water and 1/2 of the ice cream.
Blend until thick and smooth.
Pour into punch bowl.
Repeat with other half in blender.
Carefully pour lemon-lime beverage down side of punch bowl.
Gently stir to mix.
Makes 14 to 15 ounce servings of punch.

title: chicken or turkey dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Add a little more water if mixture is too thick.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate cheese cranberry cake
directions: Combine cracker crumbs, butter and sugar in mixing bowl.
Put in 10 x 2 3/4-inch spring-form pan.
Press crumbs on bottom and 2-inches up sides.
Combine cranberry sauce and chocolate chips in saucepan.
Melt over medium heat until smooth, stirring frequently. Beat cheese and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Save 1/3 cup chocolate sauce.
Put rest on crust.
Put cream cheese mixture on top.
Drizzle rest of chocolate sauce on top, then gently with knife swirl to make design.

title: apple sheet cake
directions: Mix all except apples and nuts in bowl until well blended. Fold in apples and nuts.
Bake in ungreased 14 x 10-inch sheet pan for 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Toss lightly the chicken, celery, almonds, salt and onion. Add lemon juice, mayonnaise, peas and eggs. Pile lightly in an 11 x 17-inch casserole.
Mix together cheese, potato chips and spread on top of casserole.
Bake in a 450° oven for 10 minutes or until bubbly.

title: sweet noodles
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions.
Mix sour cream, cottage cheese, eggs and margarine with sugar and salt.
Stir into drained noodles.
Put in glass baking dish and place peaches on top.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 to 3/4 hour.

title: best ever tomato bisque soup
directions: In a large saucepan, melt 1/2 stick butter; stir in flour and cook the roux over low heat, stirring for 3 minutes.
Remove pan from heat and pour in milk and chicken broth, whisking vigorously, and continue to whisk until it is thick and smooth.
Add tomatoes including liquid (Italian plum tomatoes are best).
Add the puree to the milk mixture with onion, honey, parsley dill, basil, marjoram, bay leaf and salt and pepper.
Simmer mixture, stirring frequently, for 20 minutes.
Divide the bisque in heated bowls containing melted butter (1 teaspoon each bowl).
Garnish with sprinkled dill weed.
Serves 4.

title: rice pilaf
directions: Brown rice in margarine with onions and peppers.
Add chicken broth.
Cook 20 minutes.

title: perking roast beef
directions: Cut slit in roast, completely through meat.
Put garlic and onions in slits.
Put roast in big bowl and pour vinegar over it. Make sure vinegar runs into slits.
Cover and place in refrigerator for 24 to 48 hours.
Before cooking, pour off vinegar.
Place meat in iron pot and brown on both sides.
Pour coffee and water over roast.
Cover and cook slowly for about 6 hours on stove.
May have to add more water.
About 20 minutes before serving, add salt and pepper.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Mix hash browns and 1 egg together and spread on greased pizza pan.
Scramble 7 eggs and milk.
Place on top of hash browns. Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Top with shredded cheese.
Top with ingredients of choice:
onion, green pepper, ham, fried crumbled bacon, etc.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: graham cracker chocolate chip cookies
directions: Crush graham crackers and add other ingredients.
Mix thoroughly.
Form into balls the size of a large walnut.
Press lightly.
Bake at 350°
for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: potato bake
directions: Combine all ingredients in large baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until potatoes and onions are tender.
Can be frozen.

title: meaty manicotti
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare noodles as directed.
Drain noodles and set out, not touching each other.

title: buffalo cookies
directions: Beat together shortening, sugars, milk, vanilla and eggs.
Mix flour, baking powder, soda and salt and add to creamed mixture. Mix at low speed.
Stir in remaining ingredients with a spoon. Place 1/4 cup dough on greased cookie sheet, 3 inches apart.
Bake at 350° for 13 to 15 minutes or until light brown on edges.
Cool 3 minutes, then remove with spatula.

title: summer punch(10 quarts)
directions: Combine all but the ginger ale and chill.
Add chilled ginger ale just before serving.

title: pumpkin cake roll
directions: Beat eggs well.
Stir in pumpkin and lemon juice.
Beat.
Add other ingredients except nuts.
Beat well.
Pour into well-greased, floured jelly roll pan (10 x 15-inch).
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Turn out on dish towel that has been sprinkled with powdered sugar.
Roll up.
Cool.
Unroll carefully.

title: japanese cabbage
directions: Heat
oil
in frying pan with lid.
Add cabbage; season lightly with
celery
seed and pepper.
Add water and cover to allow steam to cook cabbage.
Cook 2 to 3 minutes, then remove lid and
sprinkle soy sauce over cabbage.
Cook until tender-crisp.

title: easy peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a large mixing bowl, beat the sweetened condensed milk and peanut
butter until smooth.
Beat in the biscuit mix and vanilla; mix well.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls; roll in sugar.
Place balls 2 inches apart on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten cookies with a fork.
Bake 6 to 8 minutes. Cool in pan.
Store at room temperature.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Spray foil pan (9 x 13-inch) with Pam.
Layer drained pineapple.
Combine sugar and flour and sprinkle over pineapple. Layer grated cheese.
Top with crushed crackers.
Melt oleo and pour over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sour cream and cheese potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes and mash. Add sour cream, onion, 2 cups of cheese, salt and pepper. Mix well. Pour in greased casserole dish; put remaining cheese on top. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: cheesy corn spread
directions: In large bowl, crumble cheese with fork or blend with mixer to form small bits.
Mix in remaining ingredients, except corn, until well blended.
Stir in corn.
Cover; chill several hours or overnight.
Can be stored in refrigerator up to 1 week.

title: crispy cheese wafers
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a medium mixing bowl cream together cheese and butter; add flour, salt and Tabasco sauce.
Mix in Rice Krispies.
Roll into small balls and press flat onto cookie sheet. Bake for 15 to 20 minutes.
Yield:
6 dozen.

title: rice pudding
directions: Beat eggs with sugar.
Add milk.
Stir until sugar is dissolved.
Add vanilla, cooked rice and raisins.
Stir.
Pour into 28 x 18 x 4-inch dish.
Chip margarine on top.
Bake at 425° for 1/2 an hour.

title: easy jam tarts
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat the cream cheese and the milk until fluffy; set aside.

title: dinner rolls
directions: Combine 2 cups flour and yeast.
In saucepan, heat milk, sugar, butter and salt just until warm (115° to 120°).
Stir constantly.
Add to flour mixture.
Add eggs.
Beat at low speed for 1/2 minute, scraping sides of bowl.
Beat 3 minutes at high speed.
Stir in as much remaining flour as you can mix with a spoon.
Turn out onto a floured surface.
Knead in enough remaining flour to make a moderately stiff dough (6 to 8 minutes). Place in a greased bowl.
Turn once.
Cover.
Let rise in a warm place, about 1 hour.
Punch down.
Divide dough in half.
Let rest 10 minutes.
Shape into desired rolls.
Cover.
Let rise 30 minutes.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: chocolate-dipped fruit
directions: Rinse fruit and pat dry.
Combine over hot (not boiling) water the chocolate morsels and shortening.
Stir until melted and smooth.
Remove from heat and keep over hot water.

title: low-fat orange salad
directions: Mix cottage cheese and Jell-O
together. Add pineapple and oranges and stir in Cool Whip.

title: monster cookies
directions: Note:
This recipe is easier to mix if cut in half!
Dough can be stored in refrigerator in any airtight bowl until used.

title: dump cake
directions: Spread crushed pineapple and cherry pie filling on bottom of pan evenly.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over fruit.
Drizzle melted margarine over cake mix.
Sprinkle chopped nuts over mixture. Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: mama's butter cookies
directions: Cream ingredients together.
Roll into 3/4-inch balls.
Place on a cookie sheet.
Using a flat-head clothespin, make an indentation in each cookie; fill with various jellies.

title: mayonnaise rolls
directions: Cook in muffin pans.
Makes 6 rolls.
Bake at 425°.
Quick, easy and delicious.

title: french toast
directions: Combine milk and sugar and mix until sugar dissolves.
Beat eggs into mixture.
Add cinnamon and cardamon and blend in well. Spray pan with Pam.
Dip bread slice into milk mixture and brown on both sides.
Serve warm with syrup and butter.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Melt 1 cup butter and stir in 1/4 cup of cocoa and water. Bring to a boil.
Combine flour, brown sugar, baking soda, cinnamon and salt; add cocoa mixture as well.
Add 1/3 cup of Eagle Brand milk, eggs and vanilla.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°. Melt 1/4 cup butter, 1/4 cup cocoa, balance of Eagle Brand milk, sugar and nuts.
Pour on warm sheet cake pan.

title: pierogi dish
directions: Cook lasagna and drain.
Boil potatoes; mash with milk, butter and cheese.
(Melt cheese in milk before adding.)
Season to taste. Brown onion in melted oleo (2 tablespoons).
Put thin layer of melted oleo in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add layer of lasagna, layer of potatoes and the onion.
Continue layers with onion last.
Pour oleo over top.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: lemon-lime sheet cake
directions: Bake cake as directed in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool 20 minutes. Mix lime jello with 3/4 cup boiling water until dissolved.
Add 1/2 cup cold water and set aside.
When cake is cooled, poke holes in cake with a fork and refrigerate.

title: butter nut stuff
directions: Mix brown sugar, nuts, Pet milk and margarine in heavy saucepan.
Stir over medium heat until bubbling all over top. Boil and stir 5 minutes more.
Take off heat and add vanilla.
Add Rice Chex cereal.
Mix well.
Put on cookie sheet to cool.
Store in airtight container.

title: chili burgers
directions: Combine drained beans, mayonnaise, chopped onion and chili powder.
Set aside.
Season ground beef as desired.
Shape into 4 patties and broil, turning once.
Top each with a tablespoon of bean mixture.
Broil 6 inches from heat until lightly browned. Serve on a toasted bun.
Garnish with tomato slices and onion rings.
Serve with remaining bean mixture.
Makes 4 servings.

title: cabbage salad
directions: Toast sesame seed and almonds in butter. Then mix together.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients.
Fold in carrots and nuts.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours or until done.

title: soft lemonade cookies
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream butter and sugar. Add eggs. Combine flour and baking soda; add to the creamed mixture alternately with 1/3 cup of lemonade concentrate. Mix well. Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto ungreased baking sheets. Bake at 400° for 8 minutes. Remove to wire racks. Brush with remaining lemonade concentrate. Sprinkle with sugar. Cool. Yields 6 dozen.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Add egg, milk and vanilla. Beat well.
Stir in salt and flour.
Blend well.
Divide in half. Cover and chill for 1 hour.

title: honey bun cake
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix brown sugar, cinnamon and nuts.
Pour over cake and swirl into batter with fork.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 325°.

title: company's favorite side dish
directions: Place cooked rice in bottom of 9 x 13 sprayed casserole. Top with broccoli, mushrooms and water chestnuts. Mix Cheez Whiz and undiluted mushroom soup. Warm in microwave. Pour over casserole. Top with croutons that have been tossed with melted butter. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serves 8 to 10.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Over medium heat in large frying pan, saute garlic in olive oil until golden; remove.
Add chopped onion, green pepper and celery until golden.
Add ground chuck and saute until brown (10 minutes), stirring constantly.
Add seasonings, stirring with beef mixture for about 5 minutes.
Add tomatoes, tomato sauce, tomato paste, 1 can of water and mushrooms.
Put garlic back into mixture.
Reduce heat to simmer, cover and cook for 1 hour.
Serve over spaghetti noodles and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: lemon squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream the margarine and 1/2 cup confectioners sugar.
Add 2 cups flour; stir with wooden spoon until well combined.
Pat evenly into a 13 x 9-inch pan; bake for 20 minutes.

title: fried pies
directions: Blend sifted dry ingredients with shortening.
Mix in milk and egg.
Turn out onto floured board.
With floured hands form into large ball.
Divide into 24 balls about the size of walnuts.
Roll or press into circles to 1/8-inch thickness.
Place 1 tablespoon filling in center of dough; fold over and press to seal edges with fork.
Prick top side several times with fork.
Fry in deep oil until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar or glaze with powdered sugar and water.

title: southern okra
directions: Combine the first four ingredients.
Set aside.
In a covered saucepan, cook okra in boiling water for 10 minutes or until tender.
Drain and set aside.

title: miss ann's pound cake
directions: Beat sugar into softened butter.
Add eggs, one at a time, still beating.
Add flour, whipped cream and vanilla gradually and gently.
Pour into greased and floured loaf pan and sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.
Cool.
Remove from pan. Serve with fruit and vanilla ice cream.

title: neiman-marcus cookies(makes 8 dozen)
directions: Grind oatmeal in blender and blend until it's a fine powder. Cream butter and sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix with flour, oatmeal, salt, baking soda and baking powder.

title: german sweet chocolate cake
directions: Cake:
Melt chocolate in 1/2 cup boiling water.
Cool.
Stir in 1 teaspoon vanilla; cream 1 cup butter and 2 cups sugar in bowl. Beat in 4 egg yolks, 1 at a time.
Stir in chocolate mixture; add flour, soda, salt and buttermilk, mix well.
Fold in 4 beaten egg whites; pour into 3 greased and floured 9-inch cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes, or until cake tests done; cool.

title: oriental salad
directions: Mix all together and chill!

title: welsh cakes
directions: Mix spices and flour; rub butter into spiced flour.
Add sugar and currants; bind with beaten egg and milk to form a stiffish paste.
Roll out on floured board to about 1/4-inch thick.
Cut into 2 1/2-inch rounds.
Bake on moderately hot griddle 3 to 5 minutes each side until mottled brown.
Sprinkle with sugar. These take only a few minutes and they're really wonderful.

title: uncle scooter's french apple pie
directions: Crumble and pat onto bottom of a 9 or 10-inch pie pan.

title: zucchini chocolate pound cake
directions: Mix flour, cocoa, baking soda, baking powder, salt and cinnamon in a large bowl.
Set aside.
Beat well in a medium bowl the butter, sugar and eggs.
Add vanilla, orange peel and zucchini to egg mixture.
Mix well.
Add the egg mixture alternately with 1/2 cup milk to dry ingredients.
Stir in chopped nuts, if you like.
Bake in a greased and floured tube pan for 1 hour, or until cake tests done, in a 350° oven.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: chocolate syrup
directions: Put sugar and cocoa in saucepan.
Add water, stirring until mixed well.
Cook until heated through completely and sugar is dissolved.
Add vanilla; cool until syrup is barely warm.
Put in container and refrigerate.

title: cabbage roll entree
directions: In water cover, boil 1 whole large cabbage until leaves are limp.
Cool and separate the leaves.
Spoon enough meat mixture onto a large cabbage leaf to permit rolling tightly and roll up. Repeat until all meat mixture is used up.
Slice the smaller cabbage leaves into large pot and arrange the cabbage rolls on top.
Bring one pound can tomato puree to a boil in saucepan and stir in the juice of a lemon, 1/2 cup raisins, 1 cup brown sugar and 1 large onion sliced.
Pour tomato mixture over cabbage rolls. Cover and simmer on low heat for 1 hour.
So delicious!

title: b~b~q onion
directions: Take onion and slice 3/4 way down but leave whole. Put in aluminum foil and fill up with italian dressing. Wrap good and cook until tender.

title: repta denton's apple wisp
directions: Pare apples and slice them into a buttered baking dish. Sprinkle with sugar and a little cinnamon.
Cream sugar, butter and flour and spread over apples.
Bake until brown and until apples are tender.
Delicious.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Combine and chill 1 to 2 hours. Serve over lettuce leaves. Garnish with nuts.

title: slush punch
directions: Combine all ingredients, except ginger ale.
Mix well and freeze.
Before serving, remove from freezer and allow to partially thaw.
Stir in ginger ale.
Serve slushy.
No ice is needed.

title: marinated corn
directions: Mix sugar, vinegar, oil, salt and pepper in a saucepan.
Heat to boiling and pour over other ingredients.
Chill overnight.

title: crock-pot chili
directions: Brown beef in shortening.
Drain.
Mix in crock-pot with all other ingredients.
Stir well.
Cook on low for 8 to 10 hours, on high for 5 hours or automatic for 6 hours.

title: seven layer taco dip
directions: Layer each item without mixing in a glass bowl.
Refrigerate overnight or several hours.
Serve with chips or use as a salad. The amounts of green onions, chopped tomatoes and sour cream as well as cheese depends on your taste.
I use the medium-size sour cream and heavy on the grated cheese.

title: apple blueberry crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix fruit fillings in a baking dish.

title: ranchero beef shortcake
directions: In a large skillet, cook bacon until crisp.
Add meat and cook, stirring until well browned.
Add remaining ingredients, except cornbread.
Cover and simmer 30 to 40 minutes, until meat is tender.
Bake cornbread as directed on box, except pour both mixes into one 8-inch square pan.
When baked, cut into large squares.
To serve, split in 2 layers with beef and sauce spooned in middle and on top.
Makes 6 servings.

title: sandwiches for a crowd
directions: Cut bread in half lengthwise. Hollow out top and bottom of loaves, leaving 1/2-inch shell. Remove and save for another use. Combine cheese, onions, mayonnaise and Worcestershire sauce; spread on cut side of bread. Layer ham and roast beef on tops and bottoms. Place pickles on bottom halves. Wrap in plastic
wrap and put in refrigerator for 2 hours. Cut into 1 to 1 1/2-inch slices. Makes 12 to 14 servings.

title: butter pecan ice cream
directions: Saute pecans in 1/4 cup melted butter until lightly browned, stirring frequently.
Drain pecans on paper towels.
Combine egg yolks, 1 cup milk and brown sugar in top of a double boiler. Place over simmering water; beat at high speed of an electric mixer for 5 minutes.
Beat in 1/4 cup butter, 1/2 tablespoon at a time.
Continue beating an additional 5 to 7 minutes, or until mixture thickens.

title: crispy baked parsnips
directions: Steam or cook the parsnip sticks in small amount of boiling water until crisp-tender, about 10 minutes.
Cool slightly. Preheat oven to 425°.

title: dog ears(fried bread)
directions: Scald milk and pour over sugar, salt and shortening.
Add 3/4 cups hot water.
Let cool to lukewarm.
Dissolve yeast in 1/4 cup lukewarm water.
Add both mixtures together.
Add flour and knead. Set aside, covered with towel, until double in size.
Knead down again.
Pinch off small pieces and flatten.
Fry in skillet in shortening on both sides until light brown.
Very good buttered and served with soup beans.

title: bean salad
directions: Drain beans and pimento. To the beans add green pepper, cloves of garlic and celery.
Heat the sugar, vinegar and vegetable oil together, heat till sugar dissolves.

title: leek and potato soup simplicity
directions: Split open leeks lengthwise; wash leaves very well.
Slice. In a large, heavy soup pot, combine potatoes, leeks, stock, water and butter.
Bring to a boil; turn down to medium and let simmer strongly, uncovered, until liquid is reduced by one-half, about 1 hour.
Stir occasionally.
Taste for seasoning, adding salt and pepper if needed.
Mash some of the potatoes into soup to thicken it slightly.
Place some croutons in each soup bowl and ladle in soup.
Top, if desired, with a bit of grated Parmesan, a sprinkle of parsley or a dab of a dairy garnish.
Serves 6 to 8 as an entree.

title: drop biscuits
directions: Mix flour, baking soda and salt in bowl. Cut in Crisco with fork or pastry blender until mixture looks like coarse meal.
Add milk and stir until blended.
Drop from spoon onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 425° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 16 biscuits.

title: royal rhubarb jam
directions: Combine rhubarb and sugar; let stand for 2 hours.
Stir once, then boil for 10 minutes.
Add pineapple and boil another 10 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in gelatin.
Pour into jars and seal.

title: chili chicken casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Saute onion in butter until yellow.
Stir in soup, pimento and chili pepper.
In buttered 4 qt or 2 two qt baking dish layer half of ingredients in this order:
noodles, chicken, (sprinkle with salt and pepper), soup mixture and cheese. Repeat layers one more of each.
Bake 45 min. 12 servings.
You can substitute chicken with turkey.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Drain water from asparagus and cool the frozen peas in it. Layer asparagus, peas, eggs, mushroom soup and cheese in casserole dish.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: sherbet punch
directions: Place sherbet into punch bowl and add ginger ale.
Stir with dipper and serve.

title: buffalo wings
directions: Fry chicken wings in hot oil. Melt butter and mix with Texas Pete. Coat chicken wings completely. Spread on shallow pan and bake 10 minutes at 350° in oven.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs, sugar, corn syrup and butter; add pecans. Pour into pie shell. Bake 50 minutes at 350°.

title: tomato swiss sole
directions: Butter the bottom of shallow pan.
Place the fillet in pan and cover with sliced cheese.
Mix all other ingredients in small bowl and pour over fish.
Bake at
350° for 25 minutes.

title: barbecued lamb
directions: Blend ingredients and marinate lamb several hours.
Smoke, covered, over low coals about 25 minutes per pound or until meat thermometer registers desired degree of doneness.
Baste frequently.
Let rest 20 minutes at room temperature before carving.

title: date loaf candy
directions: Boil sugar and milk until soft ball stage.
Add chopped dates and cook until dates are soft.
Add nuts, butter and vanilla. Remove from heat and beat until pretty stiff.
Pour onto damp cloth.
Roll up into log and refrigerate several hours.
Unroll and slice when needed.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute celery and onion in oleo and mix with rest of ingredients in a casserole dish.
Bake in oven for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: old-fashioned cooked potato salad dressing
directions: Combine dry ingredients; mix.
Set aside.
Put eggs, butter and milk in top of double boiler.
Stir with wire whisk.
Stir while cooking.
When hot, add dry ingredients.
Cook for 2 minutes.
Add vinegar and water.
Cook until thickens.
Toss with desired amount of cooked potatoes, chopped celery, onion and hard-cooked eggs.

title: english cheese melt
directions: Mix cheeses and mayo or Miracle Whip and spread on English muffins.
Broil until cheese is melted.
Goes great with spaghetti.

title: scallop broil
directions: Rub the bottom and sides of shallow baking pan with garlic. Add 2 tablespoons of the melted margarine and swish around pan. Arrange scallops in the dish.
Mix the salt, white pepper, cayenne and paprika.
Season the scallops with the spice mixture.
Pour the remaining 2 tablespoons of margarine over the scallops.
Place under the broiler.
Cook 5 minutes, stir and cook 5 more minutes. This is good served over rice.
Garnish with lemon.
Serves 2.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees.
Cut cookie dough into 1/8 inch thick slices.
Arrange on pizza pan or cookie sheet that is covered with lightly greased foil.
Press slices together lightly with fingers to form crust.
Bake 10 - 12 minutes until golden brown.

title: sweet and sour pork
directions: In a large skillet, melt shortening.
Add pork.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Brown well.
Cover.
Simmer for 20 to 25 minutes, or until tender, stirring occasionally.
In medium bowl, combine brown sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Add 2/3 cup pineapple liquid, vinegar, water, soy sauce and Worcestershire sauce.
Mix well. Stir into meat.
Cook over low heat until thickened, stirring constantly.
Stir in green pepper, onion and pineapple.
Cover. Simmer 6 to 8 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Serve over rice.
Serves 6.

title: dip for pumpernickel bread
directions: Mix all together.
Chill at least 4 hours or longer.
Buy 2 loaves of whole round pumpernickel bread.
(I usually order it from the Tom Thumb bakery.)
Hollow out one loaf and tear remaining bread into bite size pieces.
Pour dip into center of hollowed out bread.
Enjoy!

title: spinach casserole
directions: Cook spinach, squeeze out all the liquid.
Combine with the sugar, undiluted soup, egg and cheese.
Turn into a greased 1 1/2 qt. casserole.
Melt butter, garlic salt and red pepper in small skillet.
Toss bread cubes in butter.
Spread over spinach mixture.
Bake for 1 hour at 350 degrees.

title: strawberry fluff pie
directions: In large mixing bowl, whip together egg whites, strawberries, sugar and lemon juice.
Beat at high speed for 15 minutes.
Fold in Cool Whip and pour into baked pie shell and freeze.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Add thawed strawberries and juice with beaten eggs and mix until well blended.
Add oil and sugar; blend well.
Combine dry ingredients and add together.
Mix well.
Add nuts, if desired. Pour into 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake at 300° for 70 to 80 minutes. Cool 10 minutes in pan, then remove.

title: honey walnut fruit salad
directions: Blend honey and mayonnaise until smooth. Toss remaining ingredients with lemon juice. Stir in honey mixture and refrigerate until ready to serve. Makes about 7 cups.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Let cookie mix soften; spread on cookie sheet and cook until brown. Cool.

title: polynesian cake
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix by hand.
Do not overbeat. Pour into ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes. Instead of raw carrots, may use 2 jars of Junior baby food carrots.
Top with frosting.

title: pineapple banana cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar, baking soda, salt and cinnamon in large bowl and make a well in center.
Add oil, pineapple, nuts, vanilla and bananas.
Stir.
Do not beat.
Pour in greased and floured tube pan.
If desired, put a glaze on with almost cool cake.
Bake at 350° for 75 minutes or 1 hour and 15 minutes or until done when tested with toothpick.

title: uncooked tomato sauce
directions: Put oil, tomatoes, garlic and basil in a container and marinate for 2 hours.
Season with salt and pepper.
Stir the sauce gently.
Mix with hot pasta and serve immediately.
Great in summer when regular pasta sauce is too heavy.

title: potapple salad
directions: Boil potatoes with skin until cooked.
Let potatoes cool and then peel off skin.
Cut potatoes and apples into 1/2-inch to 3/4-inch cubes.
Cut hard-boiled eggs into small cubes.
Slice carrots and radishes into thin slices.

title: raisin and mandarin bread pudding
directions: In a large bowl, beat eggs with an electric mixer until combined.
Add sugar a little at a time, beat mixture until it ribbons when beater is lifted.
This takes approximately 8 to 10 minutes.
Add the rest of the ingredients listed before the bread slices, beat until combined.

title: shrimp mold
directions: Combine tomato soup and cream cheese.
Heat and stir, then add gelatin. Add mayonnaise and water.
Stir. Add remaining ingredients.
Pour in mold and congeal. Serve over crackers, Melba toast or party bread.

title: whoopie pies
directions: Mix all the ingredients.
Spoon this onto baking sheet.
Cook at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: faye reed's hominy casserole
directions: Mix all except onion rings.
Bake 45 minutes at 300°.
Top with the crumbled onion rings and bake 15 minutes more.
This recipe freezes well, either baked or unbaked, but do not add onion rings until you reheat to serve.

title: quick peach cobbler
directions: Mix sugar, flour and oleo together.
Mix will be lumpy.
Put peaches in a 9-inch square casserole dish.
Cover with crust mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until crust is brown. Serve with whipped topping or ice cream.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: *For a spicy sauce, add 2 cans sauce and 2 cans of El Paso hot sauce.

title: sugar-free jello salad or dessert
directions: Mix raspberry jello with 2 cups boiling water, stir until completely dissolved.
Add frozen raspberries and stir until thawed.
Add mashed banana and pineapple.
Put half the mixture in large clear dish and place in refrigerator.
Leave rest of mixture on counter (it will not set up too quick).
When first half of mixture is set, put Equal into sour cream, spread over set jello, then very carefully pour remaining jello over sour cream.
Return to refrigerator to set.

title: pasta carbonara
directions: Prepare fettuccine according to package directions and drain. Gradually add milk to combined salad dressing and garlic in small saucepan; heat thoroughly, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat; blend in egg.
Toss with hot fettuccine until well coated. Add remaining ingredients; toss lightly.
Garnish with basil leaves, if desired.
Makes 5 servings, 324 calories per serving.

title: raspberry punch
directions: Dissolve soft drink mixes in water with ice cubes in nonmetal or stainless steel container.
Add pineapple juice and fruit. Serve at once in punch cups or tall glasses, garnishing each serving with a piece of fruit.
Makes 2 1/4 gallons (9 quarts) or 72 punch servings or 36 tall servings.

title: rum cake
directions: Spray a Bundt pan with Pam spray.
Sprinkle nuts in bottom of pan.
Add batter.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: potato cakes
directions: Fluff up potatoes with an egg beater (or hand mixer).
Mix in flour, beaten egg and seasonings.
Shape into flat cakes and brown slowly in a little fat in skillet, turning until done evenly on each side.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix together with an electric mixer and spread on a plate or bowl. Sprinkle top with chopped vegetables and shredded cheese.

title: cantaloupe ice
directions: Combine water and sugar in a saucepan and simmer about 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and cool.

title: griddle cakes(large recipe)
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, sugar and salt together. Add beaten eggs; add milk and melted butter. Stir and pour on hot griddle.

title: blueberry pie
directions: In large bowl, stir together sugar and cornstarch. Add berries; toss. Pour into crust; dot with margarine. Add top crust and cut slits. Bake at 400° to 425° for 35 to 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: sherried fruit
directions: Mix above ingredients in a sauce pan and cook over medium heat until thickened.

title: caramel-brickle apple dip
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in mixer and blend well.
Add Bits 'O Brickle.
Serve with apple slices that have been dipped in pineapple juice.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Mix the flour and sugar and set aside.
In a saucepan, put margarine, cocoa and water; bring to a boil.
Take off heat and mix in flour and sugar mixture.
Add buttermilk, eggs, salt, vanilla and soda.
Pour in greased sheet pan.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes or longer, until done.
Ice as soon as it is removed from the oven.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Mash egg yolks with a fork.
Add remaining ingredients.
Blend well.
Fill egg whites.
Garnish with sliced stuffed olives, paprika or parsley.
Chill.
Yields 6 servings.

title: pinto bean cake
directions: Cream sugar and oil.
Add beaten egg, mashed up pinto beans, vanilla and butter flavoring.
Sift together flour, salt, baking powder, soda and cinnamon.
Add to sugar and oil mixture.
Add remaining ingredients and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes in a greased 13 x 9 1/2 x 2-inch pan.

title: doie's one-egg cake
directions: Mix Crisco and sugar together; add egg and then sweet milk and vanilla.
Mix baking powder and flour well; add a little at a time to first mixture.
Bake in a 350° oven until done.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion; add seasonings and sauce.
Cook noodles and drain.
Mix milk and egg; add to noodles.
Put noodle mixture in 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Cover with meat sauce mixture and top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Take oil and add sugar, mix well.
Add eggs, soda, salt, vanilla, nuts and apples.
Mix with flour.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.
Turn
oven to 350° and cook another 20 minutes.
Very good coffee cake.

title: linda's sausage appetizers
directions: Fry sausages; crumble.
Drain.
Add cheese, stirring in until melted.
Spread rye slices on cookie sheet.
Place spoonful of sausage mixture on each slice.
Broil for 5 minutes in oven until bubbly.

title: praline cookies
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Beat egg white.
Add 1 tablespoon whiskey to dry ingredients.
Fold beaten egg white into dry ingredients, then fold pecans into mixture.
Drop on greased baking sheet.
(Teflon, if you have it, is best.)
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time, beating after each addition.
Add sour cream.
Combine flour, soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture.
Stir in flavoring and pour into a greased and floured 10-inch tube or Bundt pan. Bake at 325° for 60 to 80 minutes.

title: tamale pie or corn chip pie
directions: Place a layer of corn chips in bottom of buttered casserole. Spread half the chili, onion and cheese over the corn chips. Repeat with remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° to 375° for 25 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix cream cheese and 1/2 cup powdered sugar together and then whip until fluffy.
Place in bottom of baked pie shell.
Whip whipping cream and 1/2 cup powdered sugar and vanilla.
Add crushed pineapple and nuts. Pour over the first mixture.
Chill at least 2 hours.
Garnish; 1/2 cup toasted coconut makes a pretty garnish.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook sugar and milk until soft ball stage.
Add peanut butter and marshmallow cream.
Beat until creamy.
Add nuts and mix. Pour into greased pan.

title: blueberry-bog sparkler
directions: Mix blueberry-cranberry drink together with prepared lemonade in a large pitcher.
Chill well.
Just before serving, stir in 1 1/2 cups ginger ale.
Serve.

title: yummie potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a bowl.
Put in a glass pan (spray with Pam).
Top with cornflakes.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken breasts in peanut butter
directions: In large skillet, melt margarine and peanut butter together. Add chicken and cook until done.
Be careful not to burn.
The chicken will be very tender and have a unique flavor.

title: black-eyed peas and rice(4 to 6 servings)
directions: Melt shortening in frying pan.
Add rice.
Stir and fry a short time.
Add red pepper and chicken broth.
Cover and cook rice until fluffy.
Add black-eyed peas; stir.
Add 1/2 chopped tomato (optional).

title: sausage balls
directions: Combine well sausage, cheese, Bisquick and water.
Roll into walnut-size balls.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet for about 15 minutes at 350°.
Makes about 100 balls.

title: punch bowl dessert(or triffle bowl)
directions: Break pieces of cake in bowl.
Mix vanilla instant pudding and pour over cake, then strawberries and glaze.
Makes 2 layers. Top with cool whip.
Refrigerate for at least 1 hour before serving.

title: baked tuna sandwich(snack)
directions: Mix together.
Split Coney Island buns, put in flat pan, put mixture in and tops on.
Cover with aluminum foil.
Bake in 250° oven for 30 minutes.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: Brown ground beef with bacon.
(Optional:
Add onion and cook until tender, but not brown.)
Drain excess fat.
Add seasonings to meat mixture.
Stir in undiluted soup.
Cook slowly, uncovered, 10 minutes, stirring frequently.
Stir in sour cream and heat through; do not boil.
Prepare noodles as directed.
Serve stroganoff over hot buttered noodles.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: mexican turtle shells
directions: Place shells on lightly greased baking sheet. Do not overlap! Melt chips in microwave on High for 1 minute.
Pour over shells. Repeat with caramels.
Sprinkle nuts over top. Bake in oven at 325° for 10 minutes or until shells are lightly browned. Remove. Cool and cut as you would a pizza.

title: best ever sugar cookies
directions: Cream
margarine,
oil and sugars with mixer.
Add eggs and vanilla
and
beat
well.
In
separate bowl, sift flour, cream of
tartar,
soda
and
salt
together.
Add mixture to creamed mixture and blend well.
Chill dough in refrigerator a minimum
of 2 hours.
Using floured rolling pin, roll part of dough into 1/4-inch layer on floured board, keeping remaining dough in refrigerator.
Use
cookie cutter to cut into desired shapes, then put
on greased cookie sheets.
Repeat procedure with rest of dough.
Bake
in
preheated
oven
10 to 12 minutes or until cookies have a brown rim.
If desired, dough can be shaped
into walnut-size
balls and arranged on baking sheet.
Using a
glass with
a
flat
bottom,
dip glass into granulated sugar and flatten
each
ball.
Return to sugar to dip glass bottom again and repeat.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Stir well.
Mix in remainder of ingredients except for flour.
Measure by dip, level, pour method. Mix in flour until dough is easy to handle.
Add any remaining flour.
Knead 8 minutes.
Place in greased bowl.
Cover.
Let rise until doubled.
Shape into rolls and let rise 1 1/2 to 2 hours. Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: french salad dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients well and refrigerate.

title: lorraine's pumpkin pie
directions: Mix everything, except pumpkin and milk.
Add pumpkin; stir, then add milk.
Stir.
Makes 2 small pies.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes; reduce heat to 350° and bake an additional 20 minutes.

title: ice cream snowballs
directions: Put cookies in a bowl.
Put scoops of ice cream on top of cookies and top with coconut.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Stir all together and simmer for 1 hour.

title: fudge
directions: Grease pans with Pam.
Combine sugar, oleo and milk in a heavy 5-quart Dutch oven.
Bring to a full rolling boil, stirring constantly.
Boil 5 minutes over medium heat.
Remove from heat. Stir in chocolate chips until melted.
Add Marshmallow Creme, nuts and vanilla.
Beat until well blended.
Pour into 2 greased 13 x 9-inch pans.
Cool at room temperature.
Cut into squares.

title: dough art
directions: In a large bowl, mix salt, flour and water.
On a floured surface, roll dough out about 1/4-inch thick with a rolling pin. Cut your dough in desired shape.
For country pie, place the dough in a small pie pan and trim around the edges.
Make small balls out of the dough art for the fruit (cherries or blueberries). Paint the fruit desired color, then lattice the top.
Before baking, brush with Pet milk.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni.
Stir in margarine, onion, salt and pepper over medium heat until onion is slightly tender.
Blend in flour, stirring constantly until mixture is smooth and bubbly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in cheese until melted.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream the sugar and margarine.
Add eggs, flour and vanilla.
Stir in nuts.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch foil lined pan.
Bake for 45 minutes.
Cool cake; cut into 48 bars.

title: dump cake
directions: Pour pineapple, cherry mix and cake mix into greased tube pan. Top with nuts and dot with butter.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serve hot or cold by scooping out and dumping on plate.
Do not mix ingredients.

title: mocha mix
directions: Mix all together (marshmallows last).
Put into a jar or airtight container.
Use 3 tablespoons to one cup of boiling water.

title: tips on using cake mixes
directions: Add to cake mix batter.

title: chocolate mint fudge
directions: Place the chocolate stars in a double boiler. As soon as the water comes to a boil, remove from heat and let stars melt. Whip the whipping cream. Add the flavoring. Add melted chocolate and keep whipping until blended. Can add chopped nuts. Pour in 9 x 13-inch pan. Refrigerate.

title: curried shrimp salad
directions: About 2 hours before serving or early in the day, peel and devein shrimp.
In 4-quart saucepan over high heat, heat water and 1 tablespoon salt to boiling.
Add shrimp; heat to boiling, stirring occasionally.
Cook 1 minute or until shrimp are tender; drain.
Cover and refrigerate shrimp until chilled, at least 1 hour.
Cut zucchini crosswise into thin slices; cut slices into thin strips.
In medium bowl with rubber spatula, mix mayo, lemon juice, curry powder and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Stir in shrimp and zucchini to coat with dressing.
Serve on lettuce leaves.
Makes 6 servings.

title: italian bean toss
directions: Cook beans, drain and chill.
Combine in mixing bowl mayonnaise, cheese, pimento, salt and curry powder.
Add beans, toss and chill.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients, then add blueberries.
Fill tins half full; let rise until up to top.
Combine and let stand 5 minutes.
Add and mix well.
Bake for 350° for 20 minutes.

title: nature's granola(serves 24)
directions: Place in mixing bowl.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour honey in.
Add water and mix again.
Spread on cookie sheets and bake at 250° for 1 1/2 hours.
Stir and turn over once during cooking time.
Keeps well.
For long periods of storage, place in freezer.

title: sausage balls
directions: Combine baking mix, sausage and cheese in bowl.
Shape mixture into small balls.
Place on foil-lined baking sheets.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes or until brown.
Drain well.
Yields 40 servings.

title: microwave beef shanghai
directions: Pour oil into 3-quart microproof casserole.
Add beef, stirring to coat.
Add tomatoes, onion, garlic, salt and pepper.
Cover with casserole lid and cook (micro) on High for five minutes, stirring once.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Melt the Cheese Whiz and 1/2 stick butter.
Drain Veg-All. Crumble Ritz crackers.
Put cheese, Veg-All and 1/2 stick butter in casserole dish.
Place crumbled crackers on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: beef stew
directions: Cook carrots and potatoes until tender.
Drain off 1 cup juice.
Save juice and mix with brown gravy mix.
Add roast beef and enjoy.

title: poor man's pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour
into pie shell and bake at	350° about
50	minutes.
Cool	before	cutting.
An aluminum collar may be placed
around
the edge to prevent the crust from burning on the edges.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour bread pan.
Mix eggs, sugar and oil.
Mix dry ingredients and slowly blend into eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Add strawberries.
Bake for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: apple cake
directions: Add apples and sugar.
Let stand 1/2 hour.
Add oil.
Blend flour, spice, baking soda and salt.
Mix.
Add vanilla, nuts and eggs.
Mix.
Bake in greased 8-inch pan at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: pimento cheese spread
directions: Melt sugar and butter in vinegar over low heat.
Do not boil. Cream the cream cheese and Velveeta cheese together.
Add vinegar mixture and pimento.
Mix.

title: hello dollies
directions: Mix butter in baking dish.
Spread crackers over butter. Sprinkle other ingredients into layers.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: chess squares
directions: Mix together cake mix, 1 egg and butter.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix together sugar, 3 eggs and cream cheese; pour on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Dust with additional powdered sugar.
Cut into squares when cool.

title: lomi salmon*
directions: Soak salmon in cold water and salt for 3 hours.
Remove skin and bones of salmon, then shred finely.
Combine remaining ingredients and chill mixture.
Just before serving, add several cubes crushed ice.

title: mini cheesecakes
directions: Blend together with mixer. Put crushed vanilla wafer in muffin tin. Fill 3/4 full and bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Top with favorite pie filling when cool.

title: pink lady punch
directions: Mix orange juice with 3 cans of water. Stir in remaining juices. For a bright color, tint with red food color. Chill. Makes about 3 quarts.

title: angel cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add egg.
Sift dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture.
Shape into balls and place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: buttermilk pecan pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and eggs.
Add oleo, then buttermilk and vanilla.
Mix in pecans.
Pour into unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes, then reduce heat to 350° for about 20 minutes or until done.
Makes 2 pies.

title: easy reese's squares
directions: Combine sugar, peanut butter, graham crackers and 3 sticks butter.
Pack mixture onto cookie sheets, 13 1/2 x 9 x 1-inch. Melt the remaining ingredients in a double boiler, spread over candy and when cool, cut in squares.

title: applesauce spice pound cake
directions: Beat butter at medium speed with mixer for about 2 minutes or until soft and creamy.
Gradually add sugar, beating at medium speed for 5 to 7 minutes.
Add eggs, 1 at a time, beating just until yellow disappears.

title: banana cake
directions: In mixer bowl, cream the 1 1/4 cup sugar and butter or margarine until light and fluffy. Add eggs, the first 1 teaspoon of vanilla and the banana flavoring. Beat until fluffy.

title: chicken and dressing
directions: Boil chicken in salted water.
Be sure to have plenty of water as this broth will be used in making the dressing.
When chicken is done, cool and remove bones.
Cook chopped onions (use green tops also) and celery in 1 stick of butter.
Add soups and warm. Crumble cornbread and light bread in large bowl.
Mix all ingredients, using the broth.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Pour into large baking dish or several small ones.
Can be frozen. Bake at 350° until golden brown on top.
Baking time depends on size of pan used.

title: orange blossom muffins
directions: Combine eggs, sugar, oil, water and orange juice.
Add sifted biscuit mix.
Stir in marmalade and pecans.
Grease muffin pans, fill 2/3 full.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes or until brown.

title: spinach salad
directions: Bring juice and sugar to a boil.
Add oil gradually, stirring constantly.
Add poppy seed and bring back to a boil.
Remove from heat, cool in refrigerator.
Pour over spinach and toss.

title: cinnamon apple rings
directions: Peel and core apples; cut into rings.
Mix all ingredients; bring to boil.
Stir often; add apples and cook only a few minutes or the rings will break.

title: frozen pie crust
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients, then add egg and water mixture.
Mix and divide.
May be rolled and frozen.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix first three ingredients together, roll into balls and place on cookie sheet. Cover with wax paper. Chill for 1 hour.

title: carol's cold potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes in their skins.
Cool until they can be handled; peel and dice.
Add eggs.
Mix together Hellmann's mayonnaise, light (yellow) mustard and vinegar; mix well.
You can add 1 teaspoon Grey Poupon mustard if you want.
Pour over potatoes and mix well.
Taste and if not sour enough, add more vinegar, mustard and mayonnaise if needed.
Save the tops off green onions and cut in pieces to be added for color.
Can also cut in pimento for color.
Let stand at room temperature to absorb flavor for about an hour, then refrigerate.
Makes 10 servings.

title: gingersnaps
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream Spry and sugar. Add molasses and egg, beating well. Add sifted dry ingredients. Mix well. Roll into small balls. Roll the balls in sugar. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Mix together. Pour into pie shell and bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: chicken dressing
directions: Prepare Stove Top dressing as directed and add remaining ingredients.
Put 1/2 dressing into a well-greased pan.
Cover cut-up chicken pieces, then add rest of dressing.
Cover with can of chicken soup.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until done.

title: easy chicken
directions: Place chicken meaty side down in dish.
Mix together all other ingredients for marinade and pour over chicken.
Refrigerate 6 hours or overnight.
Turn chicken over, then bake, covered with foil for 1 hour at 350°.
Remove foil during last 15 minutes. Baste well.

title: dump cake
directions: Mix cherries and pineapple in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle cake mix evenly over fruit.
Spread coconut and nuts over cake mix.
Pour margarine evenly over top.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly, except margarine and stuffing or cracker crumbs.
Place in greased casserole dish.
Melt margarine and add desired amount of stuffing or crackers for topping.
Sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: sticky buns
directions: Take 2 tablespoons melted butter with the brown sugar, nuts and water and place in the bottom of 10-inch Bundt pan.
Mix white sugar and cinnamon together.
Dip each lightly in rest of melted butter then into sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Place each biscuit on end in Bundt pan; pinch tips or sides of biscuits slightly together.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
After baking, turn biscuit ring out onto plate.
Serve immediately.

title: cheesecake cookies
directions: Beat cream cheese, sugar, egg and lemon juice together for 5 minutes.
Place 1 vanilla wafer in bottom of midget cupcake cup. Put 1 tablespoon filling in cup.
Bake 20 minutes at 375°.
Remove cookies from oven and cool.
When completely cool, place pie filling on top of cookies.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Combine water, 1/2 cup milk and 1/3 cup oleo in a saucepan over medium heat; cook until oleo melts, stirring occasionally. Let mixture cool to 125° to 130°.
Combine 3 cups flour and next 3 ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Gradually add milk mixture to flour mixture, beating at low speed with an electric mixer. Add eggs and beat 2 minutes at medium speed.
Gradually add 1 additional cup of flour, beating 2 minutes.
Gradually stir in enough remaining flour to make a soft dough.

title: sweet cracker cookies
directions: Combine first seven ingredients, mixing until able to form into dough.
Roll out on greased cookie sheet.
Cut into 2-inch squares. Sprinkle with sugar.
Prick with a fork.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes or until light golden brown.
Remove cookies from edge as they brown.
Continue to bake remainder.

title: jalapeno fudge
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into baking dish.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.
Let cool.
Cut into squares.

title: pina colada salad
directions: Mix pudding, pineapple and milk.
Add sour cream and Cool Whip.
Add coconut to salad and mix well.
This makes a large bowl or 3/4 of an ice cream pail.

title: gary's white sauce for vegetables
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Add more vinegar and chives to taste, if needed.
Spoon over asparagus, green beans or baked potatoes.

title: bean salad
directions: Rinse and drain beans.
Thinly slice onion and pepper. Combine with beans in a large bowl.
Add dressing and chill 24 to 36 hours to improve flavor.

title: perfect sunday dinner rolls
directions: Add sugar to yeast and water.
Beat eggs in warm water.
Add oil and salt.
Add to the yeast and sugar mixture.
Gradually add flour.
This dough is rather sticky and will rise at least twice its size, so use a large bowl.
(It is not necessary to knead the dough.)
Let stand overnight.

title: chocolate syrup
directions: Melt chocolate squares over hot water. Add 1 cup boiling water and cook directly over low heat until thick and smooth, stirring constantly. Add 1 cup sugar and continue cooking for 3 or 4 minutes. Cool and store. Yields 1 1/4 cups.

title: impossible pumpkin pie
directions: Put in blender and mix until smooth (1 to 2 minutes).
Pour into pie plate.
Bake 50 to 55 minutes at 350°.

title: ham and macaroni salad
directions: Combine all ingredients, except lettuce, in a mixing bowl. Allow to chill 1 hour.
Serve on bed of lettuce.
Makes 2 servings.

title: chicken and noodle hot dish
directions: Put chicken in a large kettle.
Add diced onion. Cover with water and cook until tender. Take chicken from kettle. Cool enough to handle and remove meat from bones.
Reserve broth and chicken.

title: indian pudding
directions: Mix the cornmeal with the molasses, salt, butter, sugar, baking soda, eggs and spices.
Add 3 cups of hot milk, stirring carefully.
Place in a 2-quart covered pot and bake in a 400° oven until the mixture comes to a boil.
Stir in the remaining hot milk and bake, covered, at 275° for 4 to 6 hours or until all the liquid is absorbed.
Stir every 1/2 hour.
Serve hot with ice cream on top.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: macaroni surprise
directions: Drain both cans of fruit and mix juice with eggs, flour and sugar.
Bring
to
a
boil;
remove from heat.
Add jello powder. Let
cool,
and add drained fruit cocktail, pineapple and oranges.
Mix
with
macaroni.
Add marshmallows and Cool Whip.

title: no salt garni
directions: This can be used to season anything instead of using salt.

title: chicken salad for 25
directions: Cook chicken. Remove skin and bones.
Cut into bite size pieces. Combine all ingredients and toss lightly.

title: fancy beef casserole
directions: Brown onions and beef in pan and then add tomato sauce. Simmer for 5 minutes.
Place squash in a large baking dish and dot with butter.
Arrange eggplant on top of squash.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Pour beef mixture over top.
Bake for 45 minutes in 375° oven.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: bakeless oatmeal cookies
directions: Boil sugar, cocoa, milk and butter together for 1 to 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and peanut butter.
Stir until dissolved.
Add oats and spoon onto cookie sheets quickly.

title: chunky potato soup
directions: Boil potatoes cubes until soft.
In a large pot, heat butter and saute onions until soft.
Add milk and flour, heat a few minutes.
Mix in potatoes, ham and peas.
Lower heat.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: strawberry sour cream gelatin salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Cool; not in the refrigerator. Combine jello with strawberries, pineapple and bananas.
Pour half of mixture in mold to set.
After it has set, spread with a little more than 1 pint of sour cream.
Pour in rest of mixture and jell.

title: pink fluff
directions: Mix Cool Whip, pie filling and pineapple.
(Fold fruit gently into Cool Whip.)
Sprinkle with chopped nuts.

title: orange cheese cake
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients; press into a buttered round cake pan.
Bake at 400° for 6 minutes; cool.
Combine eggs, 1/2 cup sugar, sour cream and vanilla in container of electric blender. Blend for 15 seconds.
Gradually add cream cheese; continue blending.
Add 2 tablespoons butter, blending until well mixed. Drain oranges, reserving 1/2 cup liquid (set aside).
Combine oranges and Cointreau; let set 30 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients. Bake in a pie shell at 325° for 50 minutes.

title: moist rhubarb cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg; mix well.
Add sour milk; mix in sifted flour and soda.
Add vanilla.
Fold in rhubarb.
Before baking, add topping.
Bake in greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: edy's famous spaghetti sauce
directions: Put olive oil in saucepan; slice linquisa in thin slices and fry on medium heat until done (make sure linquisa is cooked good). Add tomato paste with equal parts of water, gradually.
Then add garlic powder and stir.
Remain on medium heat and occasionally stir.
Pour over spaghetti.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bring to a boil and boil 3 minutes.
May use at once or pour over meat loaf, ribs, chicken or etc., and bake.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix dry ingredients; stir in buttermilk, eggs and oil.
Add other ingredients.
Bake in greased skillet at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serve hot or cold.

title: candied fruit cheese ball
directions: Cut in fruit.
Soften cream cheese, add sour cream and other ingredients.
Mold in a ball and roll in crushed walnuts.
More fruit you put in prettier it is.
Nice for Christmas.
Makes two cheese balls (1/2 of recipe for one).
Roll balls in waxed paper. Better made the day before.

title: beef-onion spread
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Chill.
Serve as spread on crackers.

title: sausage cheese dip
directions: Fry crumbled sausage.
Melt cheese.
Combine all ingredients and heat.

title: oven scrambled eggs
directions: Set oven at 350°.
While warming, melt oleo in 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish in oven.
Beat eggs, milk, salt and tarragon.
Add cream cheese, cut in small pieces.
Bake 20 minutes.
Stir gently and bake 10 more minutes.
Garnish with parsley.

title: manhattan deli salad
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions.
Combine remaining ingredients in large bowl.
Add pasta; mix well.
Serve at room temperature or chilled.
Makes about 6 servings.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Grate potatoes and onion.
Strain over bowl to save juices, squeezing vegetables to press out all excess liquid.
Place the juice in a small saucepan; cook over medium heat until thick, stirring constantly.
Combine this with grated vegetables, egg, salt and pepper.
Heat enough Wesson oil to cover bottom of large skillet.
Add potato mixture by large spoonfuls, then flatten a bit.
Fry over medium heat until golden brown, about 6 minutes. Turn just once and cook about 4 minutes to brown other side but keep puffy.
Add more oil as needed.
Drain on paper towels. Serve piping hot with applesauce or pot roast.
Makes 10 to 12 potato pancakes.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Stir in flour and salt.
Add milk slowly, stirring constantly, until sauce boils and thickens.
Add potatoes and heat, stirring occasionally, until the sauce boils again.
Turn potatoes and sauce into a greased shallow casserole. Top with lumps of oleo.
Bake in a 350° oven until potatoes are tender and brown.

title: johnny cake(corn bread)
directions: Sift first five ingredients into mixing bowl.
Add cornmeal. Combine eggs, milk and shortening.
Add to dry ingredients, mixing well.
Bake in a greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan in hot oven (425°) for 40 minutes.
Best served warm.

title: 4-h biscuits
directions: Cut shortening into dry ingredients.
Add milk, stirring gently with a fork.
Knead 10 times gently.
Roll 1/2 inch thick. Cut.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes at 450°.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown hamburger meat; drain fat.
Add taco seasoning mix (follow directions on package).
Add chili beans and heat.
Put mixture in the bottom of a glass pan or large heatproof bowl.
Add cut up or shredded lettuce, cut up tomatoes, red onion and avocados, if possible.
Put shredded cheese over top.
According to your preference, put Fritos on the bottom of your plate or bowl or on top of casserole.
Add sour cream to your preference.
Top off with green taco sauce, hot sauce or salsa.

title: pumpkin pie cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into a 9 x 13-inch cake pan. Sprinkle dry cake mix over liquid, then nuts.
Slowly add melted oleo over top. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: quick n easy homemade bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add oil, sugar, salt and egg. Mix. Stir in flour; don't knead.
Cover and let rise.
Put on floured board; roll out with rolling pin.
Cut with cutter.
Put into greased pan and let rise.
Bake in a 400° oven for 10 to 15 minutes.
Brush with butter.

title: nut bread(no fat)
directions: Using a mixer, blend all ingredients.
Add nuts last.
Bake at 325° to 350° about 45 minutes.

title: date, raisin, chocolate chip cake
directions: Chop dates and raisins.
Boil in the hot water and strain (save the water).
Cream the shortening, sugar and vanilla.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat well.
Sift together the flour, soda, salt and cocoa.
Add dry ingredients to creamed mixture and alternate with water.
Beat well after each addition.
Add dates/raisins/chocolate chips.

title: chicken and broccoli bites
directions: Remove chicken skin.
Pound breast between two sheets of plastic wrap to about 1/4-inch thickness.
Cut into 1 1/4-inch square pieces.

title: apple-walnut cobbler
directions: Mix sugar, cinnamon and 1 1/2 cups walnuts.
Place sliced apples in bottom of greased 11 x 8-inch pan.
Sprinkle with cinnamon mixture.
Sift dry ingredients.
Combine egg, milk and margarine and add dry ingredients all at once.
Mix until smooth. Pour over apples and sprinkle with remaining walnuts.
Bake for 50 minutes at 325°.
Cut into squares and serve with whipped cream to which cinnamon has been added.

title: frozen cherry salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Freeze in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Take out of freezer 30 minutes before serving.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix together all ingredients.

title: mexican spareribs
directions: Combine in saucepan.
Bring to boil.
Roast ribs in 450° oven 30 minutes.
Drain fat.
Reduce to 325°.
Baste with sauce until done.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Sift flour and sugar together and put in large bowl.
Melt oleo, cocoa and water in saucepan.
Bring to a rapid boil; pour over sugar mixture.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all but last two ingredients together thoroughly.
Put into loaf pan.
Cover with bacon if you like that flavor.
Pour tomato sauce over all.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 6.

title: zucchini bread
directions: In blender, mix zucchini, oil and eggs. Sift together flour, sugar, cinnamon and salt. Stir into zucchini mix. Add nuts and vanilla. Bake in 325° oven for 1 hour.

title: banana split cake
directions: Combine the graham cracker crumbs with the melted butter.
Mix thoroughly and press into the bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix together the confectioners sugar, eggs, softened butter and vanilla.
Beat this for 5 minutes with electric mixer on medium speed.
This is the most important step.
Spread this over the crumbs, then spread the drained pineapple.
Cut bananas into thirds, then fourths.
Arrange bananas on top of pineapple. Cover with whipped topping.
Refrigerate 24 hours.
Before serving, add nuts and cherries if desired.

title: cool and easy cake
directions: Mix together by hand for 2 minutes enough batter for a 3-layer cake or 1 (13 x 9). Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: sparkling rainbow melon
directions: In a large bowl, combine honeydew, watermelon, cantaloupe and lemonade.
Refrigerate 1 to 2 hours to blend flavors.
Just before serving, add carbonated beverage, stirring gently.
Makes 8 (3/4-cup) servings.

title: cheddar-pecan bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 5 x 9-inch loaf pan.

title: sweet potatoes ala orange
directions: Peel and half sliced sweet potatoes.
Arrange in shallow baking dish.
Combine other ingredients and drizzle over top. Cover top with foil.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes or until heated through.
Canned sweet potatoes can be used, if desired.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: Saute onion in butter until golden.
Add beef, garlic, flour, salt, pepper and paprika; saute 5 minutes (until beef is cooked). Add soups; simmer, uncovered, about 8 to 10 minutes.
Stir in sour cream and sprinkle with parsley.
Serve on noodles, mashed potatoes, fluffy rice or toast.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Drain the salmon, saving the 1/4 cup liquid.
Remove skin and bones from salmon and flake.
Combine all the ingredients together and pack into a well-greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour or until nicely browned.
Loosen from sides of pan and turn out onto a platter.
Garnish with pimento and lemon wedges.
tags: cream of celery soup or mushroom soup

title: chipped beef twirls
directions: Spread one piece of meat at a time flat out.
Baste with Worcestershire sauce and cream cheese; roll.
Repeat this process until the last layer of meat rolls around the complete bundle one time.
Slice the rolls into eighths.
Place on crackers.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Combine milk, Cool Whip, lemonade and food coloring.
Mix well without blender or mixer.
Pour in pie shells and place fresh berries on top.
Refrigerate at least one hour before serving.

title: onion soup
directions: In butter in a large skillet, saute onion until golden but not browned, about 8 minutes.
In medium saucepan, combine beef broth and sauteed onion; bring to boiling.
Reduce heat; simmer, covered, 30 minutes.

title: easy banana bread
directions: Cream together sugar and shortening.
Add egg and mix completely.
Add water to mashed banana.
Blend alternately with sifted flour, powder, soda and salt.
Add vanilla.
Mix all thoroughly.
Bake in lightly greased loaf baking dish at 350° for 1 hour.
Freezes well.

title: caramel corn
directions: Put 3 family size tea bags or 9 regular size tea bags in a gallon jar and fill with cold water.
Set outside in the sunshine for 3 to 4 hours.
Serve over ice.

title: party rolls-appetizer
directions: Cut each ham and cheese slice into fourths to fit rolls. Slice rolls in half and put 1 piece each of ham and cheese on bottom half of each roll.
Mix other ingredients together and spread top half of each roll.
Close roll and spread more butter mixture on top of each roll.
Wrap rolls in foil and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar; add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Dissolve soda in buttermilk; add to creamed mixture. Place flour in a large bowl; add dates, orange slice pieces, and nuts. Stir to coat each piece. Add flour mixture and coconut to creamed mixture. You may find it easier to mix with hands. Pour into a greased and floured tube pan. Bake at 250° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours. Combine powdered sugar and orange juice; bring to a boil. Pour over hot cake and let stand for 6 to 8 hours before removing from pan.

title: onion bread
directions: Combine soup mix and 2 cups water in small saucepan; cook over medium heat for 8 to 10 minutes.
In small bowl, dissolve yeast in 1/4 cup warm water.
In large bowl, mix together the hot soup, sugar, oil and 2 cups flour.
Beat well with electric mixer.
Let cool to lukewarm.
Add to the cooled mixture the yeast, egg and remaining flour to make a soft (not sticky) dough.
Place dough in a well-greased bowl, turning to grease top.

title: coconut pineapple pie
directions: Melt margarine.
Mix with remaining ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onions together.
Mix all ingredients to gather and pour in greased casserole dish.
Add more grated cheese on top and bake 30 to 45 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: "bull's eye"(mission trip favorite!)
directions: You will need a round lid.
Take round lid and cut hole in center of a slice of white bread.
Butter both sides of bread and circular piece of removed bread.
Place bread in hot frying pan. After one minute, break egg and place in hole.
After one minute, turn bread and place circular piece in pan.
Remove when second side is toasted.
Dip circular piece in yellow of egg.

title: can opener soup
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Cook and drain macaroni.
Mix all ingredients together in a 2-quart saucepan; cook over low flame for 15 minutes.

title: easy chicken dressing
directions: Note:
Bake a pan of cornbread from recipe on bag of white, self-rising corn meal.

title: punch
directions: Dissolve Jell-O and sugar in hot water.
Add juices and extract.
Chill.
Pour sherbet and add ginger ale.
Makes 3 gallons.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix in order given and bake in low oven at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: bubble cake
directions: Cut each uncooked biscuit into fourths and roll in melted butter.
Let drain a second and then roll each piece in sugar mixture.
Pile the biscuits as they are dipped into an angel food or tube cake pan.
Do not use a springform pan as it will leak! Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.
Turn out onto a plate and serve upside-down.
Pull off each biscuit piece as you serve yourself.

title: molded vegetable relish
directions: Dissolve jello and salt in boiling water.
Add rest and chill until thickened.
Add vegetable combination and chill until firm.

title: carole's salad dressing
directions: Add all ingredients together.
Stir well. Refrigerate until chilled.

title: beef-olive ragout
directions: Brown meat in oil; add celery, onion, green pepper, mushrooms and garlic.
Cook until vegetables are tender.
Stir in soup, wine, olives, salt and pepper.
Cover and cook 1 1/2 hours.
Serve over cooked noodles.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: chop suey
directions: Salt, pepper and flour steak.
Brown in 2 tablespoons oil. Add onions and celery.
Cook until tender.
Thicken with flour, soy sauce, water and sugar.
Add bean sprouts and heat well. Serve over cooked rice.
Add additional soy sauce to taste.

title: cheese and wine bread
directions: In a saucepan, heat wine, butter, sugar and salt until warm. Add to 1 1/2 cups flour and yeast in large mixing bowl.
Add eggs. Beat at low speed for 1/2 minute and at high speed for 3 minutes. Stir in cheese and enough flour to make a soft dough and knead until smooth.
Place in covered greased bowl and let rise until it doubles, about 1 1/2 hours.
Punch down and shape into one large 8 inch round loaf.
Place in greased 9-inch pie plate and let rise until it doubles, about 40 minutes.
Bake 20 minutes at 375°. Cover with foil and bake an additional 20 minutes.

title: applesauce spice cake
directions: Soak raisins in warm water.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Combine first 6 ingredients; set aside.
In a large bowl, cream sugar and margarine at medium speed. Beat until light and fluffy.
Add eggs; beat well.
Reduce speed to low.
Add flour mixture alternately with applesauce, beating after each addition, just until smooth.
Stir in nuts and raisins (drained of water from raisins).
Pour batter into pan.
Bake 35 to 45 minutes.
Cool on wire rack.

title: caramel rolls
directions: Thaw bread but don't let it raise.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan. Tear bread into pieces (one loaf).
Pour rest of ingredients over first loaf.
Tear second loaf and drop on first.
Let raise 2 to 2 1/2 hours.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Let set for 10 minutes.
Turn out upside down on foil.

title: benny's rice and steak stir-fry for 3
directions: Cut steak into small pieces and marinate in A.1. and Worcestershire sauce.
Cut veggies in small pieces and marinate in lemon juice and olive oil.
Cook steak in approximately 3 tablespoons olive oil in hot pan just long enough to tenderize. Pour in all veggies at once and stir-fry until tender.

title: white cake
directions: Sift flour,
sugar,
salt and baking powder into mixing bowl. Add Crisco and
3/4 cup of the milk.
Beat well about 2 minutes. Add the
cup
unbeaten egg whites and remaining 1/4 cup milk. Beat
again
real well.
Add vanilla, mix well. Pour into 3 greased
and
floured
cake
pans.	Bake
at 325° approximately 25 minutes. Cool.

title: potato pancakes(from germany)
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pat into small patties.
Fry in hot oil on both sides until golden brown.
Serve with applesauce, bratwurst sausage and red cabbage for a German meal.

title: zucchini and dressing casserole
directions: Boil zucchini for 5 minutes; drain.
Mix grated carrot, chopped onion, sour cream, celery soup and seasonings with zucchini in a 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Mix stuffing flavor package with dry stuffing; sprinkle on top of dish contents.
Spread evenly (do not stir in).
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: onion potatoes
directions: Peel and cube potatoes.
Put potatoes in bowl with dry soup mix.
Toss to coat potatoes.
Put oil in baking dish.
Add coated potatoes.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until potatoes are soft.
Uncover last 5 to 10 minutes to brown.
(Stir every 15 to 20 minutes to avoid sticking.)

title: cream candy
directions: Boil the sugars and water together until sugar is dissolved. Meanwhile, beat the egg whites until stiff.
Slowly pour the hot mixture into the egg whites, continuing to beat until stiff. Immediately pour into buttered
pan.
Cool before cutting.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve sugar in jello mixture and add to other ingredients when jello has cooled.

title: german sweet chocolate cake
directions: Combine cake mix, pudding, chocolate, eggs, buttermilk and oil in a bowl.
Blend for 4 minutes.
Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 13 cake pan.
Bake at 350° for about 35 to 45 minutes or bake until cake tester in center comes out clean and cake begins to pull away from pan.

title: basic yeast rolls
directions: Soften yeast in warm water.
Combine milk, sugar, shortening, potato and salt.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add 1 1/2 cups flour; beat well.
Beat in yeast and egg.
Gradually add remaining flour to form a soft dough.
Beat well.
Place in greased bowl, turning once to grease surface.
Cover.
Chill at least 2 hours, or can be kept up to 4 or 5 days in refrigerator.
About 2 hours before serving, punch down dough; roll out on floured surface.
Cut out with cookie cutter, about 2 inches in diameter, brush with melted butter and fold over.

title: e-z fruitcake
directions: Combine
cake
mix with applesauce, eggs and flavoring. Mix well.
Toss
fruit
and nuts with flour to coat; stir into batter. Mix
well.
Put
in
two
x
5 x 3-inch loaf pans, greased and
lined with waxed paper.
Bake at 275° for 1 hour and 45 minutes or until cake tests done.

title: chocolate sauce
directions: In saucepan, combine sugar, cocoa and cornstarch.
Stir in water.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until comes to a boil.
Boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat; add margarine and vanilla, stirring until smooth.
