Chill.
Makes 1 cup.
Use over Hot Fudge Cake.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Combine sugar, flour and juice over low heat in saucepan until warm.
Stir in pineapple and cheese.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Cover with cracker crumbs.
Drizzle margarine over crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: twinkie cake
directions: Cut Twinkies lengthwise and line bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix pudding as directed on box and pour over Twinkies.
Drain strawberries and layer over pudding.
Cover with sliced bananas; add Cool Whip on top.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Boil chicken until done and tear meat into pieces.
Cook rice as directed on box.
Pour into a baking dish.
Saute onions and celery.
Add soup, cheese and chicken; stir until smooth.
Pour over rice.
Sprinkle top with broccoli pieces.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: onion pie
directions: Combine saltines and 4 tablespoons oleo; press into 9-inch pie plate.
Saute onions in remaining oleo.
Place onions in pie shell.
Combine rest of ingredients (except cheese and bacon) and pour over onions. Sprinkle with cheese and bacon on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: stuffed potatoes
directions: Microwave potatoes until tender, then place in a 350° oven for 5 to 10 minutes, until the skins are tough.
Cool until easy to handle.
Slice top of potatoes off lengthwise.
Use a spoon to scoop out potato, leaving a potato hull.
Combine all ingredients with scooped out potato, mixing well.
Stuff potato skins with mixture until heaping over top.
Place stuffed potatoes in baking pan and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until peaks of potato stuffing are brown.

title: rotini soup
directions: Boil brats, then cut up into bite-size pieces.
Mix all ingredients together but rotini.
Simmer 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Add rotini 15 minutes before eating or until rotini is tender.
Serves 8 to 10 people.

title: mystery pecan pie
directions: Cream together cream cheese, 1 egg, 1/3 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon vanilla in small mixer bowl.
Beat until fluffy.
Spread mixture on bottom of unbaked pie shell.
Sprinkle pecans over creamed mixture.
Beat 3 eggs in small mixer bowl until well mixed, but not foamy.
Do not overbeat.
Add syrup, 1/4 cup sugar, 1 teaspoon vanilla and salt.
Mix well.
Pour over pecans.
Bake 40 minutes or until nuts are lightly browned.
Serve warm or cold. May be frozen.
Thaw at room temperature.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix together.
Sprinkle with seasoned salt, garlic salt and Accent to taste.
Mix and chill.

title: cilantro lime butter
directions: In the bowl of a food processor, fitted with a metal wing blade, place cilantro, lime peel, salt and hot pepper sauce. Process using on and off motions until cilantro is finely chopped, 5 to 6 times, scraping the bowl if necessary.
Add butter; process until combined, about 30 seconds.
(Or finely chop cilantro leaves; place in a medium bowl with remaining ingredients; stir until combined.)
Serve with hot cooked corn-on-the-cob or other steamed vegetables.
Makes 1/2 cup.

title: ruby's fruit salad
directions: Put fruit cocktail and pineapple with juice in a bowl.
Drain oranges and add.
Add bananas and any other fruit you want. Sprinkle with instant pudding over top.
Mix through and let stand 1/2 hour, stirring occasionally.
Chill at least 1 hour before serving.

title: belgian honey cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into greased bread pans. Start baking at 300° and turn up to 325° when cake starts to raise.
Makes 3 loaves.

title: pig-in-the-blankets
directions: Roll the sausages up in the uncooked crescent rolls.
Bake at 350° until rolls are golden brown.
Serve as an appetizer.

title: banana cone-cake kids
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare banana bread as package label directs, except to add peanut butter morsels to batter.
Spoon batter into ice cream cones, dividing evenly.
Place cones on jelly roll pan.
Bake 25 minutes, or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool cones completely on wire racks.
With spatula, spread frosting on top of cake in each cone.
Decorate cakes to resemble doll faces, using candies for facial features and gel icing and licorice for hair.
If desired, tie ribbon around each cup for bow tie or neck tie.
Makes 14 servings.

title: apple cider
directions: Put all ingredients in a 6-quart boiler.
Bring to a boil. Lower heat to maintain temperature just below boil.
Serve in mugs.
Yields:
15-16 cups.

title: snitzel beans
directions: Fry chopped bacon.
Add sugar and vinegar to bacon and fat. Cook until sugar is dissolved.
Add beans and simmer 20 minutes.

title: egg-ham-cheese casserole
directions: Butter a 9 x 13 baking pan (or casserole) and place 8 slices of bread on bottom of pan.
Sprinkle with cheese and ham cubes. Place other 8 slices bread on top of cubes.
Pour beaten eggs, milk and mustard over all.
Cover with foil and refrigerate overnight.
Remove next morning and bring to room temperature. Top with 2 cups crushed corn flakes and 1/2 cup melted butter. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: low-fat lasagna
directions: Cook noodles as directed on package.
Brown turkey in a skillet that has been sprayed with Pam.
Combine turkey with spaghetti sauce.
In a large baking pan put a small amount of spaghetti sauce, then a layer of noodles, Ricotta cheese and Parmesan cheese.
Continue to layer until all noodles are used, ending with Ricotta cheese.
Top Ricotta cheese with 1/2 cup spaghetti sauce.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Spray pan with Pam.
Cook at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes, or until top cracks.

title: summer day fruit cobbler(serves 6)
directions: Set oven at 350°.
Put butter in deep casserole and put in oven to melt.
In the meantime, sift together the flour, sugar, baking powder and salt and mix in the milk.
Pour this mixture into the hot casserole with the melted butter in it.
Do not stir. On top of this, put the sweetened fruit.
Do not stir.
Bake at 350° until top is crusty and brown.

title: poke salet you'll love
directions: Boil poke in a large pot with enough water to cover as it boils (but not in excess).
After boiling approximately 10 minutes, drain off water, the cover with water again. Bring to a boil, then turn off heat. Drain and squeeze excess water from plant.
(Poke will resemble wet cut grass.)
In skillet, add about 1/4-inch vegetable oil. Add chopped green onions (including blades).

Fry until onions are soft and poke begins to soften. Beat 3 eggs in bowl. Add to poke-onion mixture and cook until eggs scramble. Add salt to taste. Serve with fried corn bread, baked beans or your favorites.
Yum, yum!

title: egg nog
directions: Mix all ingredients together in blender.
Place in freezer until ready to serve.
Just before serving, blend enough vanilla ice cream to mixture in blender to make it thick and serve in cold cups.
Sprinkle with nutmeg, if desired.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add bananas, egg and milk; blend well.
In separate bowl, combine flour, baking powder, soda and salt; blend well.
Add this mixture to shortening, etc. mixture. Add chopped nuts.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Check center with toothpick to test for doneness.

title: strawberry shortcakes
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 375° until brown.

title: hot crunch sticks
directions: Mix stuffing crumbs, seed and salt in a shallow dish.
Break biscuits in 3 pieces; roll each third into pencil thin stick, about 4 inches long.
Brush with water; roll in mixture.
Place on a greased sheet.
Bake at 450° about 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
Serve warm.
Makes 30.

title: chili bake
directions: Layer in casserole dish and bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: magic squares
directions: Bake in 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes until marshmallows brown.

title: granny's sugar cookies
directions: Cream together margarine and sugar.
Blend in egg.
Sift together and add to mixture salt, baking powder and flour.
Blend into mixture vanilla.
Cut with cookie cutters and bake on lightly greased cookie sheet in 400° preheated oven for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: new orleans - muffuletta sandwich
directions: Combine mushrooms, olives, pickled vegetables, parsley, garlic, oil, lemon juice, oregano and pepper in a mixing bowl. Refrigerate 4 hours or overnight.
Split bread in half lengthwise and scoop out soft bread from center, leaving an 1-inch shell. Layer bottom of bread with salami, cheese and ham.
Top with olive mixture; cut into quarters to serve.

title: lemon lush
directions: Mix oleo, flour and pecans. Put into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan; bake at 375° for 15 minutes. Combine confectioners sugar, cream cheese and 1 cup whipped topping. Mix and spread on cooled crust. Mix pudding and cold milk. Spread on cream cheese mixture. Spread rest of whipped topping over mixture and refrigerate. Top with chopped pecans if desired.

title: alfredo sauce
directions: Melt butter, add cheese and pepper.
Stir in whipping cream in double boiler.
Remove from heat; whip for about 3 minutes. Portion out in servings of 5 ounces each.
Unused portions may be frozen for future use.

title: date bars
directions: In a medium mixing bowl, thoroughly stir together the flour and baking powder.
Add salt and sugar and stir well.
Add dates; mix with fingers to separate dates.
Stir in nuts and coconut.
In a small mixing bowl, beat eggs enough to blend yolks and whites. Add to flour mixture with butter and vanilla; stir to mix thoroughly.
Turn into a buttered square cake pan (9 x 9-inch) and bake in a 325° oven for 45 minutes.

title: french dressing
directions: Place all ingredients in a screw-top jar.
Shake well.
Store in refrigerator.

title: deviled ham sandwich
directions: Mix all together.
Spread on bread.
(Good on brown wheat bread.)

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Mix together and put in casserole dish.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: venison stew
directions: Dust venison with flour, salt and pepper.
Brown it in oil in a hot skillet.
Remove venison and put it in a large pot.
Add herbs, cover and simmer in wine and beef broth for 2 hours or until tender when tested with a fork.
Saute onions, carrots and garlic.
Add to stew; cover and simmer for another 40 min.
Brown mushrooms in butter; and add to stew and simmer uncovered for 15 min.
Stir in lemon juice and brown sugar.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix Jiffy mix, eggs, sour cream, sugar, corn and margarine together.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: grandma's macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni until tender.
Drain off water.
Add milk, 2 slices American cheese, cheese sauce, butter, salt and pepper. Mix well.
Put in an 8-inch pan.
Top with sliced cheese to cover top.
Set oven on broil.
Place pan in oven until lightly browned.

title: sausage quiche
directions: Mix together and add salt, pepper and parsley to taste.
Turn into buttered 9-inch pie pan. Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: chicken on a diet
directions: Place chicken in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Combine orange beverage and soy sauce, pour over chicken.
Cover and marinate in refrigerator for 8 hours, turning chicken occasionally.
Turn cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until chicken is done, basting occasionally with soy sauce mixture. Makes 5 servings, 3 ounce serving size.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
Take chicken out of broth.
While chicken is cooling, put spaghetti, onions, bell pepper, salt and pepper into broth and cook until done.
Debone chicken and put into spaghetti and add Ro-Tel tomatoes and cheese.
Simmer and stir until cheese has melted.

title: chinese casserole
directions: Saute celery, onion and chicken until done well.
Add remaining ingredients except noodles. Turn into greased 2-quart casserole dish. Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle noodles over top. Bake 5 minutes longer.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Cut in shortening; add milk and mix to a smooth dough.
Turn onto floured surface; divide into 6 portions.
Roll each portion large enough to cover 1 apple.
Place an apple on each piece of pastry.
Mix sugar and cinnamon together.
Spoon some of this mixture into each core cavity.
Moisten edges of pastry and bring up over the apple; seal edges.
Place on greased baking sheet or in shallow pan. Bake at 350° or until apples are tender and pastry is lightly browned.
Remove from baking sheet.
Serve warm with milk or cream.

title: pizza snacks
directions: Brown sausage in skillet on medium heat.
Drain, leaving some grease to keep the cheese from sticking.
Add ketchup, Worcestershire sauce and Italian seasoning to taste.
Turn heat down to low.

title: nacho cheese soup
directions: Brown ground meat, and drain.
Then mix everything in a crock pot.

title: aunt mary's no-bake butterscotch bars
directions: Combine sugar and eggs in saucepan.
Cook over low heat for 5 minutes.
Add butter.
Keep stirring, it scorches easily.
Put graham crackers, marshmallows and coconut in a bowl and mix.
Pour sauce over dry ingredients.
Mix and press into 9 x 13 buttered pan.
Melt butterscotch chips and peanut butter.
Spread on top. Cool.
Cut.
Enjoy.
Freezes well.

title: another really good rice pudding
directions: Cook rice in boiling water for 6 minutes. Strain and cook in pint of milk with vanilla bean for 20 minutes. Dissolve gelatin and sugar in small amount of water.
Mix with rice mixture and chill.
Fold in whipped cream and mold. Serve with strawberries that have been injected with liqueur.

title: overnight coffee cake
directions: Place frozen rolls in Bundt pan. Pour margarine over rolls. Mix pudding (dry), brown sugar and pecans. Sprinkle over rolls. Cover with paper towel or wax paper; leave cake out overnight. The dough rises beautifully by morning. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Invert onto serving plate to serve.

title: chocolate supreme
directions: Melt butter in pan and add flour.
Put in pan and add nuts. Bake 20 minutes at 350° and cool.

title: texas state fair chili
directions: Work the first 4 ingredients well.
Heat the oil in a heavy skillet. Add meat mixture and saute slowly, stirring to cook thoroughly but not too brown. Add the onions and garlic.
Cook until onions and garlic are soft. Add the hot water and simmer 1 hour.
Add the paprika, chili powder, tomato sauce, cumin and chili mix.
Simmer about 1 hour, stirring often. When reheating, do not add water but warm slowly over low heat.

title: baked rainbow trout
directions: In shallow baking dish (1-quart size) combine rice, green onion, 1/2 teaspoon salt, nutmeg, 2 tablespoons orange juice and water.
Place trout on top of rice.
Combine butter, remaining orange juice, salt and pepper to taste.
Melt butter and pour over trout.
Bake uncovered at 400° for 15 minutes or until fish flakes easily.
Garnish with orange slices.

title: rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients; cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: golden hominy
directions: Saute onion in butter until tender.
Add drained hominy, green chilies, sour cream and small amount of shredded cheese.
Pour into a baking dish and bake for 15 minutes, or until cheese melts and is bubbly.

title: pineapple cheese casserole
directions: Drain pineapple.
Save 3 tablespoons of juice. Put pineapple in casserole dish.
Mix sugar, flour and juice together. Pour over pineapple and mix.
Top with cheese.
Mix crushed crackers and butter together.
Spread on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Good with ham, pork chops, anything!

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Start oven at moderate (375°) oven.
Scrub potatoes; rinse and pare.
Cut in halves or thick slices lengthwise.
Brown well in butter in 2-quart flameproof baking dish.
Sprinkle sugar over. Add honey, peel and juice.
Cover dish.

title: shoe peg corn salad
directions: In large bowl, combine ingredients; drain and set aside. Prepare dressing.

title: hamburger-potato casserole
directions: Peel potatoes and slice as for scalloped potatoes.
Place in 4-quart casserole dish.
Add broken up ground beef, both soups, undiluted, and sliced or diced onion.
Mix well.
Cover with foil and bake 2 1/2 hours in 350° oven.
Uncover last 1/2 hour.
Serves 4.

title: orange sherbet jello salad
directions: Bring all ingredients to a boil; cook for 1 minute and let cool.

title: plantation casserole
directions: Pour combined ingredients into a 12 x 8-inch baking dish.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes, until bubbly at edges.
Cover with corn bread batter, leaving center uncovered.
Bake an additional 20 minutes.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add juice and ice cream and stir until melted into jello mixture.
Add oranges and pour into mold or leave in bowl.
Chill thoroughly.

title: elegant scalloped corn
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Stir in eggs, milk and butter, mixing well.
Pour into a greased 2-quart casserole. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 50 minutes. Serves 8.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix ingredients together in large bowl.
Make a "hole" in flour mixture.
Add sugar, shortening, eggs and vanilla.
Mix good in middle first.
Gradually pulling in flour.
Cookie dough can be rolled out on floured board and cut with cutters or can be divided in two or three portions and rolled in wax paper and frozen for quick making cookies.
Bake in 400° oven 8 to 10 minutes.

title: kentucky whiskey cake
directions: Soak cherries and raisins or dates in whiskey overnight.
Cream sugar and butter until fluffy; add egg yolks and beat well.
Add soaked fruit and remaining liquid, reserving a small amount of flour for nuts (add remaining to mixture).
Add nutmeg and baking powder.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Add lightly floured pecans last.
Bake in a large greased tube pan lined with greased paper. Bake 3 to 4 hours (watch baking time) in slow oven (250° to 275°).

title: spiced tea
directions: You can't beat ice tea or lemonade to quench your thirst. sherbert or vanilla ice cream to a glass of chilled tea or lemonade. messy lemon wedge. or honey. cooler.

title: key lime pie
directions: Beat 1 egg white stiff.
Fold into mixture.
Beat 3 egg whites and gradually add 6 tablespoons sugar and 1/2 teaspoon cream of tarter.
Put into baked pie shell and bake until egg whites are golden brown at 350°.
(The egg whites are a meringue to be put over lime mixture.)

title: debbie's butterfinger pie
directions: In your blender or with your mixer, blend crumbled candy bars until smooth.
Fold in 8 ounces Cool Whip until mixed well.
Spoon into pie crust; chill well.
Sprinkle chocolate shavings or put large spoon of Cool Whip on individual pieces of pie before serving.

title: strawberry angel food dessert
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 cup boiling water.
Add slightly thawed strawberries and break up.
Refrigerate until slightly thickened. Meanwhile, break up angel food cake into bite-sized pieces and place half of the pieces in a medium glass bowl.
When strawberry mixture is slightly thickened, put half over the cake in bowl.
Add a layer of Cool Whip.
Repeat layers.
Refrigerate.
Recipe may be doubled for a crowd.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Have all ingredients at room temperature.
Grease the baking sheets lightly.
Sift the flour before measuring.
Sift together the flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix together the shortening, peanut butter, brown sugar and granulated sugar.
Beat until well blended.
Add the egg and vanilla.
Beat well.
Add the sifted dry ingredients.
Mix thoroughly.
Form the dough into balls about 1 inch in diameter.
Place 1 1/2 inches apart on the lightly greased baking sheets.
Press crosswise with a fork to flatten.
Bake in a moderate oven at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes until cookies are delicately browned.
Remove the cookies immediately from the baking sheets.
Cool on a cooling rack.
Yields 3 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Debone chicken; put back in broth.
Add all other ingredients, let boil until the noodles are done.
Put in casserole dish; add sweet milk if it seems too thick.

title: sach's cheese ball
directions: Mix all together.
Form into a ball.
Roll in cracker crumbs (use same cracker as serving).
Let sit in refrigerator overnight or at least 6 to 8 hours.

title: oatmeal chocolate chip cookies
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, soda and salt together.
In a large bowl combine shortening, brown sugar, eggs and water.
Beat until creamy.
Add vanilla.
Gradually add flour mixture.
Mix well. Stir in oatmeal and chocolate chips; mix well.
(Mix nuts in also.)
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 minutes at 375°.
Makes about 12 dozen.

title: smoked salmon a la louis
directions: Lay salmon in dish, skin side down.
Mix garlic powder, black pepper and ginger powder; sprinkle on fish.
Mix brown sugar and salt.
Sprinkle over fish.
Leave overnight.
Put in smoker until fish shine turns dull, approximately 4 to 5 hours, depending on heat.
You may reheat by broiling.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and place in a large casserole.

title: pickled green tomatoes
directions: Put tomatoes in a 4-gallon churn.
Add salt and syrup, then finish filling with cold water.
Place saucer on top of churn to keep tomatoes from floating.
In about 10 to 12 days, they will be ready to eat.
Rinse before serving.
Tomatoes will be firm, but swiveled.

title: asparagus chicken
directions: Place chicken in bottom of casserole dish.
Top with asparagus spears and juice.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake in moderate oven until chicken is done.

title: shopping day quick casserole
directions: Alternate ground beef and onion in casserole.
Pour soup over top and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: strawberry dessert
directions: Cut the top 1/3 of the cake off and set aside.
Make a tunnel in the large ring of cake by removing some of the cake in the center ring.
Save the cake crumbs.
Dissolve the Jell-O in the hot water.
Add the strawberries, cake crumbs and 1/2 of the Cool Whip to this mixture; mix thoroughly and refrigerate until mushy.
Pour this mixture into the tunnel and left over, pour into the center hole.
Place the top on the cake and ice with the remaining Cool Whip.
Garnish with fresh strawberries.
Keep cake refrigerated.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Blend peanut butter and powdered sugar until very fine in large bowl.
Mix instant pudding according to package directions. Sprinkle some peanut butter mixture into each pie shell.
Pour in 1/3 of pudding mixture.
Top with remaining peanut butter mixture and top with whipped cream.
Yields 1 pie.

title: cranberry-banana flip
directions: Combine all ingredients in container of an electric blender. Cover and process until smooth. Serve immediately. Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: chicken and spinach
directions: Mix cheese and mayonnaise.
In 9 x 13-inch greased pan, layer spinach, then chicken and top with mayonnaise mix.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sour cream cookies
directions: Mix ingredients.
Bake at 350° until done.
Make a frosting glaze and spread while warm.

title: butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream together butter and sugar.
Add egg yolks and vanilla.
Mix well. Sift flour and salt together and beat into butter mixture until well mixed.
Bake for about 10 minutes on an ungreased cookie sheet, placing them about 1-inch apart.

title: pistachio salad(club member: brandi cook)
directions: Dissolve pistachio pudding mix over pineapple; mix well.
Add other ingredients and refrigerate.

title: candied pecans(appetizer in microwave)
directions: Place butter in a 1-quart casserole dish.
Microwave on High for 30 to 45 seconds.
Stir in sugar, cinnamon and cloves. Microwave on High for 1 to 2 minutes, or until sugar dissolves. Stir in nuts until coated and microwave 4 to 5 minutes.
Spread on wax paper.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut each biscuit into 4 pieces.
Mix sugar and cinnamon. Roll biscuits in sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Arrange in Bundt pan.
Sprinkle nuts on top.
Melt butter and stir in brown sugar. Pour over biscuits and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix good and roll into balls, walnut size.
Bake 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: speedy spuds
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart casserole, microwave hash browns on 30% for 10 minutes to thaw.
Combine with the next 7 ingredients.
Mix corn flakes and melted butter.
Sprinkle on top.
Microwave on Medium (70%) for 14 to 16 minutes.
Rest 5 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: swedish glog (glug)(or what i did with the recipe received)
directions: If making double batch, double above ingredients.

title: glorified rice
directions: Mix all together and chill.

title: paradise pumpkin pie
directions: On a lightly floured surface, roll pastry to 12-inch circle. Place in 9-inch pie plate.
Turn under edge and flute.
Combine cream cheese, sugar and vanilla, mixing until well blended.
Blend in egg.
Spread onto bottom of pastry shell.
Combine remaining ingredients except syrup and pecans.
Mix well.
Carefully pour over cream cheese mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 5 minutes. Cool.
Brush with maple syrup and top with pecans.
Makes 8 servings.

title: uncle lem's sweet potato souffle
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Boil potatoes until soft.
Peel while still warm.
Place in large mixing bowl.
Add butter, vanilla, sugar and salt.
Mix well.
Add egg yolks.
Mix until sticky adding milk as needed.

title: sourdough whole wheat pan bread
directions: In large bowl, combine milk and boiling water; let cool to about 110°F.
Stir in yeast and let stand until dissolved.
Stir in whole wheat flour, 1 cup of the all-purpose flour and the sourdough starter; beat until smooth and elastic (about 5 minutes).
Cover bowl with plastic wrap and let stand in a warm place until mixture is very bubbly and spongy looking (about 1 hour).

title: peanut butter and jelly muffins
directions: Mix flour, sugar and baking powder in a large bowl.
Put peanut butter and egg in another bowl and beat with a wooden spoon until smooth.
Add milk, a little at a time, stirring after each addition.

title: chocolate dream cake
directions: Beat together all ingredients, except pecans. Fold in chopped nuts. Bake in greased and floured Bundt pan at 350° for 1 hour. Drizzle glaze over warm cake.

title: camping chicken with rice
directions: Place 1 tablespoon rice on a square of heavy-duty foil. Arrange chicken on top.
Season soup with spices; spoon 2 tablespoons soup mixture over chicken.
Wrap and seal tightly. Cook over medium coals for 45 minutes, turning occasionally. Serves 6.

title: raisin bread
directions: Combine raisins, boiling water, soda and butter in bowl.
Let stand overnight.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Fill 3 greased loaf pans 1/2 full.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until bread tests done.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes.
Remove to wire rack to cool.
Yield: 3 loaves.

title: hungry man's potato casserole
directions: Brown and season ground beef and diced onion.
Add mushroom soup and soy sauce.
Place in greased one-quart casserole pan. Place potato rounds on top of ground meat mixture.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: tropical punch
directions: Mix together first 6 ingredients with one option: Into 2 medium tubs, freeze part of the pineapple juice to keep punch cold while serving.
Chill all ingredients the night before.
When ready to serve, mix everything together in a large punch bowl; probably will mix half of first 6 ingredients with half of last 2 ingredients.
Refill punch bowl as needed.
Makes about 4 gallons.

title: bacon corn sticks(or muffins)
directions: Lightly stir bacon into batter.
Bake as directed.

title: cranberry-orange muffins
directions: Stir together flour, 2 tablespoons of sugar, baking powder and salt.
Make a well in the center.
In a small bowl, beat egg slightly; stir in orange juice and oil.
Coarsely chop the cranberries and toss with 2 tablespoons of sugar.
Add egg mixture to dry ingredients and stir just until moistened; fold in cranberries.
Fill muffin tins 3/4 full.
Sprinkle tops with remaining sugar.
Bake at 400° for 18 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: nut bread with egg nog
directions: Sift dry ingredients until well blended.
Combine beaten eggs, egg nog and melted butter.
Add to dry ingredients.
Mix until moistened.
Pour into a 9 x 5 x 3-inch greased pan or 2 smaller pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours for one loaf; 45 minutes for 2 loaves; or until done.

title: fix ahead party burgers
directions: Brown beef in margarine; add onion, salt, pepper, catsup and Worcestershire sauce and cook 5 minutes.
Add cheese and bourbon; remove from heat.
Spread thin layer of mustard and butter on each side of burger buns; fill each with beef mixture and wrap each one in foil and freeze.
Bake frozen burgers anytime people want a fast feast.

title: beef noodle casserole
directions: Brown ground beef.
Saute onions, green peppers and celery. Cook egg noodles according to directions on bag; drain.
Stir together soup, water, sour cream and sauteed vegetables (drain tomatoes) until well blended.
Mix all ingredients together and top with Cheddar cheese.
Place in a 350° oven until hot.

title: mississippi mud or oreo cookie dessert
directions: Mix cookies and melted margarine.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch dish and put in freezer for 20 minutes.
Blend pudding and milk. Fold in Cool Whip.
Spread on cookie mix and freeze 20 minutes. Top with additional crushed cookies.

title: seafood stuffed chicken breast
directions: Saute onion, bell pepper and celery.
Turn burner off.
Add bread crumbs and seafood.
Mix both cans of soup and butter in baking pan.
Stuff chicken breasts with bread crumb mixture.
Lay in baking pan on soup.
Spoon soup mixture on chicken and bake at 350°, covered, for 30 minutes, then uncover and cook an additional 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chili verde
directions: Saute meat and 1 chopped onion with meat. Add rest of ingredients, except cheese. Simmer 2 hours or longer. Can cook all day in crock-pot. Serve with grated cheese sprinkled on top. Good with Fritos lite chips.

title: orange salad
directions: Spoon cottage cheese into mixing bowl.
Sprinkle dry Jell-O over and mix.
Add Cool Whip.
Fold into cottage cheese.
Add drained fruits.
Mix well.
Store in refrigerator.
Makes 10 servings.

title: peanut butter swirl bars
directions: Beat together first 4 ingredients until creamy, then add and blend in remaining ingredients, except chocolate chips.
Blend well.
Spread into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle chocolate chips over top and bake at 350° for 5 minutes.
Remove from oven and run a knife through melted chocolate and batter to marbleize.
Return to oven and bake 25 to 30 minutes longer.

title: ritz cracker yummy snack
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Butter a 9 x 13 pan. Beat egg whites until stiff. Add sugar to egg whites while beating on low. Add vanilla and baking powder. Stir in pecans and crackers with spoon. Put in oven for 15 to 20 minutes. Let cool for 30 minutes before adding topping.

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: Flatten 1/2 chicken breast between wax paper.
Roll ham and cheese in each breast, jelly roll style.
Fasten with toothpicks. Roll in Shake 'n Bake.
Put in shallow baking dish.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Mix water, soup and wine. Pour over chicken.
Bake 60 minutes longer in 350° oven.
Serve with rice.
Serves 4.

title: super strawberry loaves
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease and flour two (9 x 5 x 3-inch) loaf pans.
Combine strawberries, oil and eggs; set aside.
In a large bowl, combine the flour, sugar, cinnamon, salt, baking soda and nuts.
Add strawberry mixture and stir until blended.
Pour into pans.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: salmon-cheese bake
directions: Combine salmon and onion; set aside.
Mix together biscuit mix and water.
Divide in half.
Roll half into an 8-inch square pan. Top with salmon mixture, then Mozzarella cheese.
Roll remaining dough for an 8-inch square top.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Bake at 450° for 15 to 18 minutes.

title: raw tomato relish
directions: Grind vegetables; let drip in bag for 20 minutes.
Add vinegar, sugar and spice.
Can cold in sterile cold jars.
Makes 10 pints.

title: custard velvet pie
directions: Thoroughly mix eggs, sugar, salt and vanilla. Slowly stir in hot milk. Pour into unbaked pastry shell. Dash top with nutmeg. Bake in a very hot oven at 475° for 5 minutes. Reduce heat to 425° and bake 10 minutes longer or until knife inserted halfway between center comes out clean. Cool on rack. Serve cool or chill as desired.

title: southwest soup
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Drain fat.
Add all other ingredients, except cheese.
Let simmer for 30 minutes.
When serving, add grated cheese.

title: mostaccioli and sausage
directions: In large saucepan, brown sausage; pour off fat.
Add onion and green pepper; cook and stir until tender.
Add pasta sauce and Parmesan cheese.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Toss hot cooked mostaccioli with oil to coat.
Serve with sauce.
Garnish as desired.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook spaghetti.
Mix chicken, pimento, green pepper and onion. Pour in soup and broth.
Season with salt and pepper. Add 2 cups cheese and spaghetti.
Stir lightly.
Put rest of cheese on top. Bake at 350° for 1 hour in a casserole dish.

title: golden lemon cheese pie
directions: Beat cheese until smooth and fluffy.
Beat in Eagle Brand until smooth.
Stir in ReaLemon and vanilla.
Pour into crust. Top with topping.
Chill 3 hours.

title: broccoli-cheese chowder
directions: Boil diced potatoes and onion until tender in a small amount of water.
Don't drain.
Add the soup and milk.
Simmer until hot. Can add diced ham or pieces of Polish sausage.
Season to taste.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Bring first 3 ingredients to a boil until soft ball stage. Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients.
Nuts are optional. Stir together and pour into greased pan.

title: three in one dip
directions: Mix all together at medium speed until well blended. Refrigerate.
Serve cold or hot, with tortilla chips or veggies. Makes 2 cups.

title: banana chocolate chip cookies
directions: Blend together shortening, sugar, eggs, chocolate chips and vanilla; mix well.
Add flour, baking powder, salt and baking soda.
Mix well.
Stir in mashed bananas.
Drop by teaspoonful onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: frito salad
directions: Prepare lettuce as for tossed salad.
Drain beans and add tomatoes, onions, cheese and dressing.
Chill 30 minutes to 1 hour before serving.
Crushed Fritos should be added and mixed well immediately before serving.
Generously serves 12.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle 2 cups crushed potato chips on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: copper pennies
directions: Cook carrots (until almost done); drain and cool.
Cut onions and bell pepper in large chunks.
Mix all ingredients together. Cover and let marinate 12 hours.
This will keep in refrigerator up to 2 weeks.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Cook together meat, onion, garlic, chili powder, salt and pepper.
Put meat mixture in casserole.
Cover with grated cheese. Sift flour, salt and baking powder.
Cut in shortening.
Add milk. On floured surface knead dough 6 to 8 times.
Roll to 1/3-inch thickness.
Place on top of meat mixture.
Make a few slashes. Bake in 450° preheated oven until top is brown.

title: dude ranch chicken
directions: Mix chicken, tortilla pieces, soups, Rotel, and green chilies. Spread into sprayed 9x13.
Evenly layer crushed chips, then cheese. Bake at 350° until bubbly, about 30 minutes.
Top with ranch dressing or picante sauce as desired.
Serves 6.

title: beef tips
directions: Cube steak into bite size pieces.
Brown meat in oil and butter.
Saute onion and mushrooms with meat.
Season to taste with garlic salt, Accent and pepper.
Add a little water.
Simmer until tender. Serve over buttered noodles or potatoes.
Great warmed up the next day.

title: pizza
directions: Mix together.
Cut loaves of French bread into small slices. Spoon mixture on bread and bake at 400° for 5 to 7 minutes.
Quick and easy!
Serves 20.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spread nuts and coconut in bottom of greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cake according to directions.
Pour over nuts and coconut.
In a separate bowl mix well the cream cheese, margarine, sugar and vanilla.
Randomly mix this into top of cake mix.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Cake will rise, fall and crack open.
